title: sourdough cinnamon rolls
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients, then add flour one cup at a time, to make a firm dough.

title: methodist corn bread
directions: Sift the first 6 ingredients together, then add the egg, oil and buttermilk.
Stir only until moist.
Pour into greased iron skillet that is lined with bacon.
Bake for 15 minutes at 400°; bake for 15 minutes at 450°.

title: octoberfest sausage brunch
directions: Combine
eggs,	cream,	mustard,
salt and pepper until well blended.
Add
cheese,
sausage
and pepper.	Pour mixture into
8-inch square baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Sprinkle with remaining cheese and bake until cheese melts. Serves 4 to 6.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Boil water; add chicken breasts and cook for 30 minutes.
Cut up into chunks.
In an 8 x 10-inch or larger pan, layer casserole: Broccoli, cut into medium-size pieces; chicken and water chestnuts; soups, mixed together with milk and poured over chicken.
Sprinkle crackers and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serve with rice.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all except catsup together.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour or until done.
Spread catsup on top and bake for about 10 minutes.

title: korean barbecued beef(bulkokee)
directions: Cut beef diagonally across grain into 1/8-inch slices.

title: brownies
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa.
Add eggs and vanilla, beat until smooth.
Mix in flour.
Add butter and mix thoroughly.
Pour into a greased 13x9 pan.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: won ton
directions: Fry hamburger and pork; drain fat.
Chop finely and add other ingredients.
Lay a won ton wrapper on flat surface.
Put about 1 tablespoon filling just below the center and wet edges of dough. Fold one corner of the dough over the filling to make a triangle and pinch edges of dough together to seal.
Pull corners base together and pinch to seal.
Repeat this process until all wrappers are used or filling is used.

title: colonial fried chicken
directions: Combine flour and seasonings; roll the chicken in the flour mixture.
Using a Dutch oven or other heavy deep pan, fry the chicken in shortening at 350° for 15 minutes on each side or until tender.

title: tomato appetizers
directions: Place tomatoes in bowl of chilled vodka.
Serve on toothpicks with kosher salt.

title: orange pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add one egg at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add orange juice, beat well.
Add flour, beat well.
Pour into a greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 325° for one hour or until done.
Yields 15 servings.

title: brandy slush
directions: Mix together and freeze. Serve with 7-Up. Garnish with cherry or orange slice.

title: no-bake butterscotch cookies
directions: Combine sugar, milk and butter in pan.
Boil.
Cook 1 minute. Remove from heat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir.
Drop by teaspoon on waxed paper.

title: world war ii pudding
directions: Cream shortening, vanilla and dark Karo syrup.
Add beaten egg.
Beat well.
Add pudding mix and beat again.
Measure flour, salt and baking powder.
Add to first mixture, alternating with milk.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together, folding in sour cream.
Bake at 325° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: brussels sprouts with bacon
directions: Cook bacon over medium heat for 5 minutes, stirring frequently until crisp.
Stir in pecans and cook 1 minute, until roasted. Drain all but 1 tablespoon fat from skillet; remove bacon and pecans to a paper towel.
Add Brussels sprouts and stir to coat with remaining bacon fat.
Stir in apple juice, cover and bring to a boil over high heat.
Reduce heat to low and simmer 8 to 10 minutes (for frozen) or 10 to 12 minutes (for fresh).
Before serving, add bacon, pecans, salt and pepper.

title: big batch thumbprint cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Knead flavor packet about 10 seconds.
Mix cookie mix, flavor packet, egg and flour in a large bowl until moist (dough will be stiff).
Shape into 1-inch balls; roll in nuts.
Place about 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake until set, 9 to 10 minutes.
Immediately and carefully, press thumb in center of each cookie.
Cool completely on wire rack. Fill thumbprints with frosting and candies.
Makes about 3 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Heat corn and milk together until hot. Gradually stir in eggs. Add 1/2 cup cracker crumbs and minced onion to taste; mix well. Pour into a buttered round casserole dish.

title: christmas cheer punch
directions: Combine sugar and water; bring to a boil.
Continue to cook for 5 minutes.
Cool.
Combine juices.
Add cooled sugar-water mixture.

title: butterscotchies
directions: Melt chips and add peanut butter. In large bowl, get ready marshmallows and chow mein. Grease 9 x 13 pan. Pour chips and peanut butter over noodles. Mix and spread in pan.

title: cauliflower broccoli bake
directions: Combine all except for 2 tablespoons butter and stuffing. Fold in veggies and gently toss.
Put in casserole dish.
Mix stuffing and butter and sprinkle over vegetable mixture.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: key lime pie
directions: Mix together and pour into parbaked pie shell.
Bake at 325° for approximately 20 minutes or until firm almost to the center.

title: orange chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Arrange chicken breasts in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Drizzle the butter evenly over the chicken breasts and sprinkle with paprika.

title: aunt rose's dilly creamy cukes
directions: Peel and thinly slice cucumbers; slice onion and set aside. Mix sour cream, vinegar, sugar, salt, pepper and dill weed.
Add cucumbers and onions; mix well and chill.

title: easy summer punch
directions: Chill
ingredients
thoroughly.
Combine ginger ale and grape juice in punch bowl.
Add fresh strawberries to float in punch as a garnish.

title: hearty italian sausage soup
directions: Brown sausage, green pepper and onion.
In soup pot, combine other ingredients, except macaroni and cheese.
Add browned ingredients.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Add uncooked macaroni and simmer until tender, about 10 minutes.
Before serving, sprinkle cheese on top.
Serves 4.

title: celery soup
directions: Put all ingredients in soup pot and boil until tender.
Cool; put in blender with 1/2 teaspoon margarine.
(Only 14 calories per cup.)

title: hamburger pie casserole
directions: Brown the hamburger and onion in oil.
Place in a casserole dish.
Add tomato soup and green beans.
Spread mashed potatoes on top.
Place in oven at 350° for about 30 minutes or until brown.

title: aunt agnes' "real" coconut cake
directions: In a large bowl, mix all ingredients.
Let stand 2 hours, stirring frequently until sugar is dissolved and "milk" is drawn (it gets really juicy).
Punch holes in layers with fork, stack and fill layers.
Refrigerate leftovers.
Better made one day ahead.

title: party pizza
directions: Brown and drain sausage and beef.
Add cheese and let melt, then add spices.
Spoon onto bread and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Serve or freeze.

title: hostess cupcake filling
directions: Beat for 15 minutes.
Use pastry bag; insert into cupcakes. Frost.

title: oreo cookie cake
directions: Mix pudding and milk.
Place in refrigerator.
Crush cookies (keep out 1/2 cup for garnish).
Place remaining crushed cookies in 9 x 12-inch pan.
Pour melted margarine on top; mix and press into pan.
Mix the cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Fold in 1/2 of Cool Whip and place on top of crust.
Chill for 30 minutes. Put pudding onto cream cheese mixture.
Spread second 1/2 of Cool Whip on top of pudding.
Sprinkle reserved cookie crumbs on top.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: In a pie plate or shallow bowl, combine butter, mustard, worcestershire and salt.
In a plastic bag, combine bread crumbs and cheese.
Dip chicken in butter mixture, then shake in crumb mixture.
Place in an ungreased 13 X 9 baking pan.
Drizzle with any remaining butter mixture.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until chicken is no longer pink and juices run clear.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Prepare cake and pudding according to package directions.
Then crumble one layer of cake in bottom of punch bowl.
Pour one-half of pudding mix over cake.
Crumble other layer of cake into bowl and pour rest of pudding mix over that layer.
Add pineapple, then cherry pie filling, then topping.
Sprinkle nuts on top and chill.

title: old southern grated sweet potato pudding
directions: In a heavy iron skillet, melt butter.
Mix all ingredients, adding the beaten eggs last.
Bake in skillet at 375°.
Stir several times while baking.
Bake 40 minutes.
The iron skillet makes a crunchier crust.

title: mama's chocolate frosting
directions: Mix sugar, milk and cocoa in saucepan.
Bring to boil.
Cook 4 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add butter and stir until frosting begins to thicken.
Spread on layers.

title: sam's pesto sauce
directions: In a blender or food processor, whirl to a paste the basil, parsley, pine nuts, olive oil and cheese.
Add salt and pepper, blend to a smooth consistency.
Serve with cheese tortellini or linguine.

title: twinkies delight
directions: Split Twinkies lengthwise and arrange with split sides up in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Prepare pudding as directed on box.
Pour over Twinkies.
Layer bananas on top and top with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle nuts on top.

title: charlie's crayfish
directions: Chop onions, bell pepper and celery.
Melt margarine in pot; add chopped vegetables.
Saute.
Add crayfish; squeeze juice of lemon over crayfish.
Sprinkle with Tony's seasoning.
Simmer for 20 minutes, covered.
Add soups, Ro-Tel, Worcestershire, Tabasco and soybean sauce.
Simmer 20 minutes, covered.
Serve over rice.

title: raspberry bars
directions: Cream the butter and brown sugar until fluffy.
Mix dry ingredients (except oatmeal) and stir into creamed mixture.
Add oatmeal and 1 tablespoon of water.
Mix until crumbly.
Firmly press half of mixture into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread with jam. Stir 1 tablespoon of water into remaining half of crumb mixture.
Sprinkle over top.
Pat smooth.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: yogurt(homemade)
directions: Boil milk until it comes to boil, then take off stove and put in bowl. Add already done yogurt (called starter), then when boiled milk gets cooled down somewhat (when you can count to ten and still hot but not too hot), mix together with milk. Cover well and leave 2 hours or more.

title: tuna italian
directions: Cook onion in small amount of oil until tender, but not brown. Add soup, milk and cheese; heat and stir.
Break tuna into chunks, add with remaining ingredients.
Pour into greased 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with additional Parmesan cheese and paprika. Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Top with minced parsley and ripe olive slices.
Pass lemon wedges to squirt over.
Makes 6 servings.

title: pecan delight pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add vanilla, salt and sugar.
Beat until incorporated.
Add crackers and pecans.
Pour in greased pie plate and bake 30 minutes.
Let pie get completely cool.
Top with whipped topping.
Chopped pecans may be sprinkled on top.

title: grilled sesame chicken breasts
directions: Wash chicken pieces, pat dry and set aside.
Combine all remaining ingredients in shallow pan (or ziploc bag).
Mix well. Add chicken, turning to coat; cover and marinate in refrigerator 4 hours.
Remove chicken from marinade, reserving marinade.
Grill 4 to 5 inches from medium hot coals 12 to 15 minutes basting frequently or broil in oven.

title: chicken 'n' rice(on the grill)
directions: Place each chicken breast on 14-inch square of double thickness heavy duty aluminum foil.
Mix soup and rice, spoon over chicken breast.
Sprinkle with paprika if you wish.
Wrap securely in foil.
Place on grill 5 inches from hot coals.
Cook about 40 minutes or until done, turning once.

title: cajun spices
directions: Mix all ingredients and store in a tightly covered container. Makes 1/2 cup.

title: chicken piccata
directions: Unfold fillets and place, one at a time, between 2 sheets of wax paper; pound with a flat-surfaced mallet until about 1/4-inch thick.
Combine flour, salt and pepper; coat breast fillets with mixture.
Melt margarine in large skillet over medium heat; add chicken and cook 3 to 4 minutes per side until done.

title: peppermint rounds
directions: Beat butter at medium speed with an electric mixer until creamy; gradually add sugar, beating well.
Add egg and vanilla, beating well.
Combine flour and salt; add to butter mixture. Stir in oats and candy.
Cover and chill 1 hour.
Divide dough in half.
Roll each to 1/8-inch thickness on a surface dusted with powdered sugar.
Cut with a 2 1/2-inch cookie cutter; place on greased, foil-lined cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes; remove to wire racks to cool.

title: cranberry punch
directions: Chop ice cream into small pieces and then add other ingredients.
Serves 35.

title: hush puppies
directions: Add milk to make stiff batter.
Drop by spoon into hot fat and fry until brown.
Especially good with fish.

title: potato cake (chocolate)
directions: *Put chocolate squares in oven or microwave to melt.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Combine sugar and shortening, then add bananas and eggs.
Mix well.
Dissolve baking soda in buttermilk, then add to mixture. Add salt and nuts.
Mix well.
Gradually add flour, a little at a time while mixing well.
Pour in greased and floured bread pan. Cook at 350° for 1 hour.

title: german chocolate pound cake
directions: Mix cake mix, oil, water and eggs together on low speed with mixer about one minute.
Scrape sides and bottom of bowl. Continue beating on low speed for 2 minutes.
Add container of frosting and continue beating on low speed for two more minutes. Grease bundt pan and pour in batter.
Bake at 350° about 1 hour. Let cake cool in pan.

title: potato soup
directions: Dice or slice the potatoes.
Add remaining ingredients, except milk.
Simmer to well done.
Mash lightly.
Add milk.
Cook just to boiling.

title: rice turkey casserole
directions: Put all into a 9 x 13-inch pan sprayed with Pam. Stir together and bake, covered, for 1 hour at 350°.

title: baked beans and beef
directions: Cook bacon. Brown ground beef. Mix bacon and beef with all other ingredients. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: cheese ball
directions: Blend all ingredients and form ball.
Roll in finely chopped nuts.
Chill.

title: apple brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch jelly roll pan.
Mix flour, baking soda, salt and cinnamon in a large bowl. Whisk oil and eggs in another bowl until blended and smooth. Stir in sugar and vanilla. Stir in flour mixture until blended.
Stir in apples, nuts and raisins. Spread evenly in pan. Bake 40 to 50 minutes until top is golden.
Let cool on wire rack. Dust with powdered sugar.

title: salted peanut crisps
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix thoroughly in bowl shortening, brown sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Set aside.
Stir in another bowl flour, salt and baking soda.
Mix the dry ingredients into the shortening mixture.
Stir in the salted peanuts.
Drop by rounded teaspoons about 2 inches apart on greased baking sheet.
Grease the bottom of a glass.
To flatten each cookie, dip glass in sugar and press down on cookie.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 6 dozen cookies.

title: apple slice cake
directions: Beat sugar and eggs together.
Add flour, salt and soda.
Stir in other ingredients.
Bake in glass dish for 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.

title: red punch
directions: Mix 2 cups sugar, Kool Aid, and pineapple juice.
Add ginger ale and ice.
Serve.

title: busy day chicken casserole
directions: Place rice in bottom of casserole. Lay chicken pieces on top. Mix soup and water and pour over chicken.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 6.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Put peanut butter, butter and chocolate chips in bowl.
Place in microwave for 2 to 3 minutes or until it comes to a boil. Stir in powdered sugar to desired thickness.
Spread onto buttered platter.

title: horseradish sauce
directions: Melt margarine and stir in flour.
Slowly add broth, stirring. Stir in rest of ingredients and simmer until thickened.
Do not boil.

title: tortilla roll-ups
directions: Mix all together.
Spread on tortillas.
Roll up tortilla and slice about 1-inch thick.
Serve with hot sauce or salsa.

title: rainy day dinner
directions: Combine all in pan.
Add water.
This is delicious with meat broth or beef bouillon cubes.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: great gramma smith's molasses cookies
directions: Combine sugar, salt, ginger, molasses and shortening. Dissolve soda in water and add flour.
Mix all together and let stand until thoroughly cold.
Roll into balls.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: date pecan balls
directions: Cream oleo and sugar.
Add vanilla and mix well.
Add flour and mix.
Mix in pecans and dates.
Roll teaspoonfuls of dough in balls.
Refrigerate balls for 1 to 2 hours.
Bake at 350° on greased cookie sheet for 20 minutes.
Remove from oven and roll balls in powdered sugar.
Sprinkle them again with powdered sugar when cookies have cooled.

title: round steak sauerbraten
directions: Cut meat in 1-inch squares.
Brown meat in 1 tablespoon hot shortening.
Remove meat from skillet.
Add gravy mix and 2 cups water.
Bring to boiling, stirring constantly.
Stir in next 6 ingredients, 1/2 teaspoon salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper.
Add meat. Turn into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Remove bay leaf.
Serve on noodles.
Makes 5 or 6 servings.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Saute onion and celery in oleo.
Cook broccoli as directed on package; drain.
Combine remaining ingredients with onion, celery and broccoli.
Pour into a greased shallow 2-quart casserole. Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: picnic beans
directions: Drain beans and place in 2-quart casserole.
Dice bacon and fry until crisp.
Remove bacon from pan.
To the bacon grease, add the water, sugar, dry mustard and onions.
(If bacon is very fat, all the grease does not have to be used.)
Simmer 10 to 15 minutes, stirring frequently.
Pour over beans; add bacon and mix well.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 1 hour.
Stir once or twice while baking.

title: deep-dish pizza casserole
directions: Cook hamburger and onion. Drain grease. Add water and tomato paste. Simmer 10 minutes. Spread biscuits in dish that is greased to make crust. Pour mixture over biscuits and add cheese. Cook at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: baskin robbins dessert
directions: Mix ingredients and press into pan.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni.
Rinse and drain.
Mix together green pepper, onion, carrot and pimiento and add to macaroni.
Mix together Eagle Brand milk, sugar, vinegar, mayonnaise and salt. Pour over macaroni mixture.
Refrigerate before serving.
Makes lots!

title: cabbage surprise
directions: Cut cabbage into small wedges.
Boil until tender.
Drain. Fry bacon until crisp.
Crumble and sprinkle over cabbage along with cheese.

title: pickled eggs
directions: In a saucepan, combine all of ingredients.
Bring to a boil; simmer 10 minutes.
Cool.
In a quart jar, layer 9 shelled, hard-cooked eggs and 1 medium onion, sliced.
Fill jar with pickling brine.
Cover.
Refrigerate 48 hours before using.
Keeps 2 months refrigerated.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Microwave first 3 ingredients for 3 minutes. Turn and bake 3 minutes more. Add last ingredients. Stir and microwave 10 minutes. Microwave on High setting.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Melt margarine in large saucepan.
Add onion and green pepper. Saute for 5 minutes.
Add hamburger; cook, stirring, until lightly browned.
Add mixed vegetables, soup and 3 cans of water. Add any diced, leftover vegetables desired.
Stir in pasta. Season with salt, pepper, sugar and Worcestershire sauce.
Simmer until vegetables are tender and soup is thick.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: bernaise sauce
directions: Boil together vinegar, wine, shallots, 1/2 tablespoon dried tarragon and seasoning until reduced to 2 tablespoons.
Strain, reserving liquid, and cool.
In a blender, put yolks, lemon juice and reserved liquid.
Mix at high speed.
While mixer runs, add butter in a steady stream.
When blended, add fresh tarragon.
Keep warm on top of double boiler to thicken.
Great on steak and shrimp kabobs!

title: jimmy carter cake
directions: Layer #1: Work flour and margarine together as for pie crust. Add peanuts and press into bottom of 9 x 13 pan. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Cool.

title: lazy daisy cake
directions: Combine eggs, sugar and vanilla. Beat until thick.
Add sifted dry ingredients.
Heat milk and butter to boiling point.
Add to mixture. Put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: cheese straws
directions: Roll and cut into very small biscuits or put into a cookie maker.
Sprinkle with sesame seed; cook at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
In separate bowl, mix flour, potato chips and remaining ingredients until blended.
Drop by teaspoon onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes.

title: chicken-n-dressing casserole
directions: Cook chicken in boiling water until tender.
Remove from broth.
Strain broth, reserving 2 2/3 cups.
Bone chicken and cut into small pieces.
Combine chicken soup with half the broth; mix well.
Combine mushroom soup with remaining broth; mix well. Combine stuffing mix and butter; reserve 1/2 cup for garnish.

title: jb's hearty breakfast waffles
directions: In a very large bowl stir together the flour, oats, baking powder, cinnamon and salt. In a small bowl stir together the eggs, milk, butter and brown sugar. Add to flour mixture and stir until blended.

title: hot german potato salad
directions: Saute onion and celery in bacon drippings until onion are limp. Add next five ingredients.
Cook 2 minutes.
Add potatoes, mayonnaise, eggs and bacon.
Toss lightly.
Serve hot and garnish with olives.

title: shoo-fly cake
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients by hand.
Take out 1 cup crumbs for top.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Mix liquid and pour over crumbs. Beat and put in pan.
Put crumbs on top and bake for 50 minutes at 350°.

title: beef noodle casserole
directions: Brown beef in butter.
Add garlic, sugar, salt, pepper and tomato sauce.
Cook over low heat for 15 minutes.
Cook noodles according to package directions; drain.
Mix onions with cream cheese and sour cream.
Cool meat mixture and noodles.
Grease 2-quart casserole dish.
Alternate layers of noodles, cheese mixture and meat mixture.
Repeat.
Sprinkle top with grated cheese.
Bake for 30 minutes or until cheese is bubbly in 350° oven.

title: snicker doodles cookies
directions: Cream together shortening, 3 c. sugar, eggs & vanilla.

title: mawe's fudge
directions: Put in skillet cocoa, sugar and salt and stir.
Add butter, vanilla, and milk.
Bring to a boil, stirring frequently.
Cook to 232° or soft-ball stage.
Remove from heat and beat until thick. Turn into buttered pan.
Cut squares before it gets too hard.

title: zucchini cake
directions: Beat eggs and sugar.
Then add the rest of ingredients.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool and frost with cream cheese.

title: sauteed trout
directions: Heat butter in large skillet; add fish and brown on one side about 3 minutes, then turn over and cook until flaky.
Place fish on a heated platter.
Place almond slivers and lemon juice in skillet and cook 2 to 3 minutes, until almonds are toasted.
Pour almond mixture over fish.

title: apple crisp
directions: Arrange apple slices in a greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan and sprinkle with lemon juice.
Combine flour, sugar, cinnamon and oatmeal.
Add melted butter and mix until crumbly.
Sprinkle over apples.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes or until apples are tender and top is golden brown.
Makes 5 to 6 servings.

title: lasagna with cilantro
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Saute mushrooms, onion and garlic in olive oil.
Split this mixture in half and set one aside.
Add to the remaining (in large skillet) the tomato sauce, paste and tomatoes.
Add also the oregano, basil, salt, pepper, bay leaf, red wine and fresh cilantro.
Let simmer for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: red devil
directions: Make toast; put aside.
Heat soup with a little milk.
Add grated cheese; stir until cheese is melted (should be a little thick).
Arrange toast points on plate; spoon mixture onto toast. This is good for lunch with a salad.

title: bourbon st beans
directions: 1. Soak beans overnight. Drain water and place beans in crock pot. Add fresh water until beans are covered.
2. Saute onions, garlic, and peppers in olive oil and add
to crock pot. 3. Add worcestershire sauce and slow cook for 2 hours.
4. Add hot sauce, salt, and pepper to taste. Dice ham and
add before slow cooking for 2 hours or until beans are
at desired consistency.

title: ice cream cake(low-fat!)
directions: This cake should be made 2 days ahead.
In 3 bowls, break cake into bite-size pieces.
Sprinkle each bowl with one box of dry Jell-O.
Layer in tube pan as follows:

title: chocolate peanut butter drops
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Shape into balls and chill for awhile.
Melt chips, Hershey bar and paraffin over low heat or double boiler.
Dip balls in chocolate.
Cool on wax paper.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Sift together sugar, flour, soda, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg and cloves.
Add to dry ingredients oil, eggs and vanilla.
Beat well, then add apple, nuts and raisins.
Mix well.
Pour into greased pans (1 Bundt or 2 loaf or 4 mini).
Bake at 375° for 1 hour or so, 35 to 40 minutes for mini pans.

title: holy guacamole!
directions: Slice avocadoes in half; remove skin and toss; remove pit and save.
Combine all ingredients in large bowl.
Blend until mixture is slightly lumpy.
To keep guacamole from turning brown, either squeeze juice of 1/2 lemon over top or place avocado pit in mixture.
Cover tightly and refrigerate.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: frozen caramel cheesecake
directions: Beat cream cheese and Eagle Brand together.
Add Cool Whip to mixture.
Pour 1/4 of this mixture into each pie crust.
Drizzle 1/4 of caramel on top of each pie.
Melt margarine in skillet, add coconut and pecan pieces, stirring until toasted.
Sprinkle 1/4 of this mixture on top of caramel on each pie.
Repeat each step, using remainder of cream cheese, caramel, coconut and toasted nuts.
Freeze and serve frozen.

title: cheese ball appetizer
directions: In a medium bowl combine all ingredients except nuts.
Beat until smooth and creamy.
Shape into 2 balls, approximately 4 inches.
Roll cheese balls in chopped nuts.
Store in refrigerator. Serve with crackers.

title: burger pizza
directions: Combine ground chuck, bread crumbs, liquid nonfat dry milk, onion, egg and salt.
Mix lightly but thoroughly.
Press on 12-inch pizza pan.
Form 1/2-inch rim around edge.
Spread pizza sauce over meat mixture.
Sprinkle with cheeses and choice of pizza toppers. Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Drain off fat. Cut into wedges.
Makes 1 (12-inch) pizza.

title: barbecue meatballs
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and shape into meatballs.
Place in a baking dish.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over the meatballs; bake for 45 minutes in 350° oven.

title: spaghetti
directions: Brown ground chuck and onion.
Add salt, pepper, oregano and red pepper. Let simmer for 5 minutes.
Add jar of Ragu sauce.
Let simmer for 30 minutes.
Prepare spaghetti according to directions.

title: butterscotch cookies
directions: Melt sugar and butter in double boiler. Mix other ingredients. Cook at 325 for 25 minutes. Line pan with wax paper and turn out on waxed paper while hot. When cool, cut into squares.

title: chicken and chorizo chili
directions: In one large pot on medium heat add 1/2 cup of vegetable or corn oil, add onion, peppers, parsley, chicken, chilli powder, salt, pepper, ground cumin and brown sugar; stir and let mixture cook for about 10 minutes, continuing to stir occasionally.
Add garlic and pork chorizo, beans and all the tomatoes.
Continue to cook on medium heat stirring often, about 30 minutes or until tomatoes get soggy.
Serve with tortillas or hearty bread.
Feeds 8-10 people.

title: low-fat carrot cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix cinnamon, flour, baking soda and baking powder together; set aside in a small bowl.
Grate and drain carrots.
Mix sugar and applesauce together in bowl.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add carrots and mix well.
Mix in a little at a time the flour mixture, to blend, until all of the flour mixture is added.

title: easy fudge
directions: Melt chips, milk and salt over low heat.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Pour in wax paper lined 8 or 9-inch square pan.
Chill for 2 hours or until firm.
Peel off paper and cut into squares. Store loosely covered at room temperature.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grease pie plate. Beat all ingredients just until smooth. Pour into pie plate. Bake in preheated oven about 30 minutes. Serve with fresh fruit.

title: fudge brownies
directions: Cream shortening and add sugar.
Beat in eggs and blend in syrup.
Stir in flour and nuts.
Bake in 11 x 16-inch greased pan at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Pre-pare jello according to package, but only use 3 1/2 c. water.
Partially set jello.
In mixing bowl on low speed, beat cream cheese and crushed pineapple.
Add jello.
Fold in softened ice cream or sherbet.
Then fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into mold. Chill.
Decorate with drained cherries.
Make a day ahead.

title: cherry crunch
directions: Combine crumbs, sugar, cinnamon and margarine.
Reserve 3/4 cup for top.
Press remaining mixture in a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish, covering sides and bottom.
Heat flour and cherries until thickened.
Pour over crumb-lined dish.
Top with meringue made from egg whites.
Sprinkle with reserved crumb mixture.
Bake at 275° for 35 minutes.
Serve with ice cream, if desired.
Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Beat together. Pour into deep baking dish. Add 2 cups fresh fruit. Slice 1 stick butter and place on top of fruit. Bake at 425° for 45 minutes.

title: pasta and fagiolo(pasta and beans)
directions: Prepare spaghetti twists as directed; drain and put into 3-quart casserole.
Heat sausages and 1/4 cup water to boiling; cover and cook 5 minutes.
Remove cover; continue cooking until well browned.
Drain sausage on paper towel.
Cut into 1-inch chunks and add to casserole.
In sausage dripping, cook onion and garlic until tender, stirring occasionally.
Add kidney beans, tomatoes with liquid, oregano and 1/4 cup water.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat, cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Add bean mixture to spaghetti mixture; mix gently.
Cover casserole and bake 50 to 55 minutes until hot and bubbly.
Makes 8 servings; 455 calories a serving.

title: choco-nut delights
directions: Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Cream butter and sugars. Cream well.
Add egg and vanilla.
Mix well.
Blend in dry ingredients.
Spread in ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes.
Sprinkle immediately with chocolate morsels. Let stand 2 minutes.
Spread to cover.

title: glazed beef short ribs
directions: Trim excess fat from ribs.
Make two vertical deep cuts into meat on each rib.
Combine ribs with tomato juice, sugar, vinegar, salt, celery seed, Worcestershire sauce and onion.
Grate 2 teaspoons peel from orange.
Squeeze to get juice.
Add peel and juice to beef.
Mix well; cover and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat. Simmer 1 hour and 20 minutes or until beef is tender.
Transfer ribs to platter.
Cover to keep warm.
Spoon off surface fat from sauce.
Mix flour with water and stir into sauce.
Cook, stirring, until it thickens.
Pour over beef.
Makes 4 servings.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Combine diced chicken, tomatoes, cheese, onions and seasonings.
Dip chips into chicken broth and line them along flat baking dish; sides and bottom.
Cover with chicken mixture.
Add soup and bake until completely hot at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
For less spicy and moist, drain Ro-Tel tomatoes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Mix all ingredients together in large bowl.
Stuff each pepper with ground meat mixture.
If any meat mixture is left, you can make balls.
In a Dutch oven, put 2 cans of tomato soup and juice from whole tomatoes and 1 can of water.
Cook on top of stove on medium heat for 1 hour (covered).
Use tomato soup mixture for gravy.

title: spinach mushroom squares
directions: Cook onions and mushrooms in butter in a large skillet until soft.
Beat eggs until frothy.
Stir in cooled onions and mushrooms, spinach, bread crumbs, soup, 2 tablespoons cheese and spices until well combined.
Spread mixture in a buttered casserole dish and sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 1 hour.
Yields 6 servings.

title: swedish steak
directions: Use beef that is not too fatty or cheap.
Choose a middle grade of beef.
Put enough margarine in pan so meat will not stick; brown on both sides.
I put a little vinegar on both sides to cut enzymes.
Also, I put Adolph's tenderizer on with spices. When meat is browned, cover with water enough to cover all meat in frying pan but not to overflow the sides.
Cut up celery and onion; put in with meat.
Keep water enough so will not run dry. Turn every so often to keep even cooking.
When you can cut meat with fork and it looks tender and really falls apart, it is done. You can put thickener in, if you want.
Put 2 tablespoons flour in 1/2 cup water into a covered jar; shake well.
All flour lumps will smooth out.
You may have to ad more flour.
Cover pan while cooking on low flame; simmer.
Continue your dinner with a salad and another vegetable.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until fluffy.
Add sugar, a little at a time.
Add vanilla, oil, zucchini and pineapple, a little at a time.
Mix together the flour, baking soda, baking powder, cinnamon and allspice.
Add to zucchini mixture, a little at a time.
Stir in mixture of fruit and nuts.
Pour into 2 greased, floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, or until done.
Test with a toothpick; bake longer, if necessary.
Let set on rack for 10 minutes before removing from pans.
Cool thoroughly.
Loaves can be wrapped and frozen for weeks.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Measure 1/2 cup pecans; set aside.
Cream the cream cheese; add remaining ingredients.
Form into ball.
Roll in 1/2 cup pecans.
Refrigerate before serving.
Serve with Town House crackers.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni; drain.
While hot, mix with oil and vinegar. Mix in remaining ingredients slowly.
Chill before serving.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: In a large bowl, blend pudding, milk and Cool Whip.

Using a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan, put a layer of graham crackers, then pour half of the mixture and spread evenly. Add another layer of graham crackers, then use the other half of the mixture and a layer of graham crackers. Frost.
Freeze for 2 hours.
Set out 1/2 hour to 45 minutes before serving.

title: green rice
directions: Mix and pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pecan puffs
directions: Beat egg whites.
Add sugar, vanilla, then the pecans.
Drop 1/2 teaspoonfuls on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 300° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: pineapple zucchini bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients and pecans.
Set aside.
Beat eggs lightly in a large bowl.
Add sugar, oil and vanilla and beat until creamy.
Stir in pineapple and zucchini.
Add dry ingredients and stir until well moistened.
Spoon into 2 well-greased and floured 8 x 4 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool in pans 10 minutes, then turn out on rack and cool thoroughly.
Yields 2 loaves.

title: mini peanut butter tarts
directions: Combine butter, sugars, egg, peanut butter and vanilla in a mixing bowl.
Beat until smooth.

title: peach cheesecake
directions: Mix together whip cream, cream cheese, vanilla, lemon juice and sugar. Spread into crust. Top with peaches and cover with glaze. Chill for 1 hour.

title: squash casserole
directions: Boil squash in salted water until soft. Drain well. Mash squash. Stir in onion, eggs, 2 cups of cheese and 1 1/2 cups crushed crackers. Place in a 9 x 9-inch greased casserole dish. Top with remaining crackers and cheese. This can be made 2 days in advance, just refrigerate. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes or until puffed and light brown.

title: mountain dew cake
directions: Mix cake, pie filling, oil, eggs and Mountain Dew.
Makes 3 layers.
Cook for 30 minutes at temperature on cake mix box.
Can also be made in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: chocolate creams(marquise au chocolat - france)
directions: Break chocolate up.
Place in basin over a pan of warm water. Add brandy, water and vanilla. Stir and mix well.
When smooth, add butter, in small pieces add 3 egg yolks only.

title: stuffed chicken breasts with spinach, ricotta and cheddar
directions: Saute onion in a teaspoon butter and combine with the other ingredients.
Place breasts skin side up.
Loosen skin from one side of breast and stuff 1/3 cup of filling under skin.
Continue with other breasts.
Bake in buttered dish for 30 to 35 minutes until golden brown.
Cool and slice for serving.

title: red rice supreme
directions: Fry bacon until crisp in a large iron skillet.
Fry sausage in a separate pan until done.
Discard sausage drippings.
Pour off excess bacon drippings, but leave enough to cover the onion and bell pepper and saute on medium high heat for 3 minutes.
Add tomatoes, water, and seasonings.
Bring to a boil.
Cover skillet; lower heat and cook for 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add cornstarch mixture, stirring until thickened.
When thick and creamy, add rice, crumbled bacon, and sausage.
Mix well.
Pour into greased casserole dish.
Bake in a preheated 350 degree oven for 25 minutes.

title: squash puffs
directions: Combine squash and egg.
Add all other ingredients, except oil, and mix until well blended.

title: spareribs and sauerkraut
directions: Brown ribs in skillet.
Have ribs cut in pieces.
Add ingredients.
Place in covered baking pan.
Bake approximately 1 1/2 hours.
Put kraut in pan.
Lift meat so kraut will be under ribs.
Cook for approximately 30 minutes longer.
Serves 6.

title: brown rice and broccoli casserole
directions: In a microwave-safe dish, combine onion, garlic and olive oil. Cook, uncovered, on High for 1 minute.
Stir in rice (if uncooked rice is used, add water), orange juice, water chestnuts and tamari.
Microwave, uncovered, on High for 5 minutes.
Stir in broccoli and mushrooms.
Cover and cook on High 4 to 5 minutes until liquid is absorbed.

title: microwave macaroons
directions: Combine ingredients in 2-quart glass mixing bowl.
Microwave on High 6 or 7 minutes until mixture loses its gloss.
Stir 3 or 4 times.
Drop by teaspoon on to waxed paper pressing to form cookie.
Cool.
Store in airtight container.

title: fat-free chips
directions: Mix together herbs.
Bring a large pot of water to a boil. Fill a small bowl with cold water.
Add 4 wonton skins to boiling water at a time.
After 20 seconds, remove and add to cold water. Arrange on a clean towel to drain.
Continue with all wrappers as desired.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Cook the chicken breasts (with skin left on) in the water until tender. Remove chicken. Add the bouillon cubes and chicken soup to broth. Heat until it comes to a rolling boil. Debone chicken and add back to broth.

title: terrific grilled chicken
directions: Marinate chicken overnight in the refrigerator with Italian dressing in a covered pan.
Grill at medium to low heat, until chicken is golden brown and tender, 15 to 25 minutes.

title: baked chicken casserole
directions: Press the four crescent rolls into 9-inch quiche pan.
Combine the rest of the ingredients and bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: oatmeal crackers
directions: Roll thin as possible.
Cut into squares and bake a light brown in a quick oven.

title: butter pound cake made simple
directions: Mix
well,
bake in greased and floured Bundt pan 1 1/4 hours at 325°.

title: sour cream pie
directions: Mix and pour batter in one large pie plate or tin.
Mix 1/2 cup brown sugar, about 2 tablespoons flour and 1 stick butter to moisten well.
Put this on top of pie.
Bake slow at 325° or 350° for about 40 or 45 minutes.

title: yum yum sweet potatoes
directions: Mix thoroughly; put in baking dish.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar, flour and soda and mix well.
Add fruit cocktail; pour in greased baking dish.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: ambrosia salad
directions: Mix all ingredients but cherries together and chill overnight. Garnish with cherries before serving.
Keep refrigerated.

title: judi's ham chowder
directions: Bring cauliflower and chicken broth to a boil.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Stir in soup and cream over low heat.
In small bowl, mix flour and water until smooth.
Stir into soup mixture.
Add pepper, parsley and ham.
Heat thoroughly.
Serve immediately.

title: chinese spaghetti
directions: Heat 3 Tbsp. oil in wok, brown the ginger and 1/2 c. green onion, then add meat and brown together.
Mix together the bean (or hoisin) and soy sauces, add this mixture to the meat, and stir fry briefly.
Then add rice wine, sugar, MSG, and 1 Tbsp. sesame oil.
Add the chicken broth and simmer for about 3 minutes, until the sauce becomes thick and shiny.
Put mixture in a serving bowl and set aside.

title: pasta putanesca
directions: Cook and drain linguine.
Drain tomatoes and cut in half, squeezing out as much liquid as possible . Combine tomatoes and olive oil in skillet.
Bring to boil and add remaining ingredients, one at a time, stirring frequently.
Reduce heat and cook until sauce has thickened.
Serve over hot pasta with additional cilantro.
Serves 4.

title: bean casserole
directions: Drain butter beans and kidney beans.
Mix everything together and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: chili
directions: Brown ground beef with large onion.
Mix other ingredients in slow cooker, add beef and onion.
Cook in slow cooker for several hours.

title: dessert taco chips
directions: Shake tortilla chips with cinnamon, nutmeg and sugar in large bag.
Drain mandarins and pat dry with paper towels.
Place chips on platter.
Surround with orange sections.
Put pie filling in small dish for dipping.

title: peach shake
directions: Mix all ingredients in a blender or a food processor until smooth!
Serves 1.

title: nut strudel
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup warm water.
Mix butter, sugar, sour cream, egg yolks and flour with the yeast and water.
Mix dough well and let it rise for 2 to 2 1/2 hours.
Mix nuts and confectioners sugar together.
Beat 4 egg whites until stiff and add to nut mixture.
If too thick, add a little milk.
Roll dough 1/8-inch thick and spread with nut mixture.
Roll tight.
Let rise again until double in size.
Bake in a greased pan at 350° for about 20 or 25 minutes.
Makes 2 rolls.
Can be iced.

title: penny carrots
directions: Combine soup, sugar, vinegar, oil, Worcestershire sauce and mustard.
Bring to a boil.
Cook for 15 minutes.
Do not scorch. Layer carrots, pepper, onion and celery.
Pour sauce over and serve cold.

title: lemon pound cake
directions: Dissolve jello in water.
Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: orange glazed oatmeal muffins
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, salt and sugar and sift.
Add quick oats; set aside.
Combine egg, milk and margarine and add to dry ingredients, stirring just enough to dampen flour.
Distribute batter evenly into 12 greased muffin tins.
Sprinkle with a little brown sugar and bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Remove from pans; cool inverted on rack.

title: aunt myrtle's goodies
directions: Melt the caramels with the milk and set aside. Combine the flour, oatmeal, brown sugar, baking soda and salt. Melt the butter and pour over the flour mixture, mixing well. Divide in half, and spread half the dough in the bottom of a 9 x 9-inch cake pan. Bake at 350° for 10-15 minutes.

title: savory turkey loaf(low-fat)
directions: Mix turkey, tomato juice, oats, egg, onions, celery salt and Worcestershire sauce together.
Place in greased baking dish. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: banana bread
directions: Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Makes 2 (1 pound 4 ounce) loaves.
I add a handful of pecans and raisins (if you have).

title: chicken stuffed shells
directions: Cook shells according to directions on box.
Prepare Stove Top stuffing according to directions; then combine with the chicken and mayonnaise.
Stuff shells with this mixture.
Place stuffed shells in a large baking dish.
Cover with the cream of chicken soup diluted with 3 cans of water (or broth from cooked chicken). Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes in a 4-quart baking dish (until soup is real bubbly).
Remove from oven and enjoy.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Preheat electric skillet to 380°.
Dredge meat cubes in flour mixed with salt and pepper.
Brown meat in 2 tablespoons butter. Add chopped onion, garlic and mushrooms; brown slightly.
Lower heat to 300° or lower; add vinegar, sour cream, cream of chicken soup, Worcestershire and Tabasco sauces and pepper.
Mix with meat. Cover; cook slowly for 1 1/2 hours.
Serve over noodles, spaghetti or rice.
Serve with a nice green salad.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: layered overnight salad
directions: Tear lettuce into bite size pieces and place in oblong dish or large, deep glass salad bowl.
Continue to layer remaining ingredients, in order listed, ending with peas.
Spread mayonnaise over peas and seal to edges.
Sprinkle sugar over mayonnaise, then cheese.
Then top with bacon crumbs.
Seal tightly.
Do not stir.

title: orange slice cookies
directions: Stir together all ingredients until blended. Drop by spoonful onto ungreased pan. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes or until edges begin to brown. Remove to wire rack to cool. Yields 2 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: pork chops with rice
directions: Brown chops and season with salt and pepper.
Remove from pan and pour off any excess grease.
Add to same pan the soup and milk. Mix well, scraping bottom of pan.
Add Worcestershire sauce.
Bring to a boil.
Shut off.
Add onion and celery to prepared rice.
Put rice mixture in buttered casserole dish.
Top with pork chops. Pour soup mixture over top.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: macaroni salad for a crowd
directions: Mix carrots, onion and green pepper together and add to cooled macaroni.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix sweet potatoes, sugar and egg; put in baking dish.
Mix brown sugar and pecans.
Put on top of potatoes.
Melt butter and pour over nuts and sugar.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: dump cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Dump cherry filling in the bottom.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over the filling.
Put pats of butter over that layer.
Sprinkle coconut over the other layers.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: pretzel salad(this was so good!)
directions: Mix together pretzels, 3 tablespoons sugar and margarine. Spread evenly into 9 x 13-inch pan; bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Cool.
Cream together 1 scant cup sugar and cream cheese.
Fold in Cool Whip and layer on top of pretzel mix.
Cook pudding; cool and layer on top of 2nd layer.
Mix jello in hot water and let partially set up.
Add raspberries.
Pour over top of all and chill until set.

title: lemon poppy seed bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and lemon peel.
Mix and add dry ingredients, alternating with milk.
Mix 2 to 3 minutes. Grease bottom only of 2 loaf pans.
Pour into loaf pans and bake in 350° oven for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: mexican lasagna
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
In large skillet, brown ground beef and onions.
Drain fat.
Stir in the rest of ingredients, except cheese and tortillas.
Layer half the tortillas on bottom of 11x7 baking dish.
Spread 1/2 the meat mixture over and sprinkle with 1/2 the cheese.
Repeat layers.
Bake 30 minutes. Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: pineapple zucchini bread
directions: Combine first four ingredients in large bowl. Beat well. Add zucchini and drained pineapple, mix well. Mix dry ingredients. Stir into zucchini mixture until blended. Divide between 2 5x9 inch loaf pans. Bake 350 degrees about 1 hour.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: In a bowl, combine veggies, chicken soup and thyme (salt optional).
Pour into an ungreased deep dish (9 x 13).
Combine biscuit mix, milk and egg.
Pour over chicken mixture.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: plantation pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs until light and fluffy.
Stir in sugar and salt. Add syrups, oleo and pecans.
Mix well.
Pour into pie shell. Bake at 350° about 1 hour.

title: freezer cole slaw
directions: Mix cabbage with salt and let stand 1 hour.
Add rest of vegetables.
Pour cool dressing over slaw.
Place in containers and freeze.

title: linguine with clam sauce
directions: In large pot, steam clams in 1 cup of water.
Remove clams and strain juice in pot. Remove clams from the shells and add to juice.
Simmer juices with butter, wine, oil, garlic, salt and pepper.
To the bread crumbs add: salt, pepper, garlic salt, parsley and cheese.
Add more bread crumbs to the seasoned juices to thicken the juices into the sauce.
Cook pasta al dente and drain.
Top with clam sauce.

title: tuna ball
directions: Cream the cream cheese, Worcestershire sauce and lemon juice. Drain tuna and add to mixture.
Add celery, onion and shredded cheese.
Make into balls.
Roll in chopped nuts and refrigerate.

title: no cook divinity
directions: Combine mix, corn syrup, vanilla and water.
Beat on high until peaks form, about 5 minutes.
Then gradually, on low speed, blend in sugar.
Stir in nuts.
Drop on lightly buttered dish. When outside feels firm, turn over. Dry at least 12 hours.
Makes about 5 to 6 dozen.

title: artichoke moussaka
directions: Saute lamb and onion in butter over medium high heat until meat loses its redness.
Add wine, tomatoes, parsley, pepper, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt.
Simmer, uncovered, stirring occasionally for about 35 minutes or until liquid evaporates. Remove from heat; skim off extra fat and stir in 3 tablespoons Egg Sauce.
Spread meat mixture into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour artichokes into colander; thaw in hot running water; drain and quarter.
Press into meat.
Spread remaining Egg Sauce over all; sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or refrigerate until needed, then bake 50 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Cut into squares.
Serves 12.

title: shrimp toasties
directions: Combine all ingredients (except muffins) and spread on English muffin halves.
Place in freezer.
Just before serving, remove from freezer and slice each English muffin half into 8 pie shaped wedges.
Place wedges on cookie sheet and broil for 3 to 5 minutes.

title: holiday fruitcake
directions: Generously grease and flour 10-inch (12 cup) Bundt pan.
In large bowl, combine eggs and water.
Beat well with mixer.
Add remaining ingredients by hand, stirring until combined.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake at 350° for 80 to 90 minutes, until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool 15 minutes.
Invert on cooling rack.
Cool completely.
To store, wrap tightly in foil or plastic wrap.
Refrigerate.
If desired, glaze with warm corn syrup and decorate with candied fruit and nuts.

title: deviled eggs spread
directions: Cut eggs in half and remove yolks.
Mash yolks and 1 egg white with fork.
Stir in mayonnaise, mustard, onion and 1 teaspoon chopped parsley.
Chop remaining (3) egg whites.
Place chopped egg whites
on serving plate.
Spread egg yolk mixture on top. Cover and refrigerate 2 hours.

title: corn chowder
directions: Cook bacon until crisp.
Remove bacon and set aside.
Saute onions in bacon fat until soft.
Add potatoes, 2 cups water, salt and pepper.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes or until tender.
Stir in corn with liquid and milk.
Blend flour with remaining 1/2 cup water until smooth, then stir into chowder.
Cook, stirring constantly, over medium heat until it thickens and heats thoroughly.
Serve sprinkled with bacon and paprika.
Serve 4 to 6.
Freezes well.

title: magic quiche
directions: Layer bacon, cheese and vegetables in buttered 10-inch pie plate.
Blend eggs, milk, flour and seasonings.
Pour over other ingredients.
Let sit 5 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until brown.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake in a 9 x 12-inch pan for 20 minutes.

title: peachy sweet potatoes
directions: Place sweet potatoes into a 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish. Sprinkle with salt.
Place peaches on top of potatoes; sprinkle brown sugar over peaches.
Pour 2 tablespoons peach liquid over sugar.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Combine egg, milk, 2/3 cup cracker crumbs, 1/4 teaspoon salt and dash of pepper.
Stir in corn, onion and pimiento. Mix well. Turn into 1-quart casserole.
Toss butter with rest of cracker crumbs; sprinkle on top of corn mixture.
Bake, uncovered in 350° oven for 1 hour or until done.
Serves 6.

title: cranberry jello
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water.
Stir in cranberry sauce.
Chill until thick.
Stir in sour cream and nuts.
Chill until firm.

title: chocolate mousse pie
directions: Cream together the butter and sugar until well blended.
Melt the chocolate. Let cool. Add to butter and sugar.
Add the eggs, one at a time, beating 5 minutes after each one.
Fold in the Cool Whip. Spoon into the pie shell.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts, if desired.
Top with Cool Whip as if it were meringue. Refrigerate 6 hours before serving.

title: low fat turkey broccoli
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cook broccoli for 5 minutes.
Arrange in bottom of sprayed baking dish.
Top with turkey.
Combine soup with milk until smooth.
Pour over turkey.
Top with cheese.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Let stand for 5 minutes before cutting.

title: fruit trifle(makes 12 servings)
directions: Cut the pound cake in half lengthwise from top to bottom, then cut crosswise into 1/2-inch thick slices.

title: grandma's apple pie
directions: Core and pare apples.
Cut in quarters, then slice thin.
Line 9-inch pie pan with crust.
Mix sugars, flour and spices.
Rub a little sugar mixture on crust in pan.
Arrange apples in pan, heaping slightly in center.
Sprinkle evenly with remaining sugar mixture; scatter lemon peel over surface.
Dot with butter.
Adjust top crust; trim edges and flute.
Cut slits in center to allow steam to escape.
Bake at 425° for 40 to 45 minutes, until apples are tender and crust is golden brown.

title: buffalo chip cookies
directions: Melt butter.
Add brown sugar, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Beat well and add flour, baking powder, salt and soda.
Add oatmeal, corn flakes, pecans and chocolate chips.
Make a large dropped cookies, about 9 to a sheet.
Bake at 350° about 15 minutes.

title: beer batter fried chicken(serves 4)
directions: In a bowl, mix flour, salt and baking powder.
In separate bowl beat together beer, egg and 2 teaspoons salad oil; stir into flour mixture.
Coat half of chicken with batter.
Meanwhile, in a 12-inch skillet over medium heat, heat 1/2 inch salad oil to 370° (frying temperature).
Fry chicken until brown and tender, approximately 20 minutes, turning once with tongs.
Drain on paper towels or brown bag.
Repeat with remaining chicken.

title: oatmeal drop cookies
directions: In a medium bowl with a wooden spoon, stir together the flour, baking powder, salt and cinnamon.
Add brown sugar with the back of spoon.
Stir until all lumps are tiny.
Stir in oats.
Make a well in the center.
Add corn oil, unbeaten eggs, water, vanilla and raisins.
Stir vigorously until the dry ingredients are moistened.
Drop by level tablespoons 2 inches apart onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake in preheated 350° oven until lightly browned, about 13 to 15 minutes.
With a wide spatula, remove at once to wire racks to cool.
Makes about 2 1/2 dozen.
Recipe may be doubled.

title: fresh tomato soup
directions: Melt butter in large heavy boiler.
Saute onion in butter for 4 minutes.
Reduce to low heat.
Add flour and stir until smooth. Gradually add water.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until thick and bubbly.
Add the next 7 ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer on low heat for 30 to 40 minutes.
Remove and discard bay leaf.

title: gourmet potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes partially.
Grate potatoes in 12 x 9-inch dish. Mix in cheese, sour cream, green onion and butter.
Bake at 350° for approximately 25 to 30 minutes.

title: puppy chow for people
directions: Melt peanut butter, chocolate chips and margarine in microwave.
Pour onto cereal.
Coat with sugar.

title: sausage and squash casserole
directions: Dice and cook squash until tender.
Brown sausage.
Add squash, sausage, butter, cheese, bread crumbs and soup.
Put into casserole dish.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Mix together.
Freeze to right consistency to roll in nuts and top with cherries.
Makes 2 large or 3 small balls.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain the juice from the pineapple.
Slice the bananas.
Mix all the ingredients.
Keep refrigerated.

title: blackberry cobbler
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream butter and sugar. Combine flour and baking powder. Add to creamed mixture alternately with milk. Stir just until moistened. Pour into a greased 1 1/2-quart baking pan. Sprinkle with blackberries. Pour juice over all. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes. Top with ice cream or cream, if desired. Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: food processor popovers
directions: Fit processor with a steel blade.
Add all ingredients and process 2 1/2 minutes, continuously.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Beat eggs well. Add sugar, a little at a time. Put in pumpkin and beat well. Add water and oil. Add flour, soda, nutmeg, cinnamon and salt (which have been sifted together) last. Blend well. Pour into well-greased and floured pans. Bake at 350° for about 1 hour until a toothpick comes out clean. Use 2 loaf pans or a large tube pan.

title: candy
directions: Use double boiler and melt chocolate chips and butterscotch morsels.
Add peanuts.
Drop from teaspoon onto wax paper.

title: flavorful chicken or pork chops
directions: Mix all ingredients (looks gross but wait until you taste!). Let chops sit in mixture covered for 30 minutes.
Broil or grill and baste often with liquid.
Wow!
Can repeat with chicken. Wonderful too!

title: pineapple cheese spread for sandwiches
directions: Soften cream
cheese and blend in the other ingredients well. Makes 3/4 cup.

title: natchitoches meat pie
directions: Fry meat in butter until done.
Add onion and pine nuts and continue frying until onion is transparent.
Add vinegar until slightly sour.
Add salt and pepper.
Let completely cool.
Put about 1 teaspoon of filling in center of dough and bring edges to center.
Brush with melted butter.
Bake at 400° until golden. Serve slightly warm.
Yields 30 to 40.

title: chicken fingers
directions: Mix all ingredients, except chicken strips, well.
Dip chicken strips into mixture and dunk into hot deep fryer grease.
It is done when golden brown.

title: doughnuts
directions: Mix ingredients, roll out and cut with doughnut cutter. Fry in deep fryer until browned.

title: tuna-noodle casserole
directions: Grease casserole.
Layer as follows:
noodles, tuna, mushroom soup, noodles, celery soup and tuna.
Repeat until all ingredients are used.
Sprinkle bread crumbs on top.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: frito casserole
directions: Heat the chili.
Using a round baking dish, cover the bottom with a layer of Fritos, then a layer of tamales, topped with 1/2 cup chopped onion.
Pour 1/2 of the chili on top of all of this and add 4 slices of cheese.
Repeat in the same order with the remainder of the ingredients, beginning with chopped onion.
Bake at 350° until casserole is hot and cheese is melted.

title: zucchini squash casserole
directions: Arrange squash in dish.
Saute onions and garlic in the oil. Add tomatoes, seasonings and vinegar.
Bring to a boil and simmer 1 minute.
Pour tomatoes and onion mix over squash.
Top with the cheese and bake in a 400° oven for 1 hour.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: pumpkin delight
directions: Into a greased 13 x 9 pan pour pumpkin, sugar, evaporated milk, eggs, cinnamon, nutmeg and allspice.
Over the top, sprinkle cake mix, pecans and butter.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.
Serve hot with Cool Whip.

title: bird treats
directions: Be careful in your selection.
Do not choose too young.
When selected, give your entire thoughts to preparation for domestic use.
Some wives insist upon keeping them in a pickle, others are constantly getting them into hot water.
This may make them sour, hard and sometimes bitter; even poor varieties may be made sweet, tender and good by garnishing them with patience, well sweetened with love and seasoned with kisses.
Wrap them in a mantle of charity.
Keep warm with a steady fire of devotion and serve with peaches and cream.
Thus prepared, they will keep for years. Author Unknown.

title: chicken salad pie
directions: Bake pie crusts for 10 minutes and set aside.
Mix chicken and all other ingredients except potato chips and cheese.
Pour in crusts.
Cover with cheese and top with potato chips.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown ground beef with onion in skillet; add seasoning mix and water to the meat and drain off the grease.
Bring to a boil. Reduce heat and let simmer about 15 minutes.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: Cook and drain spaghetti.
Mix 1/2 jar sauce in same pot. Pour half the mixture in long dish.
Pour remaining sauce over mixture. Sprinkle 1/2 each bag of cheese over mixture.
Pour remaining spaghetti over this.
Pour 1 jar sauce on top. Sprinkle remaining cheese. Add mushrooms. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: family biscuits
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt in large bowl.
Cut in Crisco using pastry blender (or 2 knives) to form coarse crumbs.
Add milk.
Mix with fork until particles are moistened and cling together.
Form dough into ball.
Transfer dough to lightly floured surface.
Knead gently 8 to 10 times. Roll dough to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut with floured 2-inch round cutter.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 425° for 12 to 14 minutes.
Yield:
12 to 16 biscuits.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix together, including bacon drippings.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: pumpkin squares
directions: *Corn oil is very important; do not substitute!

title: sour cream and lemon pound cake
directions: Cream butter and margarine with sugar, vanilla and lemon extract until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well.
Sift flour and soda together and add alternately with sour cream to egg mixture, mixing at low speed.
Blend well but do not overmix.
Pour into 9-inch tube pan that has been greased and floured.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: southern fried chicken
directions: In a large resealable plastic bag, combine the first five ingredients.
Add chickens, a few pieces at a time, and shake to coat. In a large skillet, heat 1/4-inch of oil on medium-high; fry chicken in batches for 18 to 20 minutes or until juices run clear, turning once.
Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: oyster appetizer
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Place drained oysters in baking pan. Sprinkle with bacon pieces.
Bake until bacon is crisp. Remove from oven. Sprinkle liberally with Cheddar cheese. When cheese is fully melted, serve with thin slices of French bread.

title: kuntry kassrole
directions: Put out ground heffer in bottom of big bakin' dish.
Sprinkle ungun over this.
Sprankle rice over this.
Lay carats over this. Lay taters over this.
Sprankle peas over this.
Poor cut up maters over this.
Cover and bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Smuther with grated cheez and bake nother 15 minits and then...chow down!

title: dirt cake
directions: You will also need an 8 to 10-inch plastic flowerpot or pail and a plastic or silk flower.

title: carrots
directions: Mix all together. Keeps several days.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix sugar, egg, milk, bananas and Bisquick. Then beat vigorously for 30 seconds.
Batter may be still slightly lumpy.
Stir in walnuts.
Pour into well-greased loaf pan.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes, until a toothpick stuck into center comes out clean. Crack in top of bread is typical.
Cool before slicing.

title: vegetable bake
directions: In a 1-quart casserole, stir can of cream of mushroom soup, milk, soy sauce and dash of pepper until smooth.
Mix in corn, lima beans and French fried onions.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until hot.
Top with remaining can of onions.
Bake 5 minutes more.

title: chic-and-fruit salad
directions: Mix chicken, celery, grapes and apples well.
Serve on bed of lettuce.
Garnish with tomatoes or avocados.
No set amount.
I like the taste that the avocado gives this easy dish.
It is a meal in itself.

title: cheese zucchini crisps
directions: Combine corn flake crumbs, cheese and seasonings in plastic bag.
Dip zucchini in butter and shake in bag to coat.
Place on baking sheet. Bake at 375° for 10 minutes or until crisp. Serves 4.

title: peach and berry cobbler
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Mix muffin mix and 3/4 cup milk.
In another bowl mix peaches, sugar, extract and cornstarch.
Pour into buttered baking dish.
Dot with butter and pour muffin mix on fruit.
Bake about 30 minutes.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix and spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: holiday eggnog
directions: In large bowl, beat eggs until light and foamy.
Add sugar and salt, beating until thick and lemon colored.
Stir in rum and cream.
Chill at least 3 hours.
Before serving, sprinkle with nutmeg.
Yields 12 servings (1/2 cup each).

title: zonda's cheesecake
directions: Blend cream cheese, lemon juice and milk.
Fold in whipped cream.
Crush vanilla wafers and put in pan.
Add enough butter to make the crumbs hold together.

title: chocolate turtle cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Grease pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inches, with shortening; lightly flour. Make cake mix, using water, oil and eggs. Pour half of batter into pan. Bake 25 minutes. Heat caramels and milk in 1-quart saucepan over medium heat about 10 minutes, stirring frequently, until caramels are melted. Pour and spread caramel over warm cake in pan. Sprinkle with pecans and chocolate chips. Spread with remaining batter. Bake 30 minutes. Run knife around side of pan to loosen cake. Cool completely, about 1 hour. Store, covered, at room temperature.

title: pasta and clams
directions: Heat oil; saute garlic and onion.
Add tomatoes, mushrooms, wine and seasonings.
Cook for 1 minute.
Add spinach and clams with a little clam juice.
Cover until spinach wilts and is tender.
Add cooked pasta and serve with Parmesan cheese.
Serves 2.

title: salmon casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Remove any bones from salmon. Flake salmon; add crumbs, cheese, onion and parsley. In separate bowl, beat together 1 cup milk, eggs, dash of salt and pepper and lemon juice. Add milk mixture to salmon and mix well. Place in buttered 1 1/2 quart flat casserole and set this dish in another larger flat dish containing 1 inch of hot water. Bake for 1 hour or until set. Make sauce by mixing soup, 1/4 cup milk, and Worcestershire sauce. Heat sauce and serve over casserole.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Cook until soft.
Do not drain.
Cook 4 1/2 cups chopped broccoli until tender.
Do not drain the broccoli.
Put into the potato mixture.
Add 3 tablespoons parsley flakes.
Mix 2 1/4 cups milk and 3 tablespoons flour.
Add to potato mixture, then add 3/4 pound cheese, cubed.
Simmer until melted.

title: hazelnut cranberry sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together and cook until boiling.

title: ceasar salad
directions: Wash and dry romaine; mix with a whisk the garlic, anchovy paste, mustard, Worcestershire sauce and lemon juice.
Add egg yolk and oil and mix again.
Pour dressing over lettuce.
Add cheese and croutons and eat immediately.

title: beef barbecue sauce
directions: Lightly brown beef; add onion, celery and peppers and cook until tender.
Add remaining ingredients; cover and simmer about 45 minutes.

title: glorified cabbage
directions: Heat the cabbage and onions in heatproof bowl.
Mix in saucepan the sugar, oil, vinegar, mustard and salts.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Pour over cabbage and onions.
Mix well.

title: alpine chicken
directions: Combine flour, salt and pepper.
Dredge chicken with flour mixture and brown lightly on all sides, in oil in a skillet.
Add water and bouillon cubes; cover and simmer about 30 minutes, or until chicken is tender.
Remove chicken from pan.
Combine egg and lemon juice and blend into stock in skillet.
Add parsley and heat gently (do not boil).
Serve over chicken.
Makes 4 or 5 servings.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Cook spinach as directed on package. In saucepan, saute onion until softened.
Pour cooked spinach in casserole dish.
Mix Philadelphia cream cheese and onions until blended.
Sprinkle bread crumbs on top and place in oven for 20 to 30 minutes and serve.

title: sheet cake
directions: Bring margarine or butter, water and cocoa to boil. Pour over flour, sugar and salt.
Mix well eggs, sour cream and baking soda and beat in.
Pour in well-greased pan and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Peel and cook 7 medium-sized potatoes.
Cook, drain and refrigerate.
Mash after chilled, but leave lumpy.

title: beets
directions: Peel and grate cooked beets.
Melt butter.
Add flour.
Bring to boiling point.
Add lemon juice, salt and sugar.
Mix with beets.
Boil for 2 to 3 minutes.
Add sour cream, heat and serve with main dish.

title: sweet and sour pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers and cut into chunks.
Sterilize four 1 quart jars.
To each jar add 4 slices of onion, 2 pieces of celery, and 2 heads of dill.
Fill jars with cucumber chunks.
Dissolve sugar and salt in vinegar and water.
Bring to a boil.
Cover cucumbers in jars.
Seal at once and for best results do not use for 30 days.

title: luscious pork chops
directions: Heat oil on low heat.
Wash and dry pork chops.
Mix all dry ingredients and spread mustard on pork chops.
Dip in flour mixture; fry until brown.
Pour chicken soup and milk over chops. Cover and simmer until done.

title: drop sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar, butter and Crisco; add beaten eggs and vanilla. Mix all together.
Drop from teaspoon on greased cookie sheet; bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Makes about 10 dozen.

title: strawberry preserves
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients in kettle; bring to a boil and, stirring, boil 1 minute.
Stir in sugar and bring to a boil that can't be stirred down.
Boil hard for 1 minute.
Remove mixture from heat; stir in rum and lemon juice.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Skim off foam and pour into hot, sterilized jars.
Seal. Yields 3 pints.

title: savory chicken pie
directions: Fold chicken, pimento and Veg-All together.
Mix fat and flour together.
Cook until smooth and golden.
Add milk and stock, whipping until smooth and thick.
Add seasoning and fold into chicken vegetable mixture.

title: chicken stir-fry
directions: Heat oil in skillet.
Cook chicken and vegetables, stirring constantly, 5 minutes.
Add Cup-a-Soup, blended with water. Bring to a boil, then simmer 5 minutes until sauce thickens. Serve over hot vermicelli or rice.

title: apple cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello and salt in boiling water.
Break up cranberry sauce with fork.
Add jello mixture.
Chill until very thick. Fold in apples and nuts.
Chill until firm.

title: tangy tomato dressing
directions: Combine cornstarch, salt and V-8 juice.
Cook until thickened. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover, chill, refrigerate.
Makes about 1 1/3 cups.

title: apple's temptation
directions: Put all ingredients in
a
blender
until it is creamy. Pour into individual cups and chill for 2 hours.

title: oven-fried chicken
directions: Rinse chicken and pat dry.
You may sprinkle with salt and pepper, if desired.
Place crumbs and seasoning in a plastic bag and shake to mix.
Brush or dip each piece of chicken in margarine or milk.
Place in a bag and shake to coat.
Bake in a 375° oven for 45 to 55 minutes or until tender and no longer pink.
If browning too rapidly, you may place aluminum foil loosely over top.
Serves 6.

title: chinese almond cookies
directions: Cream
Crisco and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add an egg and almond extract;
beat well.
Sift dry ingredients and add
to creamed mixture.
Shape into small balls and place on ungreased cookie
sheet.
Press
top
of
cookie slightly and brush
top with beaten egg.
Press sliced almond on center or sprinkle with sesame
seed.
Bake
in
375° oven for 12 to 15 minutes, until light brown.

title: tortilla soup
directions: Brown ground meat and drain.
Add all other ingredients.
Do not drain.
Bring to a boil, then simmer a few minutes.
Easy and ready to eat.

title: jack's coffee
directions: Add sugar and cream as desired.

title: chess squares
directions: Mix partially melted margarine with cake mix. Mix in 1 egg and knead into dough. Press in bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix sugar, cream cheese and 3 eggs. Pour over dough. Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes until filling is set and golden brown.

title: grandma donabella's sauce
directions: Pour the tomato sauce into a large Dutch oven type saucepan (6-quart).
Remove casing from pepperoni and cut into 1/4-inch slices.
In a skillet, which has a covering of olive oil, place the cut up pepperoni.
Brown each side, then add to tomato sauce. Begin heating mixture on low.
Using that same skillet, prepare the pork chops, first browning on each side, then cooking for approximately 15 minutes.

title: quick green bean casserole
directions: In a casserole dish, mix the green beans, soup dip and the corn.
Melt the butter; crumble the Ritz crackers into the butter. Sprinkle the Ritz cracker mixture on top of the bean mixture. (Try to cover the beans entirely.)
Bake at 350° to 400° until the topping is brown (topping should be lightly crispy).
Makes about 8 servings.

title: pina colada cake
directions: Bake cake as directed in a 9 x 13 inch pan.
As soon as it comes out of oven, punch holes all over the top with a meat fork (try not to hit bottom, but it's alright if you do).
Mix condensed milk and pina colada mix together and pour over cake.
Chill overnight.
Before serving, frost with whipped dessert topping.

title: spinach and mushroom salad
directions: Mix together spinach and lettuce.
Add all other ingredients except croutons.
Toss well.
Add croutons just before serving. Toss lightly.

title: oriental meatballs
directions: Mix.
Fry meatballs until done in small amount of oil.
Set aside.

title: banana bread
directions: *To sour milk use 1 tablespoon vinegar and add milk to make 1/4 cup sour milk.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening; add egg, sour milk with soda, then flour, vanilla and salt.
Last, add cocoa dissolved in the hot water.
Pour in 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Serves 10 to 12 people.

title: chicken crunch casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except bread crumbs and margarine.
Place mixture in buttered 9 x 12-inch pan.
Brown bread crumbs lightly in margarine; sprinkle over casserole and refrigerate overnight. Remove from refrigerator for 1 hour before baking.
Bake in 350° oven for 40 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: chocolate dream
directions: Mix flour, melted oleo and pecans.
Spread on bottom of casserole dish, 9 x 13-inch.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Let cool.

title: corn-corn bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients; add eggs, sour cream, corn and oil.
Mix well.
Heat oven to 400°.
Cook in a greased pan for 15 to 20 minutes.
Better served hot.

title: divinity
directions: Beat egg whites and set aside.
Cook sugar, syrup and water until it threads from spoon.
Slowly pour over egg whites.
As candy begins to set up, add vanilla and nuts.

title: mint marshmallow jello salad
directions: Mix pineapple, marshmallows and lime jello together.
Let set overnight.
Then add the whipped Dream Whip and the crushed buttermints.
Refrigerate several hours before serving.

title: chocolate eclair
directions: Mix pudding, milk, sugar and Cool Whip well.
Layer bottom of a 9 x 13-inch baking pan with graham crackers.
Pour half of pudding mixture over crackers.
Cover with another layer of graham crackers.
Cover with rest of the pudding.
Top off with graham crackers.

title: southwest chicken and rice
directions: Brown chicken in oil.
Remove from skillet.
Cook peppers and onion until tender and crisp.
Stir in remaining ingredients and chicken.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes or until chicken is tender.
Serve over rice.

title: crabmeat-spinach casserole
directions: Cook spinach until separated; drain well.
Grate Cheddar cheese; set aside 1 to 2 ounces to top casserole.
Put 3 eggs in a large mixing bowl and beat lightly.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Turn into a 12 x 8-inch dish that has been sprayed with nonstick coating.
Top with reserved grated cheese and bake at 350° for one hour.
Makes six generous servings.

title: easy cheesy muffins
directions: Combine dry ingredients in a bowl.
Add grated cheese and blend.
Add buttermilk, egg and oil; stir until thoroughly blended.
Fill greased muffin pan about 2/3 full.
Bake at 425° for about 20 minutes.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: cheese dip
directions: Stir and bake in a casserole dish at 325° for 25 minutes. Serve with party rye bread or crackers.

title: macadamia cheddar balls
directions: Note:
An easy make-ahead with two different cheeses plus crunchy Macadamia nuts.

title: chicken continental
directions: Saute
chicken,
mushrooms and garlic in oil for 2 to 3 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients except rice and bring to a full
boil.
Stir
in
rice.
Remove
from heat; cover and let stand 5 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix soup and broth together.
Drain vegetables.
Add to soup. Add chicken.
Stir lightly.
Pour into 9 x 9-inch casserole dish.

title: pound fruit cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into greased loaf pans and bake at 300° for 15 minutes.
Turn oven up to 325° and finish baking (approximately 3/4 to 1 hour more).

title: easy chicken breast
directions: Skin and debone chicken breast after splitting it in two. Pound with a saucer or meat tenderizer until it's even in thickness.
Sprinkle with salt and the basil on both sides.
Fry in preheated butter until the pink disappears.
Reduce heat to simmer and pour the wine and water over this.
Simmer, covered, for about 30 minutes.
Make gravy with juice and pour over the meat.

title: mom's muffins
directions: In a bowl combine sugar, flour, baking powder and salt.
Make a well in center.
Combine eggs, milk and oil and pour into well and mix just until dry ingredients are moistened.
(Do not overmix.) Spoon into greased muffin cups.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes, or until golden brown.
Makes 1 dozen.

title: graham wafer pie
directions: Combine graham wafer crumbs, granulated sugar and butter. Blend together and reserve 1/3 of this mixture for top of pie. Press the remainder into pie tin with even thickness as for rolled pie crust.

title: cinnamon oatmeal muffins(low-fat)
directions: Line 12 muffin cups with paper liners.
Set aside.
