Combine and mix milk and oatmeal.
Add oil, egg whites, sugar, spice and zest. Stir until blended.

title: tuna dip
directions: Blend all ingredients well in processor or by hand.
Place in bowl.
Refrigerate.
Serve as spread with crackers.

title: picante corn bread
directions: Heat an 8-inch cast iron skillet at 425° for 5 minutes. Combine first 5 ingredients in a large bowl.
Make a well in center of mixture.
Set aside.
Combine buttermilk, eggs and picante sauce.
Add to dry ingredients, stirring just until moistened. Remove skillet from oven.
Add butter and return to oven 1 minute or until butter melts.
Pour mixture into hot skillet.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes or until golden.
Serve immediately.

title: carrot and broccoli soup
directions: Steam broccoli and carrots until tender.
In separate saucepan, combine melted margarine, flour and salt.
Add milk. Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring until smooth.
Mix together sauce and vegetables until well coated.
Place in serving dish.

title: bread pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients with enough milk to make soupy.
Sprinkle top with nutmeg.
Pour into an 8 x 10-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes.

title: double chocolate nougats
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix cake mix, oil and eggs.
Stir in chocolate pieces.
Drop from teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet. If desired, top each cookie with pecan piece.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool on cookie sheet for 1 minute, then remove.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli.
Layer broccoli on bottom of casserole dish. Mix together soup, mayonnaise, eggs and onion.
Pour over broccoli.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: calico beans
directions: Drain all beans, except baked beans.
Brown bacon with onion and drain fat. Mix sugar, vinegar, mustard, bacon and onion with the beans.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: taco salad
directions: In large skillet, brown ground beef and onion; drain.
Stir in seasoning mix and hot water. Simmer over low heat about 10 minutes.
Stir.

title: gumbo a la creole
directions: In large gumbo pot, make a roux with oil and flour.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until roux is a dark caramel color.
Remove from fire and add remaining ingredients, except shrimp, 1/2 cup green onions, file and rice.
Boil for about 2 hours, or until meat is tender and gumbo is thickened.
In the last 15 minutes of boiling, add reserved green onions and shrimp. Remove from fire and add file.
Serves 5 or 6.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Boil a few potatoes and set aside.
Also, have ready a can of celery soup and can of chicken noodle soup or cream of chicken. Cut broccoli in small pieces; cook in boiling, salted water until well done.
Drain water from broccoli and add other ingredients. If this isn't thick enough, thicken accordingly.
Just before serving, add about 5 slices of American cheese and melt.
Does well in crock-pot after ingredients are mixed.

title: old fashioned raisin cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter well.
Add eggs one at a time.
Sift flour; save 1/2 cup to dredge raisins.
Add flavoring and fold in flour.
Add raisins to batter and mix well.
Line a tube pan with wax paper.
Preheat oven to 300°.
Bake one hour at 300°; lower heat to 250° and bake 2 hours longer.
Remove from oven; leave in pan 10 minutes before removal.

title: chicken spread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Chill and spread on crackers.

title: blueberry-peach cobbler
directions: Slice and peel peaches and place in a baking dish.
Sprinkle blueberries over peaches.
Sprinkle 1/4 cup sugar over fruit.
Mix flour and remaining sugar and cut in butter.
Pour over fruit. Bake around 30 minutes at 400°.
Add pecans and bake until golden brown (about 10 or 15 minutes).

title: fried rice
directions: Chop all vegetables.
Saute in 1/4 cup oil.
Add rice and meat.
Scramble 2 eggs, then add with soy sauce, salt and pepper. Mix all together, stirring frequently over medium heat.

title: blueberry crunch
directions: Butter 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread pineapple over pan.
Add berries
and
cup
sugar.
Sprinkle cake mix over mixture. Drizzle
melted
oleo
over
cake mix.
Sprinkle nuts over cake mix, then
1/4 cup sugar.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Take
knife and cut through cake to mix. Bake 15 to 20 minutes longer.

title: rice krispies cookies
directions: Sift flour and baking powder.
Set aside.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs.
Mix until creamy and fluffy.
Add vanilla, then flour.
Place Rice Krispies in pan.
Drop batter by teaspoonfuls into Rice Krispies, roll into ball and lay on cookie sheet 1-inch apart, pressing them slightly.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Watch carefully, it spreads a little and sometimes a little more flour is required so test to your liking.

title: mrs. joan pepper's lima bean casserole
directions: Combine mustard, Worcestershire, lemon juice and mayonnaise. Stir in water chestnuts and vegetables.
Put in 2-quart casserole, crumbs on top.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken divan
directions: In a greased casserole, arrange the broccoli and chicken slices.
Mix together the soup, mayonnaise and lemon juice; pour this over the top.
Then sprinkle grated cheese on top.
Melt butter and mix with the dressing mix and put on top of casserole. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: chicken divan
directions: First boil your fryer in seasoned water until done, then carefully debone and chop into chunks.

title: tomato aspic
directions: Bring 4 1/2 cups juice to a boil. Add other ingredients and boil about 10 minutes. Strain out vegetables, saving juice. Combine juice and soften gelatin.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart mold and chill. Serves 10.

title: aunt liza ellen's cookies
directions: Cream together margarine, white sugar, brown sugar and eggs. Add oats, coconut, flour, salt, baking powder, soda, vanilla and nuts.
Mix well
Shape into cookies and bake at 350° for 8 minutes.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients thoroughly.
Add milk and corn.
Mix again and pour into baking casserole about 2 inches deep.
Pour melted butter on top and bake at 325° for 1 hour or until firm.

title: taffy apple pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Remove 1/2 c of cookie dough and reserve for another use.
Roll dough into a 14 inch circle. Bake for 10 to 15 minutes or until cookie is lightly browned.
Let cool for 10 minutes then loosen cookie from pan.
Cool completely. Blend peanut butter, cream cheese, brown sugar and vanilla together until smooth.
Spread on cooled cookie.
Peel core and slice apples.
Soak apples in Sprite to prevent browning.
Arrange apple slices on cream cheese mixture.
Sprinkle lightly with cinnamon.
Heat caramel and drizzle over apples.
Sprinkle chopped nuts over pizza.
Cut into pieces and serve.

title: moo goo gai pan
directions: With a sharp knife, slice across width of chicken breasts to make very thin pieces.
In medium bowl, mix well chicken, cornstarch, sherry, ginger, monosodium glutamate and salt.

title: cranberry cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugars; add egg, milk and orange juice. Sift flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Combine with liquid ingredients and blend well.
Stir in nuts and cranberries.
Drop by teaspoons onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375 for 10
to 15 minutes.
Makes about 12 dozen.

title: grilled yam slices
directions: Scrub the skins but do not peel.
Trim the ends.
Slice yams lengthwise into 3/4-inch thick slices.
Rub with oil.
Grill on open or closed grill over a medium-hot fire approximately 10 minutes per side or until tender when pierced.

title: copenhagen cabbage
directions: Brown meat and onions.
Drain fat.
Blend next 4 ingredients. Add to meat.
Put 2 cups of cabbage into a 2-quart casserole dish. Add 1/2 of meat mixture and repeat layers.
Cover and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: cream cheese cookies(makes 48 servings)
directions: Mix cream cheese, butter and sugar. Add walnuts. Fold in flour. Drop by spoonful on cookie sheet and flatten with a wet finger. Bake for 10 minutes at 350°. Cookies are very fragile.

title: yankee bean chowder
directions: Soak the beans until they swell (couple of hours).
Drain and put in kettle with 3 quarts of fresh water.
Add the onion and bring to a boil.
Adjust the heat and simmer until beans are just tender (1/2 to 3/4 hour).
Add other vegetables and seasoning and cook until vegetables are tender (about 25 minutes).
Add milk last.
Serve as soon as it is hot.
Makes 12 to 15 servings. (Half it for family of six.)

title: crab dip
directions: Beat cream cheese, lemon juice, onion, milk and horseradish. Fold in crabmeat. Pour 1/3 in casserole dish. Layer American cheese. Pour the remaining crabmeat mix on top. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Blend Crisco, sugars, peanut butter, eggs, baking soda and salt.
Gradually add flour while mixing.
Bake in a preheated oven at 375° on a cookie sheet for approximately 8 minutes or until done.

title: pig picking cake
directions: Combine 1/2 cup reserved orange juice with cake mix and oleo. Add eggs one at a time; beat for 1 minute.
Add oranges and vanilla.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan or in 3 small cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: shrimp ball
directions: Form ingredients into ball.
Top with cocktail sauce.
Serve with crackers.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix well and chill overnight for best flavor.

title: bean and weenee
directions: Cut hot dog wieners into bite size pieces, then mix all of the ingredients into pot.
Cook over low heat for 30 to 45 minutes, until mixture thickens or wieners are done.

title: king's arms tavern old fashioned raisin-rice pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 2-quart casserole.
Combine sugar and nutmeg; add to milk and eggs and beat well.
Fold in rice, lemon juice, vanilla and melted butter.
Prepare a pan of boiling water.
Put casserole in water, then pour in mixture.
Sprinkle raisins in mixture.
Bake at 350° for approximately 40 to 45 minutes.
Test with a knife.
Don't overbake.

title: hungry boy's casserole
directions: Sprinkle onion, celery and green pepper in bottom of an 8-inch baking dish. Crumble ground beef on top. Bake at 425° for 20 minutes. Remove from oven. Stir in pork and beans, catsup, water, salt and garlic salt until well blended. Reserve 1/2 cup of bean-meat mixture. Return casserole to oven for 10 minutes while preparing biscuits.
Arrange biscuits without centers on casserole. Spoon reserved bean-meat mixture in hole of each biscuit.
Top with the biscuit hole. Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes until golden brown.

title: chess tarts
directions: In a medium mixing bowl, stir together the flour and salt. Using a pastry blender, cut in the shortening until mixture resembles fine crumbs.
Sprinkle 1 tablespoon of the water over the mixture.
Gently toss with fork.
Push moistened dough to the side of the bowl.
Repeat using 1 tablespoon of water at a time until all dough is moistened.
Form dough into a ball.
On a lightly floured surface, flatten the ball of dough to slightly less than 1/8-inch thick.
Cut into 4 (12-inch) circles.
Place dough circles in fluted tart pans.
Place tart pans on a baking sheet.
Bake in a 350° oven about 7 minutes or until pastry is set, but not puffed.

title: lasagne
directions: May substitute 10 ounces frozen spinach, thawed and drained, instead of beef.

title: cracker snack mix
directions: Put all in a large brown bag, add dressing and oil, shake and mix very well.
Pour onto paper toweling to absorb some of the oil.
Store in airtight container.

title: mother's gingerbread
directions: Cream together the sugar and shortening.
Add the egg and molasses.
Mix together the flour, soda, salt, ginger and cinnamon and add to the shortening mixture. Pour into a greased and floured 8 or 9 inch pan and bake at 350° for 25-30 minutes.

title: manicotti
directions: Mix Mozzarella cheese, Ricotta cheese and egg together.
Stuff manicotti shells with cheese mixture.
Layer in a greased baking dish.
Pour spaghetti sauce over noodles.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Cover and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Freezes well.

title: sour cream peach pie
directions: Combine peaches, flour, sour cream, salt and sugar.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes, then decrease heat to 350° and bake for 30 minutes longer.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar before baking, if desired.

title: layered mexican dip
directions: Layer all ingredients in order given.
Broil a few minutes to melt cheese.

title: chicken salad
directions: Chop eggs and add remaining ingredients.
Mix well; chill. Serve with toasted bread or crackers.

title: apple torte cake
directions: Blend eggs, sugar and oil with fork; add dry ingredients and blend.
Add apples and nuts, mix well.
Dough will be stiff.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: lemon pound cake
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat cream cheese until smooth.
Gradually beat in milk.
Add cake mix and eggs; beat on medium speed until well combined.
Pour into a greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes, until a toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Let cool 10 to 15 minutes before removing from pan.

title: zucchini squash casserole
directions: Melt
margarine
and
mix with stuffing mix; set aside. Cook squash
until
fork-tender.
Drain well.
Add soup, salt and pepper,
sour
cream
and
chopped onion and mix with the drained squash.
In a 1 1/2 quart casserole dish (sprayed with liquid shortening),
place
the
stuffing mix in bottom. Spoon on squash mixture.
Top with rest of stuffing mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: Mix all together.
Roll in
rolls
and wrap in tin foil. These are good to freeze and take out when needed.

title: layered lettuce salad
directions: Tear lettuce and spread on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer rest of ingredients in order given.
Add sugar to Miracle Whip and pour over top.
Top with cheese.
Cover well and refrigerate 8 to 12 hours or longer before serving.
Can garnish with parsley.

title: peanut butter creams
directions: Combine sugar, condensed milk and peanut butter in a medium mixing bowl; stir until well blended.
Stir in chocolate morsels and chill until firm.
Shape into 3/4-inch balls and roll each in decorator candies.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt margarine with chips and peanut butter.
Pour over Chex and stir gently.
Put in paper grocery bag and pour over powdered sugar.
Shake bag until coated.

title: coconut cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Prepare two 9-inch cake pans.
In large bowl beat first 8 ingredients with mixer at low speed.
Then beat at medium for 5 minutes.
Pour into pans and bake approximately 25 to 30 minutes.
Over medium heat, heat syrup to boiling.
Beat egg whites to soft peaks.
Slowly pour in hot syrup, beating until mixture is fluffy.
Add salt and vanilla.
Ice cakes and sprinkle with coconut.

title: jello salad
directions: Prepare jello as on package; chill to set.
Take half and add fruit.
Add cheese to the other half and beat.
Put first mixture in mold to set, then cover with second mixture.
Sprinkle with nuts.

title: layered lettuce salad
directions: Combine mayonnaise and sugar.
Tear lettuce into small pieces and place in bowl.
Layer celery, eggs, pepper, onion, bacon, mayonnaise and cheese.

title: chicken a la king(a dish truly fit for a king!)
directions: Melt butter or margarine in a large skillet.
Add celery and mushrooms.
Saute until tender.
Blend in flour and let simmer 1 minute.
Slowly add Chicken Broth. Cook about 3 to 5 minutes, stirring constantly until thick.
Add Chicken Mix, milk and pimiento, if desired, and parsley flakes.
Simmer 10 minutes. Serve over hot cooked rice.
Garnish with slivered almonds.
Makes 6 servings.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: In a large shallow baking pan, place chicken, skin side up, in a single layer.
In a bowl, mix together salad dressing, soup mix and preserves.
Pour over chicken. Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven, basting occasionally, about 1 hour or until fork can be inserted in chicken with ease.
(Pour remaining sauce over chicken when serving.)
Makes 8 servings.

title: jazzy jambalaya
directions: In a heavy 4-quart saucepan, brown sausage over low heat. Drain tomatoes, reserving liquid.
Add water to make 1 1/2 cups. Add to sausage and tomatoes the shrimp and remaining ingredients. Bring to a boil and stir.
Reduce heat to low.
Simmer 30 to 35 minutes or until liquid is absorbed, stirring occasionally.
Remove bay leaf.
Ready to serve.

title: saveybars
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients.
Sift and add the next 6 ingredients.
Stir in raisins, nuts and vanilla.
Bake in greased 13 x 9-inch pan for 35 to 45 minutes at 350°.
Frost with thin coating of confectioners sugar icing while warm.

title: cabbage and beet bake
directions: Trim stems and roots from beets.
Peel beets; cut into julienne strips.
Layer cabbage, onion and beets alternately in a 3-quart baking dish.
Combine wine and remaining ingredients, stirring well.
Pour over cabbage mixture.
Cover and bake at 325° for 1 hour and 45 minutes or until vegetables are tender, stirring every 30 minutes.
Yield:
7 servings (64 calories per 1 cup serving).

title: sweet pickled beets
directions: Cook beets and place in jars with 3 or 4 cloves.
Heat sugar and vinegar to boil, pour over beets and seal. Very good!

title: crock-pot steak and gravy
directions: Place seasoned steaks in crock-pot with cups of water and soup mixed.
Cook on low overnight.
Serve with rice.

title: nature crackers
directions: Place ingredients into bowl and mix.
Mix with a fork and knead.
Roll onto sprayed Pam cookie sheet to approximately 1/4-inch thick.
Score and prick with a fork.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until brown and crispy.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Boil chicken and salt to taste, cool, then remove skin.
Pull chicken from bones and put in greased baking dish.
Layer chicken, soups, and sour cream.
Put crushed Ritz crackers on top, pour melted margarine on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: homemade kahlua
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Simmer 1 hour.
Cool and mix in vanilla and vodka.
Makes 1 1/2 quarts and is better than commercial Kahlua.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Combine all dry ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Add eggs and salad oil, stirring until dry ingredients are moistened.
Do not actually beat with a mixer.
Stir in vanilla, pineapple and nuts.
Finally, add the bananas.
Spoon the batter into 3 well-greased and floured 9-inch round cake pans.
Bake in a preheated oven at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until cake tests done.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes.
Then turn onto cooling rack. Cool completely before frosting.
Frost with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: ham and cheese pinwheels
directions: Mix cream cheese with small amount of mayonnaise and dash of salt. Spread on ham and roll.
Chill, then slice to be served on Ritz crackers.

title: basic cream sauce(fat-free)
directions: In medium-size saucepan over medium heat, bring milk, wine, pepper and nutmeg to a simmer, stirring to prevent scorching. Stir in cornstarch mixture and cook, stirring constantly, 3 to 4 minutes or until thickened and bubbly.
Makes 2 cups.

title: stuffed zucchini
directions: Cut zucchini in half.
Scoop
out inner part of zucchini.
Put in a bowl
and chop.
Add bread crumbs, grated cheese and enough oil to moisten.
Mix well and fill zucchini halves. Bake at 350° until
zucchini are cooked.
Sprinkle Mozzarella cheese over zucchini halves a few minutes before removing from oven.

title: eggnog bread pudding with jack daniels  sauce
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter a 9-inch square baking pan and set aside.
Spread bread slices generously with softened butter and cut into squares.
Scatter over bottom of pan.
Beat eggs and sugar.
Pour in eggnog while stirring and mix well.

title: soy-oat waffles
directions: Soak soybeans several hours or overnight in sufficient water to keep covered.
Drain; discard water.
(Soaked, drained soybeans may be kept in the refrigerator for a week or stored for longer periods in the freezer.
Keep on hand for use at a moment's notice.)
Combine all ingredients and blend until light and foamy, about half a minute.
Let stand while waffle iron is heating.
The batter thickens on standing.
Blend briefly.

title: conch fritters
directions: Combine flour and dry ingredients.
Add a little water at a time to batter consistency.
Add conch, green pepper and onion; mix well.
Spoon batter into skillet of hot oil over medium heat to form small balls the size of hush puppies.
Turn occasionally until golden brown.
Drain and serve.

title: grandma harveys fudge
directions: Mix sugar and milk in large heavy pan and slowly bring to a rolling boil.
Cook for 10 minutes, stirring if necessary to bring down.
Remove from heat and add all the chocolate chips, marshmallows and butter.

title: s-2 bars(sumptuous and sinful)
directions: Mix together graham crackers, peanut butter, powdered sugar and melted butter.
Spread this evenly in ungreased pan.
Melt chocolate chips (to make richer, add approximately 1/2 cup melted butter).
Spread melted chips on top of other mixture.
Let cool. Serve immediately or chill until served.

title: rice consomme
directions: Place ingredients in a casserole dish.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until liquids are absorbed.

title: jonnie's sandies
directions: Cream butter and sugar; and water and vanilla; mix well. Blend in flour and nuts.
Chill 4 hours.
Shape in balls or fingers (make sure dough is cold at all times).
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 325 degrees about 20 minutes.
Remove from pan; cool slightly.
Roll in confectioners sugar.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Combine peanut butter, Crisco, brown sugar, milk and vanilla in a large bowl. Beat at medium speed of electric mixer until well blended.
Add egg.
Beat until blended.

title: corned beef 'n cabbage casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Saute cabbage, celery and onion in olive oil. Add remaining ingredients; mix well. Spoon into 2-quart casserole. Cover. Bake at 40 to 50 minutes until thoroughly heated. Makes 8 servings.

title: lindsay's chicken quesadillas
directions: Cook chicken and tomatoes in Pam until liquid cooks out. In another frying pan on medium to low heat, spray Pam. Lay tortilla shell in pan and add chicken mixture on one side of shell. Sprinkle cheese on top of chicken. With spatula, fold over other side on top of chicken and cheese. Flip tortilla shell and brown on other side. Serve with salsa and sour cream.

title: glazed pecans
directions: Cook sugar and orange concentrate until soft ball stage in heavy saucepan.
Add vanilla and pecans.
Cook until all water cooks out.
Spread on wax paper and let cool.
Separate with 2 forks while cooling.

title: turkey creole
directions: In 12-inch skillet over medium heat, in hot salad oil, cook onion, green pepper and garlic until onion and green pepper are tender-crisp, about 5 minutes.
Add 2 cups water, tomatoes with their liquid, chili powder, salt, sugar, oregano leaves and pepper.
Heat to boiling.
Stir in rice.
Reduce heat to low; cover skillet and simmer for 25 minutes or until rice is tender and liquid is absorbed.
Stir in turkey and heat thoroughly. Yields 4 servings.

title: italian steak
directions: Mix the ingredients together in a pan.
Cook the steak in this mixture over a low heat until done.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Add celery and onions to mixed vegetables and cook until tender as directed on package. Drain. Add mayonnaise and cheese and mix well. Place in lightly buttered casserole. Sprinkle with Ritz cracker crumbs and dot with butter. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: chocolate raspberry streusel squares
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Combine flour, oats, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Cut in butter until mixture is crumbly.
Reserve 1 cup oat mixture for streusel.
Set aside.
Press remaining oat mixture onto bottom of ungreased 9-inch square baking pan.
Bake 10 minutes.
Spread jam over crust; sprinkle evenly with chocolate chips.
Combine reserved oat mixture and almonds; sprinkle over chocolate pieces, patting gently.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes; cool completely.
Drizzle with melted chocolate.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: turkey burgers
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients together in a bowl.
Form meat mixture into patties.
Place patties in the refrigerator for about 30 minutes before grilling.
Place on outdoor grill.
Baste patties with barbecue sauce while cooking.
Cook for about 5 to 7 minutes on each side.

title: barbecue spareribs
directions: Boil ribs with 1-inch piece of fresh ginger until cooked. Drain.
Soak ribs for 1 hour in remaining ingredients.
Remove from marinade.
Place in single layer on broiler pan. Broil until browned.

title: shrimp casserole
directions: Saute onion, green peppers and celery to remove stiffness. Add mushrooms and 2 cups raw shrimp.
Cook rice (1 cup) in saucepan using mushroom liquid for part of liquid.
Combine rice to shrimp mixture in casserole and fold in 1 cup sour cream.
Bake at 350 degrees for 35 minutes or until hot.

title: "yum yum" chilli
directions: Brown hamburger meat.
Drain off grease.
Add chopped onion, celery and green pepper.
Saute for 5 minutes.
Add rest of ingredients and simmer for an hour or more.
Picante sauce can be added if desired.

title: peach supreme
directions: Make Jiffy cake mix according to instructions and bake in oblong baking dish.
This will make a very thin layer of cake in bottom of pan.
Cool.
Mix instant pudding according to directions.
Add 8 ounce package cream cheese; beat until smooth. Pour over cake, arrange sliced peaches on top of pudding.
Cover peaches with Cool Whip and refrigerate.
It is usually best if made a day ahead of time and allowed to cool overnight.
Peaches can be substituted with pineapple, strawberries, etc.

title: yam pecan pie
directions: Combine first seven ingredients and pour into unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Top with butter, brown sugar and pecans.
Bake an additional 25 minutes.
When cool, serve with whipped cream.

title: party punch
directions: Mix juices according to directions.
Add ginger ale and sherbet when ready to serve.

title: brownie pie
directions: In medium saucepan melt butter and chocolate square.
In a bowl stir together next 4 ingredients.
Add to chocolate mixture, then add vanilla.
Stir together.
Pour into 9-inch glass pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: autumn harvest bisque
directions: In a kettle, cook onions, leeks and celery in 3 tablespoons butter over moderate heat, stirring for 5 minutes or until softened.
Add carrots, squash, turnips, apples and stock; bring to a boil and simmer 45 minutes or until vegetables are soft.
In small saucepan, melt 6 tablespoons butter over moderate heat.
Add flour and cook roux, stirring 3 minutes.
Remove pan from heat. Add 1 cup soup liquid in a stream, stirring.
Stir mix into soup pot.
Add cider, nutmeg, sage, rosemary, salt and pepper; simmer for 10 minutes.
Stir in cream and Gruyere.
Ladle into heated bowls and garnish.
Serves 6 to 8. Makes 9 cups.

title: old fashioned tea cakes
directions: Combine sugar and molasses.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add well beaten egg, milk and vanilla.
Mix and sift dry ingredients and add to first mixture.
Chill dough until firm enough to handle.
Roll out on floured surface to 1/4-inch thickness.
Cut with cutter and bake on buttered cookie sheet 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.

title: breaded veal panne
directions: Trim veal scallops to remove any tendons from edges.
Using a flat veal pounder or meat mallet, pound veal until very thin and almost doubled in size.
Pat dry with paper towels; set aside.
In a medium bowl, combine bread crumbs, salt and pepper; set aside.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Roll into a ball and roll in crushed nuts.
Chill at least 2 hours before serving.

title: spiced cider
directions: Put cider in pan.
Add sugar and cinnamon sticks; stir.
Put other spices in cheesecloth and tie securely.
Add to cider mixture.
Heat on stove until hot; simmer on medium-low heat for 20 minutes.
Remove spices.
Serve hot with cinnamon stick.

title: cajun red beans and rice salad
directions: In large bowl, combine rice, red beans, tomato, green bell pepper, red onion and garlic; mix well.
In small jar with tight-fitting lid, combine the oil, vinegar, chili powder, seasoned salt, salt, pepper and hot sauce and shake well.
Pour dressing over salad and toss gently to coat.
Cover and refrigerate 1 hour to blend flavors.
Makes 12 servings.

title: seasoned crackers
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in small bowl; mix well.
Pour over crackers in bowl; toss to coat well.
Place in airtight container.
Let stand several hours for better flavor.
You can add more garlic and dill weed, if you like.

title: tarts
directions: Combine flour and salt. Cut in shortening and butter until mixture resembles coarse meal. Sprinkle milk (1 tablespoon at a time) over mixture.
Stir with fork until dry ingredients are moistened. Shape into balls (about 3/4-inch).
Place into ungreased mini muffin pans and shape to make tarts.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes. Cool.
Yields 60 tarts.

title: sesame baked chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat egg and milk together.
Combine flour, baking powder, salt, paprika and sesame seed in a paper bag.
Dip the chicken pieces in the egg mixture and then shake in the paper bag.
Place the chicken pieces skin side up in a baking dish so that they do not touch each other.
Pour melted butter over and bake 1 hour.

title: sugarless oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients, beating well.
Let stand 5 minutes so that oats will absorb moisture.
Drop dough by heaping teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Let stand 1 minute on cookie sheets; transfer to wire racks to cool completely.

title: chess pie
directions: Melt butter; cool slightly.
Mix all ingredients.
Use chocolate, coconut or lemon to flavor to taste (1 tablespoon cocoa or 1/2 cup coconut or 3 tablespoons of lemon juice) and omit vanilla.
For plain Chess Pie, just use vanilla.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Cream butter until light and fluffy.
Gradually beat in sugar. Beat in egg until well blended.
Stir in milk.
Sift flour with baking powder and nutmeg.
Add all to batter at once and stir until well blended and smooth.
Drop by tablespoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Sprinkle top of cookies with sugar mixed with ground nutmeg.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Remove from pan while warm and cool on rack.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix lemon juice to sweetened condensed milk.
Fold in whipping cream and strawberries.
Do not beat.
Add flavoring to taste. Place in baked pie shell.
Chill.

title: cherry coke jello
directions: Bring 1 Coke to boil; pour over Jell-O and dissolve.
Add remaining Coke; mix well.
Add pineapple and nuts; mix well. Refrigerate until jelled and enjoy.

title: corn salad
directions: Drain vegetables.
Mix all ingredients and let set overnight.

title: easy pickled mushrooms
directions: Wash mushrooms and cut in half.
Place in Pyrex bowl, pour dressing over.
Microwave for 4 minutes.
Let cool and refrigerate for 12 hours.

title: peach custard pie
directions: Combine above ingredients.
Place about 8 peaches sliced (fresh or canned) in unbaked 9-inch pie shell.
Pour mixture over peaches.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes until custard sets and is slightly brown.

title: mama's peanut butter candy
directions: Cook syrup, sugar and water until it makes a hard ball. Pour over egg whites that have been stiffly beaten.
Beat this mixture until stiff
enough
to
spread on buttered wax paper. Spread peanut butter on
top
of
mixture	and
roll up like a jelly roll.
Wrap
wax
paper
around roll and cool completely before cutting into slices.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Cream together oleo, sugar, cocoa, vanilla and eggs. Add flour, nuts and coconut; mix well. Spread in a sheet pan. Bake at 350°.

title: instant russian tea
directions: Mix thoroughly.
Store in jar with tight lid.

title: caramel apple sauce
directions: Melt caramels.
Add sour cream.
Cut up apples and pour caramel over for easy eating or put stick in apples and dip. Caramel will remain soft.

title: yams with orange sauce
directions: Cook yams until tender in water.
Remove skins and slice into greased casserole dish.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over yams.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: pumpkin-pecan bread(rich raisin-filled loaf)
directions: About 2 1/2 hours before serving or a day ahead, grease 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Preheat oven to 350°.

title: kid's pizza
directions: Split an English muffin in half.
Place 1 tablespoon of pizza sauce on top of each half.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese. Place under the broiler until the cheese melts.

title: cool orange delight
directions: Mix cottage cheese with orange jello and mix well.
Add Cool Whip and mix well.
Add crushed pineapple and mandarin oranges, well drained.
Chill and serve.
Serves 6.

title: ginger water
directions: Mix sugar and ginger. Add vinegar, then water.
Chill.
A great thirst quencher!

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Combine vegetables.
Mix vinegar, oil and sugar; pour over vegetables.
Mix well; let stand in refrigerator overnight.

title: stuffed potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes in microwave.
Peel off skins and cut into chunks.
Place potatoes in large mixing bowl.
Add all ingredients and beat until smooth.
Spoon into foil potato boats.
Bake at 350° for about 5 to 10 minutes.
Top with Cheddar cheese and heat until the cheese melts.
Yields 20 (1/2-cup) servings.

title: vodka slush
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Mix all ingredients together and freeze for 24 hours.
Stir a couple of times while it is freezing.
Put a couple of scoops of slush in cup and add 7-Up.

title: pickly porcupines
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Mix ingredients together and shape into balls.
Brown in oven for 15 minutes.
Pour 2 cups tomato juice over them.
Bake in oven at 325° for 1 hour.

title: parmesan twist
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 2 baking sheets.
In medium bowl, beat together the Parmesan cheese and butter with electric mixer until mixture is fluffy; add sour cream and beat.
In small bowl, combine flour and seasonings.
Beat flour mixture into cheese mixture.
Knead dough lightly and divide in half.
On lightly floured surface, roll out dough into 12 x 6-inch rectangles; cut into twenty-four 6 x 1/2-inch strips.
Holding each strip by ends, gently twist the pastry 2 or 3 times and place on prepared baking sheets.
Bake the twist in the oven at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.
But before you put in oven and before you separate them, brush with yolk and water mixture and sprinkle with sesame seed or poppy seed.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Mix well.
Marinate several days before serving.

title: frying pan cookies
directions: Put in large heavy frying pan and cook like scrambled eggs (about 5 minutes) oleo, sugar, dates and egg.
Remove from heat and add nuts, Rice Krispies and vanilla.
Let cool and form into balls and roll in coconut.

title: d. d.'s cheese cookies
directions: Crumble by hand and make into small balls.
Bake for 10 minutes at 375°, or until slightly browned.

title: chicken tortellini soup
directions: In large pot, combine water, chicken broth, soup, chicken, carrots, onion, vermouth, garlic, basil and oregano.
Bring to a boil; add tortellini.
Simmer, uncovered, for 20 minutes.
Add broccoli.
Simmer an additional 5 to 10 minutes or until broccoli is tender.
Serve with cheese.
Makes 10 (1 1/2 cup) servings.

title: the world's easiest peanut clusters(microwave)
directions: Mix and melt in microwave for 3 minutes.
Drop in clusters on waxed paper.

title: baked stuffed shrimp
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease an oblong glass baking dish.
Peel, devein and clean shrimp.
Leave the tails intact. Lightly mix the seasoned crumbs with the crab meat.
Add beaten egg, mixing in lightly.

title: chicken rice bake
directions: Combine soups and milk.
Heat.
Add rice.
Pour into pan.
Lay chicken pieces on top.
Sprinkle onion soup mix on top of this. Cover with foil.
Bake at 325° for 2 hours.

title: corn fritters
directions: Beat egg.
Add milk and corn.
Add sifted flour, baking powder, salt and dab of pepper.
Mix well.
Stir in fat.
Drop by tablespoon into hot deep fat and fry until golden.

title: cherries jubilee
directions: Beat together first 5 ingredients.
Pour into chilled crust. Chill about 1 hour.
Top with cherry pie filling (you can also use blueberry pie filling).

title: low country boil
directions: Fill large stock pot 1/2 full with water over gas cooker.
Heat to boiling.
Add crab boil seasoning, then potatoes, carrots and onions.
Boil for 20 minutes.
Add sausage and corn.
Boil 10 minutes.
Turn down heat and add shrimp.
As soon as they turn pink, remove all ingredients from water and serve.
Have butter for corn and seafood sauce available.
Great for Super Bowl parties.

title: chicken pie
directions: In large greased casserole, put chicken in bottom of dish. Mix broth and soup together.
Sprinkle bird with frozen vegetables.
Next pour in soup mix.
Mix flour and buttermilk together.
Add oleo, salt and pepper.
Pour over bird mixture. Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: munching peanut brittle
directions: Stir the peanuts, sugar, corn syrup and salt together in a 1 1/2 to 2-quart casserole.
Place in microwave oven and cook 7 to 8 minutes on High, stirring well after 4 minutes.
Add the butter and vanilla to hot syrup, blending well.
Return to oven and cook 1 minute more.
Peanuts will be lightly browned and syrup very hot.
Add soda to mixture and gently stir until light and foamy. Pour mixture on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Let cool 1/2 to 1 hour.
When cool, break into small pieces and store in airtight container.
Makes approximately 1 pound.
(If using roasted salted peanuts, omit salt and add peanuts after first 4 minutes of cooking.)

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients together.
Form into loaf.
Place in baking dish.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Mix and pour over loaf.
Baste often.
Start baking at 350° or microwave on Medium-high for 22 to 24 minutes.

title: quick cobbler
directions: Pour cherries into a 9-inch, deep dish pie crust.
Mix remaining
ingredients well and pour over cherries.
Bake for 70 minutes at 350°.

title: cheese-filled coffee cake
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.

Mix flour, 3/4 cup sugar and salt. Beat egg yolks and blend in sour cream, butter and yeast. Stir this egg yolk mixture into flour to make a soft, smooth dough. Knead for 5 minutes on floured surface. Put in a bowl; cover.
Let rise until almost double.

title: hot onion-cheese canapes
directions: Remove crusts from bread. Cut each slice into quarters. Combine mayonnaise, cheese and onion. Spread on bread.
Broil about 4-inches from heat until lightly browned.
Mixture will keep several days in refrigerator.
Yields 32 squares.

title: soft ginger cookies
directions: Sift together the first 5 ingredients and set aside.
In large mixing bowl, beat margarine; gradually add sugar.
Beat until fluffy.
Add egg and molasses.
Beat well.
Stir in dry ingredients.
Shape into 1 1/2-inch balls (about one heaping tablespoonful).

title: easy chicken supreme
directions: Place chicken in shallow baking dish.
Top each with 1/2 slice of cheese.
Mix soup with 1/2 can of milk and pour over chicken. Mix stuffing with melted butter.
Spoon over soup.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve with rice.

title: delicious hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix all contents together by shaking in a large container. For each cup, use 1/4 cup mix and fill cup with boiling water. Add marshmallow if desired.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all but the cheese together and bake in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 35 minutes.
Top with grated cheese and bake for 10 minutes longer.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place apples in greased, shallow baking dish.
Sprinkle with lemon juice.
Combine dry items.
Add melted butter, mixing until crumbly.
Sprinkle crumbs over apples.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until apples are tender.

title: enchiladas
directions: Brown hamburger meat; drain grease.
Mix taco seasoning mix with 1/3 cup of water.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Preheat oven at 350°.
Rol meat inside shells.
Cover with tomato sauce in pan, then put shredded cheese, onions and olives and bake for 15 minutes.

title: caramel pie
directions: Beat egg yolks and add milk.
Mix 1/2 cup sugar with flour, getting out all lumps.
Add to egg mixture. Warm in saucepan, stirring well.
Caramelize the other 1/2 cup sugar in heavy skillet; brown, do not burn!
Add butter to make a syrup.
Pour this into other mixture.
Cook until thick.
Pour into prepared pie shell.
Beat egg whites until stiff; put on top of pie.

title: super amazing cookies
directions: Cream butter and peanut butter.
Gradually add sugars and blend until mixed.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat until smooth.
Stir together flour and soda and add to creamed mixture. Stir in chocolate chips.
Drop from a teaspoon onto greased baking sheet.
Slightly flatten dough with back of spoon.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes.
Makes 6 dozen 2-inch cookies.

title: lemon bars
directions: Mix with fingers the first three ingredients and spread in a 9 x 10-inch pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: peanut butter quickies
directions: Mix together and drop by spoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt butter, peanut butter and chocolate chips.
Coat Rice Chex.
Put in a large bag with powdered sugar.
Shake; refrigerate.
Makes 8 servings.

title: crisp corn sticks
directions: Sift corn meal.
Add salt and soda; mix.
Add oil; stir.
Add buttermilk and syrup; stir well.
Fill thoroughly greased iron corn stick pans; bake at 400° for 1/2 hour.
Makes 9 sticks.
Easy to add to for large family.

title: grandma kinney's plain cake
directions: Mix shortening and sugar.
Add remaining ingredients.
Makes 2 layers or a 9 x 13-inch cake.
Bake at 350° approximately 25 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: neiman-marcus bars
directions: Mix cake mix, margarine, egg and pecans and pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan, which has been greased and floured.
Then mix powdered sugar, cream cheese, eggs and coconut.
Pour this mixture over cake mixture and bake at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Alternate sliced potatoes and sliced onions in casserole dish. Place browned pork chops on top, covered with can of tomato soup together with 1 soup can water.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Bake 1 hour and 30 minutes at 350°.

title: roast beef round up(for leftover roast beef.)
directions: Brown onion in fat and stir in flour.
Add water, catsup, chili powder, instant bouillon, cumin and salt, stirring to combine.
Cook slowly, stirring often, 12 to 15 minutes or until thickened.
Stir in beef and green pepper strips; cook slowly for 5 to 10 minutes.
Serve with corn bread squares; top with cheese, if desired.
Yield: 4 servings.

title: summer squash casserole
directions: Melt butter and stir into dressing.
Divide and place half onto bottom of 8 x 12-inch baking dish.
Combine squash, onions, soup, chestnuts and pimientos; pour over dressing.
Cover squash with remaining dressing and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes. Yields 10 to 12 servings.

title: venison stir-fry
directions: Put the first 6 items in a skillet over medium heat and saute until all ingredients are cooked.
Add a little water if it starts to stick.
Season to taste. Add the remaining ingredients. Stir in and blend well. Season again to taste.
When rice is hot and all ingredients are blended, remove from heat.
You can prepare this dish in an electric wok, regular wok or in a regular skillet.

title: pineapple pound cake
directions: Cream Crisco, butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Add flour and salt, alternating with milk to mixture; beat well.
Fold in pineapple with juice.
Grease and flour pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes, until done.
Do not preheat oven.
Bake in cold oven.

title: susie's potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes, butter, celery and carrots until potatoes are tender.
Mix flour with milk to make thicker to personal preference.
Add flour mixture to pan, stirring constantly to prevent sticking on the bottom.
Stir 3-5 minutes then add cheese. Add salt and pepper anytime while potatoes are cooking.

title: southern spoon bread
directions: Stir the cornmeal and salt into the boiling water and mix well.
Beat in the butter, eggs and milk.

title: creole burgers
directions: Brown ground beef with onion in skillet, stirring until ground beef is crumbly; drain.
Add soup, prepared mustard, catsup, salt and pepper; mix well.
Simmer for 5 to 10 minutes or until flavors are blended, stirring occasionally.
Toast and butter buns.
Serve ground beef mixture on buns.
May top with lettuce, if desired. Yield:
6 servings.

title: fruit pudding
directions: Mix pudding and juices.
Heat to a boil; boil until thick. Mix together oranges, pineapple, bananas, grapes and marshmallows. Pour pudding mix over and stir.
Refrigerate.

title: chopped chicken livers
directions: Simmer chicken livers in enough water to cover (I add bouillon to water).
Saute onion in 3 tablespoons butter or oleo.
Place livers and eggs in bowl and chop together.
Add the onion mixture and mayonnaise for desired consistency.
Season to taste with salt, pepper and paprika.
Chill.
Serve with Melba rounds.
Can be garnished with thinly sliced red onion.

title: rosemary-thyme potatoes
directions: Peel and chop potatoes.
Toss with a little oil.
Add rosemary and thyme.
Sprinkle in pepper.
Microwave 10 minutes.
Add butter flavored salt and more pepper.
Toss and microwave more if needed.

title: crab hors d'oeuvres
directions: Let all set at room temperature for 15 minutes.
Mix all together.
Quarter muffins and spread thickly.
Freeze 30 minutes on sheet before using.
Put in oven at 350° for 20 minutes in foil.
Double recipe = 92 snacks.

title: hot chicken pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Put in pie tin with pastry on bottom and top.
Bake until golden brown.

title: popcorn cake
directions: Pour the melted mixture over the popcorn and candy.
Press tightly into a large lightly greased Bundt or angel food cake pan. (Pam can be used.)
Let set until firm or refrigerate to set quickly.

title: chicken, red grape and apple salad
directions: Combine chicken, grapes, apple, celery, raisins and onion in a bowl; toss gently.
In a separate bowl, combine yogurt, mayonnaise, lemon juice, celery leaves and salt.
Add to chicken mixture; toss gently to coat.
Cover and chill.
Serve on individual lettuce-lined serving plates.
Makes 6 servings (1 cup each).

title: baked beans
directions: Bake at 325°.
Cook 2 hours, covered, then 1/2 hour, uncovered.

title: onion roasted potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
In plastic bag, add all ingredients. Shake until potatoes are evenly coated.
Empty contents into shallow baking dish.
Bake, stirring occasionally, for 40 minutes or until potatoes are tender and golden brown.
Garnish with chopped parsley if desired.
Makes about 8 servings.

title: 2 minute fudge
directions: Stir in confectioners sugar, cocoa, salt, milk, vanilla extract until blended in 1 1/2-quart dish.
Top with butter. Microwave on High for 2 minutes.
Stir smooth.
Blend in nuts. Pour into buttered 8-inch square dish.
Chill.
This recipe is for microwave.

title: tarragon-tanged shrimp
directions: Place cooked, shelled, deveined shrimp in a large serving bowl with cooked rice, torn romaine lettuce, orange slices, halved cherry tomatoes and sliced onion.
In a small bowl, whisk together oil, frozen orange juice, vinegar, olive oil, garlic powder, salt, tarragon leaves, crushed and pepper.
Toss with shrimp, rice and lettuce.

title: bell pepper steak and rice
directions: Mix tomatoes, soy sauce and tomato sauce and bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer while browning the steak.
Add bell peppers to cooking steak.
Drain grease; add tomato mixture.
Simmer for 1 hour.
For a thicker sauce, add a little cornstarch.
Serve over rice.

title: dilly beans
directions: Put pepper, garlic and dill in a pint jar.
Stack whole green beans in jar.
Bring to a boil, water, vinegar and salt.
Pour over beans.
Put in hot bath 10 minutes.

title: apple pandowdy(serves 6)
directions: Melt oleo.
Add sugar and egg, then dry ingredients.
Stir. Bake in greased pie plate for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: hearty chili
directions: In a large saucepan, cook beef, chopped onion and garlic until beef is brown and onion is tender; drain off fat.
Stir undrained tomatoes, tomato sauce, chili powder, salt and pepper into browned meat in saucepan. Bring to boiling.
Reduce heat. Cover and simmer for 1 hour.
Add drained beans to saucepan. Cover and simmer for 30 minutes. To serve, place some rice in the bottom of chili bowls.
Top with chili, cheese and optional onions and sour cream.
Makes 5 to 6 servings.

title: diabetic cookies
directions: Mix together first 3 ingredients.
Cook 1 minute.
Stir while cooking.
Add remaining ingredients.
Make out in patties. Refrigerate.
Can be frozen.
This makes a large amount.

title: 7-up cake and icing
directions: Beat all ingredients together; add the 7-Up last. Pour into a tube pan. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: beef enchilada rice
directions: Brown meat, onion and green pepper together in a skillet until cooked, then drain well.
Mix in a large bowl the rice, spices, picante sauce and tomato juice.
Fold in the cooked meat mixture. Place in a greased casserole dish and bake in a 350° oven for 25 minutes.
Remove from the oven and sprinkle the top with the cheese.
Return to the oven and bake for 10 more minutes.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Melt butter.
Mix well with flour and nuts.
Line a 10 x 12 x 2-inch pan with mixture.
Cook at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool. Combine sugar, cream cheese and 1 cup Cool Whip; spread over crust.
Mix pudding and milk; beat until thick.
Spread over cream cheese mixture.
Top with remaining Cool Whip.

title: sweet dill pickles
directions: Put sliced pickles back in jar.
Bring to boil last four ingredients and pour over pickles.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator before serving.

title: polish potatoes
directions: Heat potatoes in juice; then drain.
Saute onions in oleo. Add to potatoes.
Pour in salad dressing and stir with rubber spatula.
Add salt and pepper.
Then add dry parsley flakes.

title: sugarless gingerbread
directions: Combine shortening and molasses; add egg.
Stir until thoroughly blended.
Mix and sift dry ingredients and add alternately with hot water.
Pour into well-greased and floured 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake 45 minutes in 350° oven.
Serves 16.

title: mississippi corn bread
directions: In a bowl, mix together sour cream, corn and oil.
Stir in cornmeal, salt, baking powder and eggs.
Pour batter into well-greased 9-inch square pan or 12-cup muffin tin.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes for bread or 20 to 25 minutes for muffins.

title: crab cakes with shrimp
directions: Pick over the crab meat to remove any cartilage or shell. Leave the lumps as large as possible.
Shell and devein shrimp. Put the shrimp in a food processor or blender and add the egg, cream, salt and pepper.
Blend as finely as possible.
Pour and scrape the mixture into a mixing bowl.
Add the crab meat, green onion, mustard, Worcestershire sauce and Tabasco sauce.
Blend gently, but thoroughly.
Shape the mixture into 10 cakes.
Heat 2 tablespoons oil in a nonstick skillet and add the cakes, several at a time.
Cook over medium heat about 3 minutes on each side or until golden brown.
Serve with Parsley Butter.
Refrigerate the cakes when you first make them to get them good and cold before cooking.

title: sad cake
directions: Combine eggs and vanilla; beat well.
Mix Bisquick, brown sugar and cinnamon, then beat 2 minutes. Combine pecans and coconut into the other ingredients.
Bake in a 9 1/4 x 13 x 2-inch pan at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes. If you want a glaze, combine milk and powdered sugar with vanilla flavoring and spread over warm cake.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients thoroughly and place firmly into a loaf pan.
Bake in a moderate oven at 350° for about 1 hour.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: spinach salad dressing
directions: Mix well.
Use on a salad made of spinach, mushrooms, sliced eggs and bean sprouts.

title: emmie's bread
directions: Add yeast and warm water in mixing bowl.
Add crisco, sugar, salt, and mix well.
Add enough flour to make right consistency for kneading.
Knead until air bubbles are out. Dough not sticky. Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: swedish pancakes
directions: Melt butter or margarine.
Mix all ingredients together until blended.
Heat lightly greased frypan.
Pour in just enough batter to cover the bottom of the pan.
Turn when lightly browned. Serve, rolled up with your favorite filling.
Makes about 5 (9-inch) pancakes.

title: broccoli bread
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients until thoroughly blended.
Add cornbread mix, stirring until just moistened.
Pour batter into a 10-inch cast-iron skillet coated with vegetable cooking spray. Bake at 425° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Yields 10 wedges.
(Note: May bake bread in square baking dish.)

title: pizza with hamburger crust
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
In a bowl, mix beef, bread crumbs and oregano.
Stir in 1/2 cup tomato sauce.
Spread mixture in bottom of 10-inch pizza pan.
Pour 1/2 cup tomato sauce on top.
Spread on top of beans and cheese.
Bake, uncovered, 20 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chess pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: asparagus parmigiana
directions: Drain asparagus.
Arrange in shallow baking dish.
Saute onion and garlic in oil until golden brown.
Add salt, Tabasco sauce and tomatoes.
Simmer, uncovered, for 10 minutes.
Add thyme and tomato sauce.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Pour sauce over asparagus; place Mozzarella cheese over top.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: baked sausage casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients well, except cheese. Pour in baking dish. Cover with cheese.
Let stand in refrigerator.
Bake at 350° until desired brown stage.

title: frozen salad
directions: Mix together; pour into pan or dish sprayed with Pam and freeze.

title: peppercorn bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients together in a large bowl.
Now make a well and pour in cream-style corn, evaporated milk and egg in that order, then mix together.
Pour into greased baking dish 1/2 of the mixture (9 x 12-inches).
Place enough cheese over entire mixture, then scatter onions, chives and sweet peppers over the cheese. Pour in the remaining mixture, then repeat procedure with cheese, onions, chives and peppers.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: skillet sweet potatoes
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Add potatoes and water.
Sprinkle sugar over all. Cook, uncovered, on medium heat, stirring often, for about 30 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: layered derby day dip
directions: Combine cream cheese, sour cream, mayonnaise, bouillon and ground red pepper; blend until smooth.
Let mixture stand 15 minutes to dissolve bouillon; stir.

title: mashed potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes in water until soft.
Drain and mash with electric mixer until smooth.
In small bowl, blend cream cheese and sour cream until smooth.
Pour cheese mixture into potatoes and mix until really smooth.
Pour into a 1 1/2-quart casserole. Dot with butter and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until top starts to turn a little brown.

title: mexican dip with chips
directions: Layer baking pan with cream cheese or sour cream, then layer each ingredient except for cheese.
Cook 20 to 30 minutes in a 350° oven.
Take pan out and mix ingredients.
Add cheese and put in oven until cheese melts.
(Serve with chips.)

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix first five items together.
When jello is set, top with cream cheese and sour cream.
Mix these together until fluffy, then put on jello.

title: norwegian gold cake
directions: Mix flour and shortening at low speed.
Add eggs, 1 at a time. Mix well. Sift sugar, salt and baking powder.
Add to cream mixture.
Beat well.
Add almond flavoring and beat for 2 minutes at low speed.
Bake for 1 hour at 325° in a lightly greased and floured Bundt pan.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar when cooled.

title: creole okra
directions: Wash and cut okra into 3/4-inch pieces.
Chop onion and bell pepper.
Saute onion and pepper until tender in oil.
Add stewed tomatoes and Ro-Tel tomatoes; add okra.
Stew on low setting in skillet or cook in baking dish in oven until okra is tender.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: pam's party punch
directions: Mix jello in 9 cups boiling water.
Mix 4 cups sugar in 5 cups boiling water.
Combine.
Add 2 large cans pineapple juice and ReaLemon.
Freeze.
When ready to use, mash mixture with potato masher and add desired amount of 7-Up or ginger ale.

title: crescent cheesecake
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar, almond extract and egg yolk until smooth.
Spread 1 package crescent rolls in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread cheese mixture on top.
Put second package of crescent rolls on top.
Brush top with egg white and sprinkle with 1/4 cup sugar.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve with fresh fruit such as strawberries.

title: chicken enchilada casserole
directions: Cook and debone chicken.
Reserve 1 cup broth.
Combine soups, chilies and spices to broth.
Blend well.
Preheat oven to 350°. Cover bottom of 2 1/2 to 3-quart casserole dish with 2 cups chips. Spread 1/2 chicken over chips; then half sauce and then half cheese.
Repeat layers, ending with cheese.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: hungry jack beef and bean round-up
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In skillet brown ground beef and onion; drain.
Stir in barbecue sauce, brown sugar and beans.
Heat until bubbly.
Pour into 2 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Separate dough into 10 biscuits.
Cut each biscuit in half.
Place biscuits cut side down over hot meat mixture in spoke fashion around the edge of casserole.
Sprinkle cheese over biscuits.
Bake at 375° for 22 to 27 minutes or until biscuits are golden brown.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cucumber and dill salad
directions: In large mixing bowl, combine yogurt, lemon juice, dill and honey.
Chill for 15 minutes.
Just before serving, peel and seed the cucumbers.
Slice thinly, then gently combine with yogurt mixture.
Divide greens among the salad plates (4).
Top with cucumber mixture.

title: salmon croquettes
directions: Drain the salmon, reserving the liquid.
Flake the salmon and remove the skin and bones.
In a large bowl, combine the salmon, reserved liquid, eggs, salt and corn flake crumbs to make a firm mixture.
Blend in the baking powder.
Shape into croquettes and fry until lightly browned.
Serves 4.

title: raves review coconut cake
directions: Blend cake mix, pudding, water, eggs and oil in a large mixing bowl.
Beat
at
medium
speed
for 4 minutes.
Stir in coconut and nuts.
Pour into 3 greased and floured 9-inch cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Frost with Coconut Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: fruit salad dressing
directions: Reserve juice from any fruit used in salad.
Add to mayonnaise; mix thoroughly.
Add honey Dijon dressing; mix until smooth.
Store in refrigerator.

title: cabbage birds
directions: Select 8 tender white cabbage leaves and pour boiling water over them to make pliant. Mix ground beef, tomato pulp, rice, eggs, salt and pepper.
Work mixture with hands and shape into rolls. Wrap cabbage leaves around meat rolls, pinning each end with toothpicks.
Place in stewer (side by side).
Pour hot water over just enough to cover, with 1 tablespoon of oil to season cabbage. Put on lid and simmer until tender.

Remove from stewer with egg turner and place on platter carefully. Serve with sauce made of gravy they were cooked in by adding thickening made of 1 tablespoon flour or cornstarch and enough water to mix to smooth paste.
Cook until thick as heavy cream.
Let cool slightly before serving. They will slice like cold meat.

title: norwegian meatballs
directions: Melt butter.
Add onions and fry until soft and translucent.

title: chow chow
directions: Grind tomatoes, peppers and onions using a coarse grinder. Add remaining ingredients and cook until thick (about 2 hours). Stir frequently to prevent burning.
Pack in hot sterilized jars and seal immediately.
Very good on cooked greens.
Great on hot dogs.
Makes 4 pints.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Cream sugar and margarine; add flour, milk and baking powder. Pour batter in greased pan and add fruit.
Bake at 400° until brown and set.
You may use any other fruit.

title: lila's chocolate sheet cake
directions: Sift
flour,
sugar
and
salt together.
Combine oleo, water and
cocoa	in a pan until melted.	Pour into flour and sugar mixture.
Add
the	rest of the ingredients.
Mix well. Bake for 20 minutes at 350° in a 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch pan. Last 5 minutes start Quick and Easy Chocolate Frosting.

title: coconut pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Add flour, butter and milk.
Add coconut. Pour into partially baked pie shell and bake about 45 minutes or until firm, at 325°.

title: cherry dump cake
directions: Pour pie filling in bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add pineapple.
Sprinkle cake mix over pineapple.
Pour margarine or butter over cake mix.
Add coconut.
Sprinkle pecans over entire cake.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: hot onion salad
directions: Peel onions and slice 1/4-inch thick.
Fry bacon until crisp; drain.
Separate onion into rings and saute in bacon drippings until tender-crisp.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and flour.
Stir gently.
Add vinegar and cook until slightly thickened.
Sprinkle with bacon crumbs and parsley.
Serve warm.

title: chinese noodles
directions: Chop vegetables.
In electric frypan, fry onion and celery in oil.
Dissolve broth in 2 cups of water and pour over onion and celery.
Add chopped carrots; let simmer until tender.
Add more water if necessary.
Cook noodles in separate pot until tender. Add noodles and gluten to electric frypan.
Keep adding water as necessary.
Add broccoli and cover to steam broccoli until tender. Serve with soy sauce.

title: sparkling lemonade
directions: Soak lemons in hot water for about 15 minutes.
Dissolve sugar in 1 cup boiling water and cool.
Squeeze juice from lemons. Combine fresh squeezed juice with dissolved sugar water.
Pour into 2-quart pitcher and add sparkling water.
Check for sweetness, but added sugar will not dissolve well.
Add ice and garnish with lemon slice.

title: crustless cheese pie
directions: Cream the cheese; add other ingredients.
Beat until creamy and smooth.
Bake in 13 x 9-inch Pyrex dish.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes, then lower temperature to 250° and bake for 45 minutes more.

title: pumpkin squares
directions: In mixing bowl, stir together the pumpkin, brown sugar, eggs and oil until well mixed.
Combine the flour, oats, cinnamon, baking powder and baking soda.
Add flour mixture to pumpkin mixture and mix well.
Pour into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: million dollar fudge
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in large bowl.
Set aside.
Boil together the sugar and canned milk for 8 minutes; start timing after it comes to a boil.
Pour hot mixture over chips mixture and stir until well blended and chips are melted.
Pour into buttered pan.
Cool.
Makes about 5 pounds.

title: gazpacho
directions: Combine all ingredients in a stainless steel or glass bowl. Cover and chill thoroughly, at least 4 hours.
Serve in chilled cups.
Top with croutons.
Makes 6 servings.

title: dressing casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Brown onion in margarine.
Mix in all the rest of ingredients.
Put into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake 1 hour.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all and bake at same temperature you bake regular cornbread.

title: meat cabbage casserole
directions: In medium skillet, saute onion in butter until soft, but not brown.
Add meat.
Cook until loses pink color.
In a 2 quart buttered casserole dish, layer carrots and half of cabbage. Sprinkle with salt.
Add meat mixture; press down slightly.
Add remaining cabbage.
To spaghetti sauce, add Worcestershire sauce and chives.
Pour over top of casserole.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until cabbage is soft.
Add cheese to top.
Bake uncovered for another 5 to 8 minutes until cheese is melted. Serve immediately.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream the margarine and shortening.
Add sugar and mix well. Add egg yolks, one at a time, and beat until fluffy.
Combine flour and soda and add to mixture alternately with buttermilk. Stir in vanilla, coconut and pecans.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour into 3 floured and greased pans.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool and frost with cream cheese frosting.

title: hawaiian cake
directions: Mix by hand all ingredients.
Grease and flour a 9x13 pan. Pour batter in pan.

title: e. z. fudge
directions: Melt all together and pour into buttered pan or dish.
Cool thoroughly and cut into pieces.

title: easy chocolate pie
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients with a small amount of the milk. Add the egg yolks, the rest of the milk, margarine and vanilla. Bring to a boil over medium heat until thick, stirring constantly. Pour into a pre-baked crust.
Top with meringue if desired. Recipe works well when doubled, too.

title: pie crust (4)
directions: With a fork, mix first 4 ingredients in a separate bowl.
In another bowl, beat egg, water and vinegar.
Combine the 2 mixtures until all ingredients are moistened.
With hands, mold dough into a ball.
Chill at least 15 minutes.
Dough can be left in the refrigerator up to 3 days or frozen until ready to use.

title: grannie's griddle scones
directions: For variations, add currants or raisins.

title: fresh coconut cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter, adding sugar a small amount at a time. Beat until light and fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add flour, coconut milk, canned cream and vanilla at low speed, adding the baking powder with the last of flour.
Bake in 9-inch pans 30 or 35 minutes at 375°.

title: polish beans
directions: Brown bacon, kielbasa and onion in drippings from bacon.
Toss with remaining ingredients and bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: benihana ginger sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender and process until smooth. Serves 6.

title: shrimp jambalaya
directions: Cook garlic, onion, pepper and mushrooms in a small amount of oil.
Add tomatoes and bouillon; simmer 10 minutes.
Add water chestnuts.
Twenty to 30 minutes before serving, add rice, celery leaves and thyme.
Add shrimp at the end so they won't shrink up too much.

title: blackberry cobbler
directions: Dissolve cornstarch in juice of blackberries.
Add lemon juice.
Pour in bottom of round cake pan.
Add berries.
Separate cinnamon rolls; place over top of berries.
Bake in a 400° oven until sauce is bubbling and rolls are golden brown.
Garnish with Cool Whip.

title: sugar jumbles
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, salt and baking soda.
Mix eggs, shortening, butter and vanilla; add dry ingredients.
Mix until creamy.
Add nuts and chocolate pieces.
Stir until well blended. Drop rounded teaspoon on a greased baking sheet until light brown, 8 to 10 minutes at 375°.

title: layered taco bean dip
directions: Place in 9 x 13-inch pan in order given.
Serve with chips.

title: marinated mushrooms
directions: Combine all ingredients except mushrooms and bring to a boil (stovetop or microwave).
Add marinade to mushrooms, cover and refrigerate 8 hours or overnight.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Mix well.
Pour into a tube pan.
Cook at 325°.

title: peppermint meringues
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat egg whites until foamy.
Sprinkle with salt and cream of tartar; beat until soft peaks form.
Gradually add sugar, beating until stiff peaks form, about 7 minutes.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased foil or paper-lined baking sheets; sprinkle with the crushed candy.
Bake at 225° for 1 1/2 hours. Turn off heat; leave cookies in the oven with the door ajar for at least 1 hour or until cool.
Store in an airtight container. Yield:
3 dozen.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Combine egg, milk, 2/3 c cracker crumbs, salt, and pepper. Stir in corn and onion.
Mix well.
Put in 1 qt. casserole dish. Toss melted butter with remaining cracker crumbs.
Sprinkle on top of corn mixture.
Bake at 350 for 65-70 minutes.

title: neiman-marcus brownies
directions: Mix cake mix, butter and egg.
Spread into buttered and floured 9 x 13-inch Pyrex pan.
Mix powdered sugar, cream cheese and eggs.
Put on top of cake mixture.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: orange julius
directions: In a blender, combine orange juice, milk, water, sugar and vanilla.
Cover and blend until smooth.
With blender running add ice cubes, one at a time, through opening in lid.
Blend until smooth.
Serve immediately.
Yields 4 to 5 servings.

title: bubba's buttermilk pie
directions: Add butter to eggs.
Combine dry ingredients and add to butter and egg mix.
Add buttermilk and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour into unbaked pie shells and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 18.

title: deluxe peach ice cream
directions: Combine peaches and 1 cup of sugar, stir well, and set aside. Beat eggs with an electric mixer at medium speed until frothy. Combine 1 1/2 cups sugar, flour and salt; stir well.
Gradually add sugar mixture to eggs, beating until thick.
Add milk, mix well.
Pour egg mixture in a large saucepan.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and coats metal spoon (about 15 minutes).
Remove from heat and set pan in cold water; stir gently until cool.
Stir in cream and vanilla.
Add peaches, stirring well.

title: dump cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.

Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch cake pan. Dump undrained pineapple in pan and spread evenly. Dump pie filling on top of pineapple and spread evenly. Dump dry cake mix on top of pie filling and spread evenly. Sprinkle nuts (if desired) over the top.
Place slices of butter over top of cake. Bake 48 to 53 minutes.
Serves 24.

title: mexican meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Place in loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add salt; slowly add sugar, vanilla and then chocolate chips.
Mix thoroughly and drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Heat oven to 375°.
Put cookies in all together.
Turn off heat and leave in oven overnight.

title: new england corn chowder
directions: Chop salt and pork.
Strain fat into soup pot. Discard rendered scraps. Add onions and saute until tender.
Add flour, mixing well.
Cook without browning 3 to 4 minutes.
Add chicken stock slowly, stirring until smooth.
Add corn.
Cook potatoes separately. Drain and add to chowder. Add hot milk and cream. Season to taste.
Enjoy!

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix first six ingredients. Add mayonnaise and pile lightly into buttered aluminum or glass 9 x 13 pan. Sprinkle with cheese and potato chips. Bake at 450 degrees for 15 mins. or until heated thoroughly.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Bake at 350° or until topping is bubbly and browned some. Combine chicken, chicken soup and milk; mix well.
Add mushrooms, celery, noodles, almonds and pimento.
Saute onions in the butter. Add seasonings and mix well.
Mix all together.
Cook over low heat for 10 minutes to blend flavors.
Put in greased 2-quart casserole. Mix egg whites to yolks; mix in cheese.
Put this over casserole.

title: lo-cal tuna crispies
directions: Drain tuna.
Mix all ingredients in bowl until texture is even.
Shape into 2 equal patties.
Fry in nonstick pan until crispy brown on both sides.

title: mary hunsaker's dip
directions: Blend all ingredients well.
Add 1 small can shrimp.
Chill. Serve with crackers and/or vegetable sticks.

title: pineapple cream cheese salad
directions: Set jello as directed on package; refrigerate until almost set.
Soften cream cheese with a fork and a little cream.
Whip 1/2 pint of whip cream until stiff (may substitute Dream Whip). Whip jello; mix jello and whipped cream together.
Beat in cream cheese with a spoon.
Fold in crushed pineapple and refrigerate until set.
Put in mold.

title: cottage pudding cake
directions: Mix sugar and Crisco.
Add egg.
Sift together about 1/2 cup flour with baking soda, baking powder and nutmeg.
Add alternately with milk.
Add more flour until batter is heavy enough to stand in peaks.
Pour into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: sour cream banana pudding
directions: Prepare pudding mix with 3 1/2 cups milk using package directions.

Stir in 2 tablespoons whipped topping and sour cream. Layer vanilla wafers, banana slices and pudding mixture alternately in a 9 x 13-inch dish, ending with vanilla wafers. Top with remaining whipped topping.
Chill, covered, for 24 hours. Yield:
15 servings.

title: baked pork chops
directions: Pour mixture over pork chops.
Put foil over all and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Then, uncover and cook at same temperature for 15 minutes.
(Can bake potatoes at same time.)

title: peanut butter cups
directions: Cream the butter, peanut butter and sugars.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
Mix well.
Blend in dry ingredients.

title: easy all occasion punch
directions: Put sherbet in a bowl approximately 30 minutes before serving. Just before serving, pour Hawaiian Punch over softened sherbet and fold.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Mix and put in 1/2 gallon jar.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: cajun heath cake
directions: Sift together flour and sugar; set aside.
Place margarine, cocoa and water in a pot; bring to a boil.
Pour hot mixture on flour and sugar; mix well.
Add buttermilk, soda, vanilla and eggs. Mix well.
Pour in greased and floured oblong pan (9 x 13-inch). Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 400°.

title: 24 hour salad
directions: Add marshmallows to whipped cream.
Drain pineapple, pineapple chunks, fruit cocktail and mandarin oranges; add grapes, sometimes bananas and a few apples.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: spaghetti broccoli bake
directions: Cook spaghetti and drain.
Mix all together in a casserole and bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: upside-down ham loaf
directions: Mix the brown sugar and dry mustard together; sprinkle it all over the bottom of a loaf pan.
Set the peach halves in the loaf pan with the rounded bottoms sitting on the sugar.
Now, mix the ground ham and beef with the bread crumbs, beaten eggs, pepper and milk; pack it all into the pan right over the peaches.
Bake the loaf in a 350° oven for 1 hour.
Cool in the pan for about 10 minutes before turning it out with the peaches on top.

title: ice cream sandwiches
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Beat egg, shortening, butter, vanilla and 1/2 of cake mix until smooth, then stir in remaining cake mix until smooth.
Roll dough out; cut squares.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes.
Poke fork holes in when fresh out of oven.
Put ice cream between and freeze.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Mix pudding with milk.
Set in refrigerator for 15 minutes until it starts to set.
Beat Cool Whip into pudding mix.

title: steak strips and mushrooms
directions: Cut steaks into 1/2 x 2-inch strips.
Heat 3 tablespoons of the butter in frying pan.
Over high heat, saute meat, 3 to 4 minutes, tossing constantly until meat is cooked to your liking but do not overcook.
Remove to warm platter.
Add 3 tablespoons more butter to pan.
Add green onions and mushrooms to pan.
Saute over high heat for 3 to 4 minutes.
Remove to platter with meat. Keep warm.
Add wine and broth to pan.
Over high heat, boil, scraping the brownings from the pan into sauce.
Taste and add salt and pepper.
Add lemon juice.
Also add any juices from meat on platter.
Boil over high heat until juices are a glaze about 1/4-inch deep in pan.
Whisk in remaining butter.
Return meat and mushrooms to pan.
Toss and cook over high heat until mixture is hot.
Sprinkle with chives and serve immediately.

title: flossie johnson's cabbage casserole
directions: Cook cabbage in salted water 8 minutes and drain.
Saute onion and green pepper in bacon drippings.
Mix cabbage, bacon, onion, green pepper, soup, milk and cheese and turn into casserole.
Top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until bubbly.
Makes a lot and can be easily halved.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together well and bake in 3 greased and floured cake pans at 350° until done.

title: old-fashioned baking powder biscuits
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup; level off.
In large bowl, combine flour, baking powder and salt. Using fork or pastry blender, cut shortening into flour until consistency of coarse meal.
Add milk; stir with fork until mixture leaves sides of bowl and forms a soft, moist dough.

title: oatmeal molasses cookies
directions: Sift together the 8 cups flour, salt and soda.
Mix oatmeal, sugar and ginger.

Stir in melted shortening, molasses, eggs, water, sifted dry ingredients, nuts and raisins. Work dough by hand until well mixed. Add 1/2 cup flour if needed. Roll portions of dough to 1/4-inch thickness.
Cut with 3 1/2-inch cutter. Place on lightly greased sheets. Brush with water and sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: tofu casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except buttered crumbs. Sprinkle crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and onion; drain.
Salt and pepper to taste. Put in a baking dish.
Mix remaining ingredients and add to broccoli.
Top with Pepperidge Farm cornbread stuffing mix.
Dot with butter.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: tater appetizers
directions: Take each Tater Tot and wrap with 1/2 slice bacon and 1/2 slice cheese.
Pierce with toothpick.
Broil.

title: jeff davis pie
directions: Cream together butter and sugar; add flour, salt and vanilla. Beat well.
Add eggs; stir in milk.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes. Reduce heat to 350° and bake for 30 minutes until firm.

title: cheese-dried beef ball
directions: Mix together.
Shape in ball and roll in parsley flakes.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Combine and roll into balls.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: xnipec salsa (dog breath)
directions: Soak diced onion in lime juice for at least 30 minutes.
Add chilies and tomato and mix; salt to taste and add a little water if desired.
Yields 1 1/2 extremely hot cups.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Lightly grease pie plate, 10 x 1 1/2-inches.
Cook and stir ground beef and onions in skillet until brown; drain.
Stir in salt and pepper.
Spread on plate.
Beat milk, baking mix and eggs until smooth, 1 minute with hand beater. Pour into plate.
Bake 35 minutes.
Top with tomatoes.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake until knife inserted in center comes out clean, 5 to 8 minutes longer.
Cool 5 minutes.

title: tater-topped casserole
directions: In a skillet, cook onion, celery and ground beef over medium heat until the meat is no longer pink and the vegetables are tender.
Drain.
