Stir in salt and pepper.
Spoon mixture into a greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Spread soup over meat.
Top with Tater Tots.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes or until bubbly. Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 5 minutes longer or until cheese is melted.

title: italian creme cake
directions: Cream oleomargarine and Crisco; add sugar and beat until mixture is smooth.
Add egg yolks and beat well.
Combine flour and soda and add to cream mixture.
Alternate with buttermilk. Stir in vanilla; add coconut and nuts and fold in egg whites. Pour batter into 3 greased and floured 8-inch cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool and use cream cheese frosting.

title: zucchini patties
directions: Mix all ingredients together and drop by spoonfuls onto a greased griddle or frypan.
Fry until golden brown.

title: rotel dip(club member: clint hudson)
directions: Brown meat and put the can of Ro-Tel tomatoes in a crock-pot. Melt cheese; pour meat and cheese into crock-pot and stir. Keep crock-pot on low. Serve with corn chips.

title: grandma's lemon cream pie
directions: In a saucepan, mix sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Add milk gradually and stir until smooth.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until smooth and thick, about 10 minutes.
Stir a small amount of hot mixture into beaten egg yolks, then gradually add yolks to remaining hot mixture.
Continue cooking, stirring constantly, about 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add butter, lemon peel and juice and blend thoroughly.
Pour hot filling into pie shell.
If made with a baked pie shell, top with meringue.
If a graham cracker crust is used, serve with whipped cream.

title: cowboy beans
directions: Brown meat and onion; drain.
Add barbecue sauce; mix well. Drain beans and add; stir well.
Add catsup for the liquid, taste and color.
Cook to the consistency desired.

title: recipe for a happy church family
directions: Mix thoroughly with faith.
Bake in moderate oven of tolerance.
Cool.
Cut in equal portions; garnish with smiles. Serve in everyday life God, community and country.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix first 2 ingredients together in saucepan.
Heat over low heat until it comes to a boil.
Boil for 2 minutes.
Beat Marshmallow Cream into mixture.
Add peanut butter and blend well. Spread mixture into shallow pan and refrigerate, cut into bars.

title: bachelor's banquet
directions: Carefully remove cardboard container from T.V. dinner.
Set oven temperature as indicated on box.
Remove foil over wrap, if necessary.
Place contents in oven.
Gently cook meat, potato and veggies until overly dry.
Wash down with a cool sip of white wine. Continue to sip wine until meal tastes good.
Then call Domino's pizza for the main coarse.
And then pray for a woman in your life!

title: boston brown bread
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients; let stand 3 hours.
Add rest of ingredients and mix well.
Pour into 4 (1 pound) coffee cans, well greased.
Fill about 1/2 full.
(I use small loaf pans.)
Bake 1 hour at 350° or until done when tested.

title: cabbage roll casserole
directions: Fry sausage and drain.
In a medium casserole dish, place cabbage, onion, rice, soup, water and sauerkraut.
Mix well.
Add sausage.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes without lid.
Reduce oven to 350° for 1 hour.
Let stand 10 minutes and serve.

title: apple walnut ring cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Mix sifted flour, baking soda, salt, cinnamon and mace.
Gradually stir two mixtures together. Stir in vanilla, apples and nuts.
Batter will be stiff.
Spoon into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours or until done.
Cool 10 minutes before removing from pan.

title: classic coke cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter and flour a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan. Combine flour and sugar.
Combine butter, cocoa and Coke.
Add to flour and sugar mixture, stirring well.
Add buttermilk, eggs, soda and vanilla.
Fold in marshmallows.
Pour into prepared pan. Bake 30 to 35 minutes.
Frost while warm.

title: key lime pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large mixer bowl, beat egg yolks with sweetened condensed milk.
Stir in ReaLime brand and food coloring, if desired.
Pour into prepared pastry shell; bake 12 minutes.
Cool.
Chill.
Top with whipped cream.
Garnish as desired.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: wacky cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients (first 6) into bowl. Add rest of ingredients. Mix well. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: bohemian cabbage
directions: Mix all ingredients together except sour cream in skillet. Cover tightly.
Cook 5 minutes or until cabbage is crisp-tender. Stir in sour cream; heat through.
Makes 6 servings.

title: sweet and sour surprise
directions: Combine cornstarch, sugar, chicken bouillon cube, water, vinegar, pineapple juice, soy sauce and butter.
Cook and stir until mixture boils; cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Group cooked meatballs, shrimp and chicken livers in the sauce.
Heat through. Serve hot!!
Makes 1 1/2 cups sauce.

title: rigatoni and tomatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients except rigatoni and cheese.
Cover and refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Prepare rigatoni as directed on package; drain and immediately toss with tomato mixture.
Serve immediately or chill.
Sprinkle with cheese before serving.

title: pumpkin squares
directions: Mix all ingredients together until smooth.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes.
Frost with Pillsbury vanilla frosting (ready to spread) and 3 ounces cream cheese.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Stir cranberries until spreadable.
Put 1 layer jellied cranberries, l layer Cool Whip and 1 layer crumbled crackers. Alternate until cranberries and Cool Whip are gone.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Mix zucchini, onion and cheese.
Mix Bisquick, eggs and oil together.
Pour in 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes (uncovered).

title: tostito pie
directions: In a skillet, brown the ground beef and drain.
Add 1 1/2 cups tomato sauce and the taco seasoning.
Stir well.
Line the bottom of an 11 x 8 x 2-inch pan with 2 cups corn chips that have been crushed.
Set remaining chips aside.
Spoon meat mixture over the corn chips.
Combine the remaining tomato sauce and refried beans and spread over the meat mixture.
Bake in 375° oven for 25 minutes.
Take out of oven and sprinkle remaining corn chips and Cheddar cheese and bake an additional 5 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve sugar in Jell-O and water.
Add celery, nuts, orange, cranberries and pineapple.
Stir well and chill until set.

title: tuna salad
directions: Combine tuna, carrots, zucchini, apple and onions.
Mix in mayo, mustard and poppy seeds and toss lightly.
Cut pita bread in half to form pocket; fill with tuna mixture and serve.

title: strawberry sparkle cake
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water.
Add frozen block of strawberries, stirring to break up and mix berries.
Place cake, widest side down, on a serving plate.
Cut a 1-inch layer from the top and set aside.
Cut around cake 1 inch from outer edge to 1 inch from bottom, then cut around cake 1 inch from inner edge to 1 inch from bottom.
Gently remove the section of cake between the cuts, tearing it into small pieces.
Fold pieces into strawberry mixture and pour it into cake shell.
Replace the cake top.

title: broccoli and cheese casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and onion together; drain.
Add cooked rice and other ingredients.
Pour into greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: beef burgundy
directions: Roll the steak in flour and brown in the margarine.
Place meat in a large roaster and cover with the water, 1 cup Burgundy, stew mix, gravy mix, salt, pepper and dash of Worcestershire sauce.
Bake at 350° until almost tender.
Add the mushrooms, onions, 1 cup Burgundy and more water, if needed.
Bake until tender.
Good served over rice.

title: apple cake
directions: Cream the butter with sugar.
Add egg, apples and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients, sifted together.
A few raisins or nuts are optional.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: baked corn
directions: Mix together.
Put into buttered 1 1/2-quart serving dish. Bake for 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: angels on horseback
directions: Slice raw hot dogs down the middle.
Place shredded Cheddar cheese inside.
Wrap with raw bacon strips, held with toothpicks. Cook under broiler until done.

title: old miss coffee cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to directions.
Bake 10 minutes. Remove.
Sprinkle nuts, warm syrup, cinnamon and margarine over cake.
Return to oven.
Bake 15 minutes.
Drizzle with frosting when done.

title: scampi butter
directions: Mix all ingredients into softened butter.
Do not heat butter to blend in ingredients.
Refrigerate until ready to use.
Scampi butter not used in cheese sauce can be used to prepare shrimp, scallops, sirloin steak or chicken.

title: lola phillips' lemon cake
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Let cool.
Beat eggs lightly in a large bowl.
Add vegetable oil and salt.
Add dissolved jello. Mix in lemon cake mix and beat for 2 minutes.
Bake in an oiled and floured 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
When done, pierce cake all over every 2-inches while still hot.
Mix powdered sugar and lemon juice.
Pour over hot cake.
This will soak in and make a glaze when cold; do not frost.
May be topped with ice cream or whipped cream.
Cake is better if baked 2 days ahead of serving.

title: easy ghost cookies
directions: Melt almond bark in microwave on low heat; stirring constantly.
Dip each cookie in melted almond bark and place on wax paper.
Place two chocolate chips on warm candy coated cookie for eyes.
Cool and serve!

title: sherry's chicken casserole
directions: Boil
chicken
until
done.
Melt
butter and pour over stuffing mix.
Stir until well mixed.
Pour 3/4 of mix into 13 x 9-inch casserole dish.
Pull chicken into bite-sized pieces and cover
in dish.
Cover with stuffing mixture.

title: sister lila cobourn's vinegar pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add dry ingredients, egg, vinegar and water.
Cook in top of double boiler until thickened, stirring constantly.

title: apple pecan cake
directions: Mixing by hand, combine sugar and eggs.
Add flour to mixture; add vanilla.
Mix well.
Add pecans and apples.
Batter will be thick.
Pour into a 13 x 9-inch ungreased pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until top of cake is golden brown.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Drain liquid as best as possible from pineapple.
Put pineapple in large bowl.
Add box of powdered lime Jell-O.
Mix well.
Add tub of Cool Whip.
Mix well.
Add cottage cheese. Refrigerate approximately 1 hour and serve chilled.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine cornmeal, sugar, garlic powder and onion.
Combine milk and eggs. Add to mixture.
Layer mixture, sausage, corn and cheese.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.

title: lasagne
directions: Cook and stir ground beef, ground pork, onion and garlic in large saucepan or Dutch oven until meat is brown and onion is tender.
Drain off all fat.
Add tomatoes and break up with fork. Stir in tomato sauce, 2 tablespoons parsley flakes, the sugar, 1 teaspoon salt and the basil.
Heat to boiling, stirring occasionally.
Reduce heat; simmer, uncovered, 1 hour or until mixture is consistency of spaghetti sauce.
Heat oven to 350°. Mix cottage cheese, 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese, 1 tablespoon parsley flakes, 1 1/2 teaspoons salt and the oregano.
Reserve 1/2 cup meat sauce for thin top layer.

In ungreased baking pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inches, layer 1/4 each of the noodles, remaining meat sauce, the Mozzarella cheese and cottage cheese mixture; repeat 3 times. Spread reserved meat sauce over top; sprinkle with 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese.
(If desired, lasagne can be covered and refrigerated several hours at this point.)
Bake uncovered 45 minutes.
(Allow an additional 10 to 15 minutes if lasagne has been refrigerated.)
For easier cutting, let stand 15 minutes after removing from oven.

title: chicken in apple mustard sauce
directions: Flatten chicken breasts and brown in margarine in skillet. Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and cook 10 to 12 minutes or until chicken is tender.
Makes 4 servings with 250 calories per serving.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Mix pretzels, butter and 3 tablespoons sugar; press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 10 minutes at 350°; cool.

title: lemon sauce
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch with 1/4 cup water.
Then add the rest of the water and remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil and boil until it thickens.

title: tuna linguini
directions: Cook linguini.
Drain.
Mix 1 can mushroom soup, 1 can chicken soup, 3/4 cup milk and 2 tablespoons wine in an ungreased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Stir in half of linguini, 1 can mushrooms and 1 can tuna.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup of cheese.
Repeat with remaining ingredients in a second pan.
(Cook 1 dish uncovered in a 375° oven until hot and bubbly, about 30 minutes.)
Wrap second dish and freeze.
About 1 1/2 hours before serving, remove pan from freezer and unwrap.
Cook, uncovered, at 425° for 80 to 90 minutes.

title: pastry(home ec. dept.)
directions: Sift flour.
Measure, add salt and cut into Crisco with a pastry blender.
Add lemon juice to slightly beaten egg.
Then add water to liquid and mix well.
Sprinkle lightly on dough.
Mix well.
Roll out to form pie shell.

title: baskin-robbins pie
directions: Mix flour, nuts and margarine in pie plate and press to bottom.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl except carrots.
Add carrots last.
Grease and flour three 8-inch layer pans.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Depending on individual oven, you may bake up to 45 minutes.

title: linda's broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix together eggs, cottage cheese, salt, onion, margarine and broccoli.
Add cornbread mix last.
Put in well-greased baking dish.
Bake at 400° for 20-30 minutes, until brown.
Serve hot.

title: vegetable relish
directions: Grind vegetables using coarse blade.
Sprinkle with salt; let stand overnight.
Rinse and drain.
Combine remaining ingredients. Pour over vegetables.
Heat to boiling.
Simmer 3 minutes.
Seal in hot sterilized jars.
Makes 8 pints.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Beat margarine and sugar until creamy. Add eggs, milk and vanilla.
Beat together.
Add flour, baking soda and salt and mix well.
Stir in oats, chocolate chips, coconut and nuts.
Mix well.
Drop by tablespoonful onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 9 to 10 minutes.
Cool 1 minute and remove to wire racks.
Cool.
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: peanut soup
directions: Heat chicken broth to boiling.
Add peanut butter, stirring until smooth.
Add salts and sugar.
Stir in cream or evaporated milk.
Heat; do not boil.
Top with chopped peanuts.
Serves 6.

title: cranberry pie
directions: Butter pan; add sliced cranberries.
Mix 1/2 cup sugar and nuts; add to pie.
Beat eggs until light; add 1 cup sugar and flour.
Cream oleo and shortening; add all ingredients.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Top with whipped cream.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Slice beef across the grain into very thin trips.
In skillet, over high heat, in 1 tablespoon hot margarine, cook 1/2 the beef and onion until meat is no longer pink and onion is tender; set aside.
Repeat with remaining margarine, beef and onion.
Return meat mixture to skillet.
Stir in soup and paprika.
Heat through. Stir in sour cream.
Serve over hot cooked noodles.
Makes 6 servings.

title: applesauce pie
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients in a Dutch oven over medium heat, stirring often, 35 minutes or until thickened.
Remove from heat and discard lemon. add butter and vanilla, cool.
Fit one piecrust into a 9 inch pie plate.
Pour applesauce mixture into crust.
Roll remaining piecrust to press out fold lines and cut into 1/2 inch strips.
Arrange strips into a lattice design over filling, fold edges under and crimp.
Bake at 425 degrees for 30-35 minutes.

title: bacon corn bread muffins
directions: Sift flour with baking powder and salt.
Add corn meal; combine egg, milk and bacon to dry ingredients.
Fill muffin tins (greased) 2/3 full.
Bake in hot oven at 450° for 15 minutes.

title: emerald isle salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 cup of boiling water; dissolve marshmallows in pineapple juice.
Add to jello.
Chill until it starts to jell.
Then add pineapple, cottage cheese, whipping cream (whipped) and nuts.
Chill until firm, at least overnight.

title: christmas fruit cake
directions: Mix in order given.
Grease and flour pans.
(Will make 2 cakes in loaf pans or 3 in coffee cans.)
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 1 hour.

title: quick caramel coffee cake
directions: Grease the bottom of Bundt pan with Crisco.
Put 1/2 of the nuts in the bottom of the pan.
Drop in all of the frozen balls of dough, spreading around in the pan.
Sprinkle dry pudding mix over dough balls; top with remaining nuts.
In a bowl, cut the sugar and butter together; sprinkle these crumbs over top.
Set in cold oven at night.
(Prepare at bedtime if you want to use in morning.)
In the morning, bake at 350° for about 1/2 hour or until done.
Let stand in Bundt pan about 5 minutes, then invert pan on serving plate.
Best served warm.

title: apricot salad
directions: Heat small can of crushed pineapple (do not drain) with apricot nectar.
Pour over jello and stir thoroughly.
Chill until firm, then fold in 1 small package Dream Whip and cottage cheese.

title: texas caviar
directions: Drain
the
peas.
In bowl, add the next 4 ingredients. Place in covered bowl and refrigerate until ready to serve (1 to 2 hours).

title: beef 'n cheese foldover
directions: Brown meat and onion; drain.
Stir in barbecue sauce; set aside.
Heat oven to 375°.
Unroll dinner roll dough into 4 long rectangles on ungreased cookie sheet.
Overlap long sides.
Press perforations and seal.
Pat to form 15 x 13-inch rectangle.
Spread meat mixture lengthwise in a 4-inch wide strip down center of dough to within 1 inch of ends.
Top meat with cheese slices.
Fold shorter ends of dough 1 inch over filling.
Bring long sides of dough rectangle over filling, overlapping edges.
Pinch edges to seal.
Sprinkle with sesame seed.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes, or until golden brown.

title: chili like wendy's
directions: Brown beef in heavy pot; drain off fat. Crumble into small pieces. In a large pot, combine beans, tomato sauce, celery, tomatoes, onions, pepper, spices, seasonings and water. Add cooked beef. Bring to a simmer over low heat. Cook, stirring every 20 to 30 minutes for 2 to 3 hours. Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese when serving.

title: cheese and sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage; drain.
Add vegetables, continue cooking 5 minutes; drain.
Set aside to cool 10 minutes.
Stir together sausage mixture, cheese and bread cubes.
Place in a greased 8 1/2 x 12-inch baking dish.
Beat milk and eggs.
Pour over sausage mixture.
Cover and refrigerate for several hours.

title: chicken angel pasta
directions: Boil pasta nest until done. Drain.
Meanwhile brown chicken slightly in olive oil.
Remove, add onion, celery, pepper and chives.
Saute.
Place pasta in casserole.
Top with cheese then onion mixture, then chicken.
Pour milk over.
Spoon soup over each piece of chicken.
Bake 375° 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine sweet potatoes, sugar, butter, eggs, vanilla and milk; mix well.
Spoon into a 2-quart casserole dish.
Cover with topping.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix ingredients together. Bake at 400° for 40 minutes.

title: easter eggs
directions: Boil and mash potato.
Add confectioners sugar, vanilla and coconut or peanut butter.
Refrigerate 2 to 3 hours.
Shape into eggs and refrigerate overnight.
Cover with coating chocolate.

title: ambrosia
directions: Drain juice from fruit cocktail, mandarin oranges and cherries.
Mix all fruit into large bowl.
Mix in marshmallows and sour cream.
Put coconut in last.
Stir and cover.
Refrigerate for 2 to 3 hours.

title: craban sauce
directions: Cook cranberries following
instructions on the bag and either separate half or cook half, reducing sugar and water by half.
As cranberries are simmering, add the tangerine peel to the
water. Squeeze
some of the juice from the tangerine and also
add
to the water.
When cranberries are done, let cool and
remove tangerine
peel.
Add mashed banana and mix thoroughly.
Chill.

title: jalapeno casserole
directions: Mix soups and boned chicken in saucepan; heat. Pour over Doritos chips in large 11 x 13-inch casserole dish. Top with grated cheese and sliced jalapenos. Heat in 350° oven until cheese melts. Serve and enjoy.

title: black and white cheesecake brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt 1 1/2 cups of chocolate chips in microwave for 1 1/2 minutes on High.
In large bowl, combine sugar and butter; beat until creamy.
Add eggs, vanilla and salt, then add melted chocolate and flour; mix well.
Spread into foil lined 9-inch square pan.

title: shredded carrot salad
directions: Peel and shred, or grate, carrots.
Add marshmallows, pineapple, raisins and coconut.
Mix lightly.
Combine carrot mixture with mayonnaise; carefully fold in whipped cream. Refrigerate at least one hour.
This freezes well!

title: strawberry yogurt whip
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add cold water.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Add yogurt and beat with rotary beater until mixture is light and fluffy.
Pour into punch cups or individual dishes.
Chill about 2 hours.
Makes 8 servings.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix Veg-All, corn, celery, onions and mayonnaise. Put in casserole dish. Add cheese. Top with Ritz crackers and margarine. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mock sukiyaki
directions: Brown the steak; add beef broth, vegetables and soy sauce. Cover; simmer 10 minutes or until tender.
Stir often.
Combine 1/4 cup water and cornstarch.
Stir into mixture.
Simmer until thickened.
Serve over rice.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Drain pineapple.
Heat pineapple juice and dissolve jello in warm pineapple juice.
Cool slightly.
Cream the cheese.
If necessary, add small amount of cream.
Whip the cream.
Add slightly cooled jello to cream cheese.
Add whipped cream.
Add other ingredients.
Chill to set.

title: sourdough bread and starter
directions: Let stand out of refrigerator 8 to 12 hours.
(This doesn't rise, only bubbles.)
Take out 1 cup to use in making bread. Return remaining to refrigerator.
Keep in refrigerator 3 to 5 days.
(I keep mine in refrigerator from one week to the next week.)
Take out and feed again.
If not used to make bread, throw away 1 cup or give to someone as a starter.
Must feed every 3 to 5 days.

title: old-time sugar cream pie
directions: Combine sugars, salt and flour.
Add cream and vanilla, mixing until smooth.
Pour into pastry shell.
Sprinkle with nutmeg. Bake in very hot oven (450°) for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake for 30 to 35 minutes.
Use fruit for garnish, preferably strawberries.

title: candy coated carrots
directions: Boil carrots until just tender.
Drain and set aside.
In pan, combine butter and brown sugar; mix well over low heat.
Stir until bubbly.
Add Tabasco and salt.
Remove from heat.
Add lemon juice and carrots.
Stir gently to coat well.
Serve warm or cold.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: In a large bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking powder and salt. Stir in blueberries.
Add milk, egg whites and Ultra Promise. Mix just until dry ingredients are moistened.
The batter will be lumpy.
Do not overbeat.
Spoon batter into 12 (2 1/2-inch) muffin cups (sprayed with Pam).
Bake at 400°
for 25 minutes or until tops spring back when lightly touched.
Serve warm.

title: dump cake(black forest)
directions: Grease and flour 9 x 13 x 2-inch cake pan.
Add marshmallows over bottom of pan.
Mix Duncan Hines cake mix. Pour over marshmallows.
Spoon can of cherry pie filling over chocolate cake mix.
Sprinkle nuts over the top.
Cook for 45 to 60 minutes in 350° oven.

title: italian beef
directions: Cook in crock pot until meat falls apart.
Take the meat out, place on a plate and take two forks and shred the meat then put back in juice.
Serve on Bun with chips pickles or over rice with vegetables.

title: zucchini goulash
directions: Cook macaroni as directed on package, adding the cubes of zucchini and peeled tomato quarters.
Drain.
Brown ground beef and onion.
Drain off excess fat.
Add cooked macaroni, zucchini and tomatoes.
Add pepper, brown sugar, margarine, milk, packet of cheese and seasoning mix to taste.
Stir to combine all ingredients.
Simmer 10 to 15 minutes, uncovered.

title: apple crisp
directions: Combine sugar, eggs, oil, salt and cinnamon.
Pour over apples and let stand 20 minutes.
Mix flour, soda and nuts.
Add mixture to apples.
Bake 45 minutes in 350° oven in 10 x 13-inch pan or 9 x 13-inch pan for 50 minutes.

title: chocolate syrup
directions: Boil for 4 minutes.
Take off heat.
Excellent for chocolate milk, hot chocolate and ice cream topping.

title: bojangles' biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Cut in Crisco; mix in buttermilk and work until smooth.
Roll out thick and cut.
Dip in melted butter. Bake at 400° until brown.
Yields about 10 big biscuits.
Very good!

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients, starting with softened oleo.
Mix with wooden spoon.
Chill dough 1 hour or overnight.
Shape dough into balls size of walnuts.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten with bottom of glass dipped in sugar.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Makes about 10 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Thaw hash browns for 30 minutes.
Add all ingredients; mix well.
Add additional shredded cheese on top, if desired.
Bake at 350° for one hour.

title: butter mints
directions: Cream together margarine, milk and butter flavoring until fluffy and stir in sugar replacement.
Knead or work with hands until smooth.
Roll in small balls and press each ball into mold. Unmold on wax paper.
Yield:
45 pieces; calories per 3 pieces, 56.

title: pistachio biscotti(makes about 40 biscotti)
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease 2 baking sheets.
In small bowl, combine flour, baking powder and pistachios.
With electric mixer, beat egg and egg whites until frothy.
Gradually beat in sugar and vanilla until very thick and pale yellow (about 5 minutes).
Fold flour mixture into egg batter until well combined.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Cook carrots.
Mix in all ingredients.
Top with crumbs.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine all casserole ingredients in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Crumble topping over the top of the potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
I always double the topping due to everybody wants the topping with the sweet potatoes.
If you do this, just double the recipe for the topping.
I usually cut the butter to 3/4 cup instead of 1 cup.

title: yellow gold carrots
directions: Cook carrots until tender but not soft.
Combine with remaining chopped ingredients and marinate at least 24 hours before serving.
Serve hot or cold.

title: tangy mustard cauliflower(microwave)
directions: Place cauliflower and water into 1 1/2-quart glass casserole. Cover with glass lid.
Microwave 9 minutes on High.
Drain.

title: cheese carrot casserole
directions: Scrape and slice carrots.
Cook until tender.
Drain well; melt cheese and butter together with carrots. Put all together in a buttered baking dish.
Sprinkle with buttered Ritz cracker crumbs on top.
Bake in 375° oven until bubbly.

title: desserts
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Make pie crust or unthaw 2 pie crusts. Beat eggs slightly, then add remaining ingredients.
Pour into pastry lined pie pan.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes, then reduce heat to 350° for 45 minutes.

title: scallop potatoes
directions: Slice potatoes in 11 x 14-inch baking dish.
Slice onion on top.
Bring butter, flour and milk to a boil and gradually add cheese to mixture.
Add salt.
Add this mixture over potatoes and onion.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour or until potatoes are done.

title: diabetic apple pie
directions: In sauce pan blend apple juice concentrate and cornstarch. Cook and stir until the mixture boils, is clear and thickens. Stir in butter and spices.
Pour thickened mixture over apples. Put filling in unbaked pie shell and top with pie crust.
Bake in a preheated oven at 425° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Turn heat down to 350° and bake for 30 to 45 minutes more or until crust is brown.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix in dish the pudding, fruit cocktail, crushed pineapple and miniature marshmallows.
Stir in Dream Whip.
Use a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Refrigerate.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Cook spaghetti.
Combine first 7 ingredients in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Top with cheese; then cornflakes.
Cook at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: frozen lemon mousse
directions: Cook egg yolks, sugar, grated lemon rind and lemon juice for three minutes, stirring constantly. Fold in evaporated milk that has been chilled and whipped, and the stiffly beaten egg whites. Place 1/4 inch of graham cracker crumbs in bottom of 8 inch square dish. Pour in mousse. Place another 1/4 inch layer of crumbs on top. Cover with plastic wrap and place in freezer, preferably overnight. Do not remove until ready to serve.

title: sausage noodle bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown sausage and onion over medium heat and drain.
Mix soup, cheese, evaporated milk, salt, oregano and pepper in 3-quart bowl.
Stir in meat mixture and 3 cups cooked noodles.
Pour into a greased 2-quart baking dish.
Top mixture with bread crumbs and pour melted margarine over it.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until bubbly hot.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: frozen yogurt pie
directions: Grind graham crackers into fine crumbs.
Add sugar and melted margarine.
Press into pie plate and chill 1 hour or bake at 375° for 6 to 10 minutes and then cool thoroughly.
Fold whipped topping and yogurt together and spoon into crust.
Chill and serve.

title: barbecued spareribs
directions: You will need 2 (10-inch) skillets and a baking pan.

title: oat pancakes
directions: Combine oats, flour, sugar, baking powder and salt in mixing bowl.
Make a well in center.
Combine eggs, milk, oil and lemon juice.
Pour into well and stir just until moistened.
Pour batter by 1/4 cupfuls onto a lightly greased hot griddle.
Turn when bubbles form on top of pancakes.
Cook until second side is golden brown.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix 1/2 cup oleo, melted with graham cracker crumbs.
Put into pan (9 x 13-inch).
Beat egg, remaining oleo and powdered sugar for 5 minutes.
Spread over crust.
Cover with sliced bananas; spread crushed pineapple on that.
Cover with topping.
Put nuts and cherries on top.
Refrigerate overnight or for 6 hours.

title: german chocolate brownies
directions: Combine cake mix, 1/3 cup milk and melted butter.
Press 1/2 of this mixture into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 6 to 8 minutes in 350° oven until bubbly.
In double boiler or microwave, melt caramels and remaining 1/3 cup milk.
Remove cake. Sprinkle chocolate chips over crust, followed by nuts, then melted caramels.
Crumble remaining cake mix over all and return to oven for 15 to 18 minutes.
Cool in refrigerator 30 minutes. Makes 36 bars.

title: ugly duckling cake
directions: Combine the cake mix, fruit cocktail with syrup, 1 cup of the coconut and eggs in a large mixer bowl.
Blend, then beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan. Sprinkle with brown sugar.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes or until cake springs back.

title: creamy corn italiano
directions: In saucepan, cook onions with garlic, oregano and basil in margarine until tender.
Add remaining ingredients.
Heat; stir occasionally.
Makes about 4 1/2 cups.

title: fat-free cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Use an 8-inch square nonstick pan, or a regular pan coated with a nonstick cooking spray.
In a medium bowl, combine cornmeal, flour, baking powder and baking soda.
In a small bowl, beat egg whites until foamy.
Add to flour mixture and blend thoroughly.
Pour into pan and bake for 20 to 25 minutes, or until springy to the touch.

title: canatappi with prosciutto, artichokes and sun-dried tomatoes in
directions: Heat oil and rosemary in skillet.
Add sun-dried tomatoes and artichokes to oil and saute 2 to 3 minutes.
Add Prosciutto. Saute 1 minute.
Add canatappi and toss with other ingredients until well mixed and canatappi is lightly and evenly coated with rosemary oil.
Saute another minute, then portion pasta into 4 bowls.
Garnish with fresh rosemary and freshly ground pepper. Serves 4.

title: salmon jay's way
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix salt, flour and garlic powder well. Press the mixture on all 4 sides of the salmon fillets.
In a heavy ovenproof skillet, add the oil and once it is hot, add the fillets, browning them lightly on both sides.
Place the skillet in the oven and bake for 10 to 15 minutes.
Do not overcook. Serve immediately.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Cream Crisco, brown sugar, milk and vanilla in a large bowl.
Blend until creamy.
Blend in egg. Combine flour, salt and baking soda.
Add to creamed mixture gradually.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: spiced fruit
directions: Drain
fruit
syrup
into
saucepan
and
put the fruit itself into
a
bowl.
Add sugar, vinegar and whole spices to the syrup and boil for 5 minutes.
Pour syrup and spices over the
fruit and
cover	tightly.
Put
in refrigerator and let stand at least 4 hours.

title: no peek casserole
directions: Combine ingredients well in a 2-quart casserole, (I use a roaster).
Cover.
Bake at 300° for 3 hours.
Don't peek until it is done.
Serve over rice or noodles.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: company hash
directions: Make a dark roux using oil and flour.
Saute the onion, celery and garlic until they are clear.
Add the rest of the ingredients including the meat and simmer for 30 minutes.
While the meat mixture is cooking, parboil carrots and potatoes.
Add to meat mixture after 30 minutes.
Cook for 5 minutes and add the additional 1/2 cup Claret wine.
Cook for additional 5 minutes. This may be served over rice, noodles or bread.
Serves 6.

title: magic pumpkin pie
directions: In large size mixing bowl, blend together all ingredients. Turn mixture into pie shell.
Bake in a 375° (moderate) oven until sharp-bladed knife inserted near center comes out clean, 50 to 55 minutes.
Cool.
Refrigerate at least 1 hour.
Serve cold with whipped cream or Cool Whip.

title: winter relish for tacos
directions: Boil until it is thick.
The longer you boil the better it is. Spoon on taco shells after all other ingredients are on.
Yummy.

title: karo sweet 'n sour pork
directions: Drain pineapple, reserve juice.
In large skillet, heat oil over medium high heat.
Add pepper, onion and garlic; stir-fry 2 minutes or until tender-crisp.
Remove.
Stir-fry pork, half at a time, 3 minutes.
Return vegetables to skillet.

title: texas hash
directions: Saute onions and celery in margarine until tender.
Remove from skillet and brown ground meat.
Drain.
Add onions and celery back to meat; stir in tomatoes and Worcestershire sauce.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Sprinkle rice over meat mixture.
Add a little water, if necessary.
Place lid on skillet and simmer until all liquid is gone.
Fluff with fork and serve.
Great with chips and picante sauce.

title: pork barbecue
directions: Cook meat for 3 to 4 hours until done.
Let cool, but not cold, then shred apart and add to cup of broth, sugar, vinegar and onion.
Cook for 1 hour or so.
Then serve on buns.

title: baked fish
directions: Season fish; coat with flour and saute in 4 tablespoons butter 8 to 10 minutes.
Saute mushrooms.
Brown sliced potatoes in 4 tablespoons butter.
Place in a glass baking dish.
Layer fish, then egg slices, mushrooms and potatoes on top.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix all ingredients together and store in an airtight container.
Use 1/3 c. mix to 2/3 c. water when making hot chocolate.
Makes a great gift with the Chocolate Coffee Spoons (below).

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Bake pie shell in 400° oven.
Mix sugar and cornstarch in 1 1/2-quart saucepan.
Stir in water gradually.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and boils; boil and stir 1 minute.
Add the beaten egg yolk to hot mixture; boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat; add margarine, lemon juice and food coloring (optional).
Pour into pie shell.
Spoon meringue over hot pie filling, carefully sealing meringue to edge of crust.
Bake until brown.

title: fruit salad
directions: Layer fruits in large glass bowl in order given.
Spoon orange juice on top.
Cover and chill for 6 to 8 hours.

title: potato soup
directions: Saute onion in butter until soft, but not brown.
Add 5 cups thinly chopped potatoes.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Barely cover with water.
Cook until potatoes fall apart and become thickened. Remove from heat.
Mash with potato masher or fork.
Add vinegar and condensed milk.
Reheat to serving temperature, but do not allow to boil.
Serve with crackers, cornbread or cornsticks. Serves 4 or 5.

title: brown sugar cookies
directions: Cream the first 4 ingredients together. Add remaining ingredients, except flour. Add flour. Roll dough into balls, then in sugar. Bake at 375° for 12 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil noodles and put in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Add soups, chicken and peas in same pan.
Stir to mix ingredients.
Add cheese on top with cracker crumbs.
Cover with foil and cook at 350° in oven for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: never spoil cole slaw
directions: Boil vinegar, oil and salt.
Set aside to cool.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Sprinkle sugar over cabbage.
Pour liquid mixture over cabbage mixture; mix thoroughly.
Refrigerate in Tupperware covered bowl.
Will keep 3 or 4 months.

title: hot chicken salad(serves 10)
directions: Combine all ingredients, except the potato chips.
Place in 13 x 9-inch dish. Top with chips and place in refrigerator overnight. Remove to room temperature for 1 hour before baking at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Can be made ahead and froze.

title: microwave rice krispies treats
directions: Microwave margarine and marshmallows on Full power in large glass mixing bowl for 2 minutes.
Stir to combine.
Microwave on Full power 1 1/2 to 2 minutes longer.
Stir until smooth.
Add cereal.
Stir until well coated.
Press into well buttered 13 x 9-inch pan.
When cool, cut into squares.

title: clara's deluxe carrot cake
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a Bundt pan.
Beat sugar and eggs until thickened and pale.
Stir in oil.
Sift together flour, baking soda, baking powder and cinnamon. Stir into egg mixture. Fold in carrots and nuts.
Spoon batter into pan. Bake in preheated oven for 35 to 40 minutes. Turn onto cake rack to cool. Frost.

title: macaroni and cheese with ham
directions: Layer into buttered 1 1/2 to 2-quart baking dish 3 layers each of macaroni, onion, ham and cheese.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper, ending with top layer cheese, salt and pepper.
Pour milk over all. Sprinkle with paprika. Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes or until brown.

title: zucchini flan
directions: Melt butter in large skillet; add onion.
Cook, stirring until onion is wilted.
Trim and discard ends of zucchini; slice into thin rounds and add to skillet.
Cook briefly; stir.
Spoon mixture into buttered casserole.
Blend cream, egg yolks, egg and nutmeg.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Pour mixture over zucchini.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until custard is lightly set.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: rhubarb cake #2
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in spray-greased 10 x 13-inch pan in which only bottom of pan has been greased.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes.

title: lemon cake
directions: Mix all ingredients with mixer on high speed until smooth. Pour batter into greased and floured angel food cake pan and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Let cool 10 to 15 minutes, then turn out onto plate.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Mix jello with boiling water.
Add frozen berries.
Place in refrigerator until slightly jelled.
Fold in Cool Whip.

title: chicken wellington
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Saute chicken in butter.
Roll out pastry shells between wax paper until fairly thin.

title: pineapple dream cake
directions: Make angel food cake according to directions on box.
Cut cake in three layers.
Put all other ingredients in bowl (except pineapple) and mix at medium speed until thickened.
Do not overbeat.
Spoon in pineapple evenly throughout mixture.
Spread each individual layer generously.

title: "no bake fudge brownies"
directions: Melt over hot (not boiling) water the chocolate morsels.
Stir until smooth.
Add milk, chocolate wafers and 1/2 cup nuts.
Stir until blended.
Press into foil-lined, 8-inch square pan.
Press remaining 1/2 cup nuts into brownies.
Let stand at room temperature until firm.
Cut into 2-inch squares.

title: mississippi mud slide
directions: Combine margarine, flour and nuts.
Mix well.
Press in bottom of 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes (or use graham cracker crust).

title: campfire stew
directions: Cook stewed potatoes; drain half of water.
Add both cans of soup.
Make patties of meat of your choice real small, half the size of normal patties.
Drain grease.
Add to soups and potatoes.

title: cake mix cookies
directions: Mix together the cake mix, oil and water.
Then after it's mixed together, put the chips in.
Drop onto cookie sheet.
Cook 8 to 12 minutes on 350°.

title: oven barbecued chicken
directions: Combine tomato sauce, cranberry sauce, brown sugar, vinegar, Worcestershire sauce and chili powder in medium saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer uncovered for 20 to 30 minutes or until slightly thickened.

title: golden carrot ring
directions: Cook carrots in boiling water, then drain thoroughly.
Mix all other ingredients together and combine with carrots.
Spread butter thoroughly over inside of 9-inch ring mold.
Line with greased wax paper, then pour carrot mixture into mold and bake in 325° oven for 40 minutes.
Turn onto a large plate and fill center with any other vegetable, such as peas, mushrooms, etc.
Serves 12 to 14 easily for a buffet.

title: flip-flop bean salad
directions: Important:
You will need a Tupperware or similar tight fitting bowl that won't leak when turned upside down.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown hamburger, drain and add taco seasoning.
Chop lettuce, tomato and add cheese, chips and seasoned hamburger.
Pour dressing over top and stir together.

title: yum-yum cake
directions: Mix cake as directed and bake in a rectangular pan.
Mix instant pudding as directed and beat together with cream cheese. Layer cream cheese/pudding mixture on top of cake.
Follow with a drained can of crushed pineapple, then Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with crushed nuts and coconut.
Decorate with cherries and chill for 1 hour before serving.
Yum-yum!

title: russian barbecue chicken
directions: Simmer onion soup mix, Russian dressing and water for 10 minutes.

title: microwave chili cheese dip
directions: Melt in microwave for 5 minutes, stirring and turning once. Serve with nacho chips.

title: fruit jumbles
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Cream shortening and brown sugar until light; stir in egg yolk, vanilla and syrup from maraschino cherries. Blend or sift together flour and salt; add to creamed mixture and mix well. Add dates, raisins, coconut, quartered maraschino cherries, candied pineapple and walnuts. Combine thoroughly. Drop from a teaspoon onto greased baking sheets. Bake in preheated 375° oven for about 10 minutes. Makes 6 dozen cookies.

title: creamy chef's dressing(low-fat)
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Blend or process until smooth. Cover and refrigerate.

title: buttermilk fudge
directions: Mix
soda with buttermilk;
stir well.
Add to sugar in a large
boiler.
Stir in corn syrup; add butter.
Cook until medium ball
is formed (240°).
Remove from heat.
Beat well. Add nuts. Pour out on buttered surface or drop by spoonfuls.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream margarine.
Add sugar gradually and cream.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add vanilla and cream.
Add flour, salt and baking powder.
Chill dough overnight or a minimum of 4 hours.
Roll on floured board and shape with cookie cutters.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain all fruit.
Beat egg yolks; add other ingredients (sugar, pineapple juice and vinegar).
Mix well and cook until thick,
stirring
constantly.
Let
cool.	When
cooled,
add fruit, marshmallows and 1 cup Cool Whip.
Let set overnight in refrigerator.
This is real good.

title: clete's fettuccine alfredo
directions: Heat butter in 10-inch skillet over medium-high heat.
Saute onion in butter. Stir in whipping cream; heat to boiling. Stir in 2 tablespoons cheese, 1 teaspoon nutmeg, 1/2 teaspoon salt and 1/2 teaspoon pepper; reduce heat.
Simmer, uncovered, for 30 minutes, stirring frequently.

Heat water and 1 tablespoon salt to boiling in large kettle; add fettuccine noodles. Boil, uncovered, until tender, but firm. Drain fettuccine. Mix fettuccine and sauce; top with 2 tablespoons cheese and 1 teaspoon nutmeg.
Serve with pepper. Makes 4 servings.

title: herbed tomatoes
directions: Peel tomatoes, cut crosswise in half.
Place in deep bowl, sprinkling each layer with seasonings and herbs.
Combine oil and vinegar and pour over tomatoes.
Cover, chill an hour or more, basting often.
Drain.
Yields 12 servings.

title: date loaf
directions: Crumble all but 4 graham crackers very fine; chop nuts fine. Chop pitted dates and cut marshmallows into small pieces.
Combine all ingredients together and form into a long roll; crumble remaining 4 crackers and roll in those.
Wrap in waxed paper and place in refrigerator at least 1 hour.
Slice and serve with whipped cream.

title: canned beets
directions: Cook and peel beets (cook approximately 60 minutes) until knife-tender, but don't check very often because they will bleed and be dry.
Dip into cold water and peel.
Slice and put into jars.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Rinse a large bowl with hot water, then pour warm water into bowl.
Sprinkle yeast over warm water.
Add sugar and salt and stir until completely dissolved.
Add egg, butter and 3 cups of flour, mixing with a wooden spoon or mixer at medium speed.
Beat very hard for 2 minutes or until smooth.
Gradually add 1 cup of flour, beating hard after addition.
Using hands, work remaining 2 cups of flour into dough until dough is smooth and elastic.
After working in all flour, return dough to large bowl.
Brush top of dough with 1 teaspoon melted butter.
Cover and let stand until it doubles in size.
If using immediately, punch dough down and shape into medium size balls.
Let rise again before baking.
If not using immediately, punch dough down and refrigerate.

title: cole slaw
directions: Grate cabbage.
Add other ingredients; mix well.
This makes a large amount and is ideal for cookouts.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugar in mixing bowl.
Add eggs, mixing well after each addition.
Beat until fluffy.
Combine cocoa, flour, baking powder and salt.
Add vanilla to milk. Add milk mixture alternately with flour mixture to butter mixture. Pour batter into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan. Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 25 minutes.

title: green tomato fish pickles
directions: Sprinkle salt over the tomatoes, pepper, onions and hot pepper.
Let stand overnight.
Drain off liquid.
Squeeze out all the liquid so it won't be too salty.
Mix sugar, mustard seed and vinegar.
Heat until sugar dissolves.
Then add vegetable mixture. Heat until vegetables change color.
Stir and let boil about 5 minutes.
Put in jars and seal.
I put the filled and sealed jars in hot water bath for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: salad
directions: Melt marshmallows in milk in double boiler.
Pour hot mixture over gelatin; stir until dissolved.
Stir in cream cheese.
Add pineapple.
Cool.
Blend in Dream Whip.
Refrigerate until set. (May use any flavor gelatin.)

title: pecan rolls
directions: Use about 1/3 refrigerator dough.
Roll out dough into a 12 x 7-inch oblong pan.
Spread surface with the soft butter.
Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.
Cut into 12 slices.
Place in pan coated with the melted butter, brown sugar and pecans.
Let rise 25 to 35 minutes.
When baked, turn pan upside down onto serving plate for a few minutes.

title: vanity fair coconut custard pie
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar, coconut and milk.
Pour mixture into pastry shell and bake for 1/2 hour.

title: strawberry pizza
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until light brown.

title: pepper steak
directions: Cut steak into strips.
Sprinkle with garlic.
Brown beef in margarine in a large skillet.
Add mushrooms.
Cover with bouillon and cook 30 minutes.
Prepare rice or noodles at this time.
Stir in onion and peppers; cook 5 minutes.
Blend flour, water and soy sauce.
Stir onto meat and vegetables; cook until thickened.
Add tomatoes and stir gently.
Serve immediately over rice or noodles.

title: chicken pie
directions: Cook chicken and debone; remove skin.
Put chicken into a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Pour the celery soup and chicken broth over chicken.
Mix the flour and milk together until lumps dissolve. Pour over chicken.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: lima bean casserole
directions: Cook beans according to package directions.
Set aside.

title: french tomatoes
directions: Put
tomatoes in flat dish and cover with onion, pepper and parsley.
Cover with the dressing.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown hamburger meat with onions and celery.
Add both soups and stir until well mixed.
Place mixture in a large baking dish. Sprinkle Cheddar cheese on top.
Cover the top with Tater Tots. Bake at 400° until Tater Tots are golden brown.

title: minced clam-cheese dip
directions: Allow cream cheese to soften at room temperature.
Drain clams and reserve liquid.
Mix clams, softened cream cheese and other ingredients until creamy.
Add reserved liquid by spoonfuls until desired consistency is obtained.
Serve with crisp crackers or potato chips.

title: glazed acorn squash
directions: Heat oven to 350 degrees.
Cut each squash lengthwise in half; remove seeds and fibers.
Place squash, cut sides up, in ungreased rectangular pan, 13 x 9 x 2. Spoon 1 Tbsp. of maple syrup and 1 Tbsp. whipping cream into each half.
Bake uncovered about 1 hour or until tender.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Drain pineapple well.
Put in casserole dish.
Mix sugar and flour, sprinkle over pineapple.
Grate cheese, put over this. Then crumble crackers real fine, add next.
Melt butter, pour over crackers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sausage twirls
directions: Combine biscuit mix, milk and butter in large bowl until blended and refrigerate dough for 30 minutes.
Divide refrigerated dough into two portions and roll out each portion on wax paper to 1/8 inch thick rectangles, each about 10 x 7 inches.
On each of the rectangles, spread half the uncooked sausage over dough and top sausage with half the peppers and onions if desired.
Roll lengthwise into a log.
Place both logs, wrapped, in freezer until hard enough to cut easily, about one hour.
Preheat oven to 400°. Cut each log into 24 thin slices and place on non-stick baking sheets.
Bake 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Remove twirls from oven.
Reheat to serve.

title: individual cheesecakes
directions: Mix 5 minutes at medium speed with mixer. Fill a cupcake tin with cupcake papers. Put a vanilla wafer cookie in the bottom of cupcake paper. Fill each cupcake paper 3/4 full.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: garlic chicken with pasta
directions: Cook pasta; drain well.
Rinse chicken and cut into 3/4-inch pieces.
Stir together chicken broth, cornstarch, salt and pepper. Preheat wok.
Add onion, garlic, oregano and thyme; stir-fry for 2 minutes.
Add mushrooms and zucchini; stir-fry 2 to 3 minutes. Add oil, then chicken to wok.
Stir-fry 2 to 3 minutes.
Add sauce; fry until thick and bubbly.
Cook for 2 minutes more.
Stir in tomato, veggies and pasta.

title: friendship tea
directions: Mix ingredients and store in tightly covered jar.
To serve, add 1 1/2 to 2 teaspoons to each cup of boiling water you use.

title: something really delicious(spinach bread)
directions: Let frozen bread dough rise according to package directions. Cook spinach; drain and squeeze out excess liquid.
Let cool. Remove sausage from casing and crumble it.
Cook and drain off grease.
Let cool.
Combine cooled spinach, sausage, cheeses and seasonings.
Roll each loaf of bread dough into a rectangle, about 9 x 12-inches.
Do not stretch too thin.
Spread half of spinach mixture lengthwise down the center third of each rectangle.
Dot filling with butter.
Fold over one side of dough, then fold over the other side to overlap.
Pinch to seal tightly; seam should be on top.
Fold ends under and seal tightly to keep filling from running out.
Place each loaf on a cookie sheet and form into a slight crescent shape.
Brush with egg white.
Bake at 375° about 25 minutes or until golden.
Loaves should sound hollow when tapped.
Let loaves stand about 5 to 10 minutes to firm up cheese. Slice with serrated knife.
Loaves freeze well after baking. Reheat in oven.

title: texas impossible pie
directions: Beat eggs until light.
Beat in butter, sugar, flour, baking powder and salt.
Beat well.
Add milk, vanilla and coconut; beat well.
Pour mixture into 2 pie pans.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes. Makes its own crust.

title: mexican hamburger
directions: Brown hamburger meat.
Then in a bowl, mix Ro-Tel, Cheddar cheese, cream of chicken, cream of celery and cream of mushroom. In a long Pyrex dish, place Tostitos in bottom.
Place hamburger meat on top of chips.
Slice Velveeta and place on hamburger, then pour remaining ingredients over.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: raisin bread(low-fat)
directions: In a large bowl, combine all dry ingredients, including raisins.
Mix together egg substitute, nonfat milk and vanilla. Add liquid mixture to dry mixture and mix well.
Pour into a greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Let stand for 5 minutes.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until done.
Serves 20.
Contains .3 grams fat and 112 calories.

title: corn flake kisses
directions: Cook sugar and Karo until sugar melts.
Add peanut butter and mix well.
Pour over corn flakes and mix well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto wax paper.

title: easy spaghetti
directions: Cook onion, pepper and beef in skillet until brown.
Mix in the can of spaghetti until the spaghetti is warm.

title: chippy oatmeal raisin bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat sugar, margarine, eggs and vanilla until creamy.
Gradually add flour and mix well.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Spread into pan.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool completely and cut into bars.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Add sugar; beat.
Add Karo syrup; beat. Add nuts, salt and vanilla.
Put in unbaked pie shell; dot with butter or margarine.
Bake for 50 minutes in slow oven (325°). Pie will seem not done (or loose) after baking, but will settle and firm as it sets.

title: baked corn
directions: Add milk to eggs.
Then add sugar and corn.
Stir in flour paste mixture and melted butter.
Put in well-greased pan (8 x 8-inch).
Flavor with nutmeg (sprinkle on top).
Bake 55 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: tea cakes
directions: Combine oleo and sugar.
Add remaining ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet and bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: sauce
directions: Bring
vinegar, garlic, red and black pepper to a boil; reduce heat
and
add
butter
and lemon juice.
Let simmer 5 minutes; remove from heat and let cool.
For white sauce, add mayonnaise at room temperature, to 1 1/2 pints of Sauce recipe and shake in quart jar.

title: peanut butter squares
directions: Over low burner, cream peanut butter, confectioners sugar and butter.
Remove from heat and fold in Rice Krispies.
In a double boiler, melt 12 ounces chocolate chips with oil.
Spread peanut butter mixture in a cookie sheet and pour melted chocolate on top. Refrigerate 10 minutes; cut in squares and serve.
Store in refrigerator.

title: quiche
directions: Brown ham or bacon with peppers, onion and mushrooms.
Put in pie shell.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Pour into pie shell over meat mixture.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: split pea soup
directions: Soak peas overnight, drain.
Place ham and peas in large pot; bring to boil.
Skim if necessary.
Add other ingredients and simmer for 3 hours.
Remove ham, bones, and bay leaves.
Pour soup into blender and process until smooth.
Dice ham and return to soup.
If too thick, add canned chicken broth.
Serve hot with croutons.

title: peanut butter cups
directions: Combine all ingredients except chocolate chips and press mixture into a buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt chocolate chips and spread over mixture.
Refrigerate until firm, then keep at room temperature for easier cutting.

title: crab meat
directions: Mix crab meat, soup and peas.
Put in casserole.
Sprinkle top with pepper, grated cheese and paprika.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: frank and kidney bean bake
directions: You can leave franks whole or cut in half or quarter.
Mix with the last 5 ingredients.
Bake in oven at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: coca-cola salad
directions: Pour juice off pineapple and cherries; boil juice 5 minutes. Add gelatins and allow to melt.
Chill until slightly thick.
Add softened cream cheese, nuts, pineapple and cherries; stir.
Add cola and stir.
Pour into refrigerator dish.
Chill until set. Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: chiffon cake
directions: In 1 bowl sift flour, sugar, baking powders and salt together. Make well in dry ingredients and add egg yolks (what is left from whites), oil, water and vanilla. Mix well.

title: plunk-it cake
directions: Layer biscuits in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix other ingredients in microwave (enough to melt).
Stir well.
Pour over biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: no bake oatmeal chocolate cookies or candy
directions: Cook sugar, butter and milk. Boil 1 full minute. In bowl, mix remaining ingredients. Stir all together and drop by tablespoon on wax paper.

title: cornbread dressing
directions: Crumble the cornbread into a roaster pan; add onion, celery, eggs and cream of chicken soup.
Also, add sage and salt.
Mix well so all is combined.
Pour enough chicken broth over dressing so that it is moist, but not too soupy.
Cover and bake for about an hour checking to make sure it's not becoming dry.
If so, add more broth.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Preheat oven to 275°.
Brown and drain hamburger and onions. Prepare rice.
Combine all ingredients, but green peppers.
Boil salted water for peppers.
Boil peppers for 5 minutes. Immediately dunk them in cold water.
Place peppers in a 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish.
Pour other mixture over them.
Bake 20 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix all together and bake in a loaf pan, greased, for 50 to 60 minutes at 350°.
Let cool in pan before removing from pan.

title: roasted fries with honey mustard sauce
directions: Cut potatoes lengthwise into four wedges.
Combine 1/4 cup mayonnaise, garlic powder and salt; toss with potatoes, coating evenly.
(Ziploc bag works great and less mess.) Bake potatoes on greased baking sheet at 450° for 15 minutes.
Turn potatoes and bake an additional 15 minutes or until browned and crisp.
Combine remaining 1/2 cup mayonnaise, mustard and honey; stir well.
Serve as dipping sauce for hot potatoes.
This sauce is also good served with fried mushrooms.

title: *nut cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar together. Add eggs, one at a time, and beat well after each addition. Stir in cinnamon, flour and baking powder.

Stir in walnuts. Turn batter into a greased 10 x 14 x 2-inch pan. Bake in a hot 400° oven for 30 to 35 minutes until cake tests done. Remove from oven and while hot, pour cool Syrup over it. Cut into diamond shape.

title: hamburger broccoli casserole
directions: While browning ground beef, cook broccoli.
Mix two soups together and heat.
Put half of browned beef into 8 x 11-inch casserole, covering bottom of dish.
Layer in half of the chopped broccoli, onion rings, cheese and soup.
Repeat layers.
Bake at 350° until mixture bubbles.
Serves four to six.
Tastes great with tossed salad.

title: savory beef patties
directions: In a measuring cup, break up bread, then add enough milk to measure 1 cup (just to moisten bread).
Combine all ingredients and form into small patties.
Roll in flour and fry on both sides. Place patties in small baking dish and add gravy to cover.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: skiers sausage
directions: Mix all together. In baking dish, cover. Bake at 350° for 45 min. Serves 6.

title: surprise grilled cheese sandwiches
directions: Lay out 4 slices of bread and top each with 1 1/2 slices of cheese.
Top cheese with bacon and onion.
Top each with 1 1/2 slices of cheese and bread.
Press down hard on each and prepare as you would a regular grilled cheese sandwich.
If you wish, tomato slices may be added.
Serves 4.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Make brownies according to package directions; allow to cool. Make chocolate mousse.
Crumble brownies.

In trifle bowl or large glass bowl, place 1/2 of the crumbled brownies at the bottom; place 1/2 of the chocolate mousse over the brownies, 1/2 of the Heath bars over the mousse and 1/2 of the Cool Whip over the Heath bars.
Repeat the whole process, starting with the brownies, one more time, saving some of the crumbled Heath bars for the top.
You should have a layered effect.

title: fish chowder
directions: Heat oil and butter in large kettle.
Add onions and celery and cook until soft.
Add remaining ingredients.
Add fish; cover and simmer 1 hour.

title: deluxe sugar cookies
directions: Mix together powdered sugar, granulated sugar, margarine and oil, then add remaining ingredients.
Blend well.
Make into 1-inch balls.
Flatten with bottom of glass dipped in sugar.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet for 10 minutes in 350° oven.
Yields 6 dozen.

title: scalloped corn casserole
directions: Drain
corn.
Save liquid.
Mix liquid with flour.
Pour into corn
in
mixing bowl.
Add sugar, beaten eggs and melted margarine.
Mix
together well.
Put in casserole dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: dirt cake
directions: Mix milk and pudding together and let stand.
Cream the cream cheese, margarine and powdered sugar.
Fold Cool Whip into creamed mixture.
Add pudding to mixture.
Layer half of cookie crumbs in bottom of bowl or pan, then layer pudding on crumb mixture.
Cover with remaining crumbs.
Decorate any way you wish.

title: dirt cake
directions: Beat together the cream cheese, sugar and butter.
In another bowl, combine pudding, milk and Cool Whip until thick.
Mix with first mixture.
Layer bowl, flowerpot or toy wheelbarrow with a layer of crumbs, pudding, etc., ending with crumbs on top.
Top with gummy worms and silk flowers.
Chill and serve with a spade or shovel.

title: jalapeno jelly
directions: Mix green peppers with jalapeno peppers in food processor or blender.
In large pot mix sugar, vinegar and gelatin.
Add the blended peppers.
Bring to a boil, stirring continuously.
Lower heat and simmer for 20 minutes, stirring all the time.
Cool slightly and put in jars.
Place in refrigerator to cool.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: italian chicken
directions: Cook chicken in hot oil until it turns color.
Place chicken in casserole dish or electric skillet.
Cover with spaghetti sauce.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 45 minutes or until chicken is tender.
Serve over hot rice.

title: butternut layer cake
directions: Beat first 4 ingredients for 10 minutes at high speed.
Add flour and milk, alternately beating after each addition.
Bake in three 9-inch pans at 350° until top springs back to touch, about 25 to 30 minutes.

title: lemon bars
directions: Mix flour, powdered sugar and butter till it clings together. Press into 9x13 in. baking pan.
Bake at 350 degrees until lightly browned. mix eggs, sugar, lemon juice and rind, baking powder and flour.
Pour into crust and bake 350 degrees for about 25 minutes. Cool.
Shift on powdered sugar as desired and enjoy.

title: pumpkin bars(sugar-free)
directions: Combine butter, fruit juice, fructose and banana.
Beat egg, pumpkin and vanilla.
Combine dry ingredients and stir into pumpkin mixture.
Add raisins and nuts.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan, well coated.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 325°.

title: creamy spinach bake
directions: Place spinach in saucepan with 1/2 cup boiling water.
Return to a boil, cover.
Lower heat to a simmer.
Cook for 4 minutes, until spinach is broken up.
Drain but do not press all liquid out. Put spinach, onion, salt, pepper, cream cheese, basil and egg in blender or processor until just blended.
Pour into buttered 1-quart casserole.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes or until knife in center comes out clean.
Serve hot.

title: apple turnovers
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Combine flour, sugar, salt and cinnamon.
Cut in Crisco until well mixed.
Sprinkle water in one tablespoon at a time, until it forms a ball.
Roll out into 5-inch squares.
Put 2 tablespoons of filling in middle.
Moisten edges with water.
Fold it into a triangle.
Seal edges with fork and bake at 425° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: carob pudding
directions: Blend 2 cups milk with other ingredients.
Pour into saucepan. Add other 2 cups milk and cook until thick, stirring often. Serve hot or chill and serve.

title: dirt cake
directions: In a food processor crush cookies until fine. Set aside. In a mixing bowl, beat cream cheese, butter and sugar until smooth. In another bowl, mix pudding and milk until well blended. Fold into cream cheese mixture. Fold into cool whip. In flower pot, alternate layers of cookie crumbs and pudding mixture, ending with crumbs. Chill several hours or overnight. Decorate with silk flowers or gummy worms.

title: classic banana cream pie
directions: In heavy pan, dissolve cornstarch in water.
Stir in condensed milk and egg yolks.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly. Remove from heat; add margarine and vanilla.
Cool slightly. Slice 2 bananas, dip in lemon and drain.
Arrange bananas on prepared crust.
Pour filling over bananas; chill 4 hours or overnight.
Spread top with whipped cream.
Dip third banana.

title: icebox vegetable salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large glass bowl; set aside.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Cook cabbage, drain well.
Place cabbage in baking dish.
Alternate layers of cabbage, soup, milk and cheese.
Dot with butter.
Bake in 350° oven 30 minutes.

title: sugarless fruitcake
directions: Combine raisins, fruit and water in saucepan.
Cook uncovered until water is evaporated and fruit is soft.
Set aside to cool. In a large bowl, combine flour, soda, salt and cinnamon.
In another bowl, combine eggs, applesauce, sweetener, oil, and vanilla.
Add nuts and reserved fruit.
Stir into dry ingredients and blend thoroughly.
Pour into a greased 10-inch fluted tube pan (9 cup size).
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until cake tests done.

title: spiced carrot strips
directions: Place carrots in a saucepan; cover with water.
Cook until tender, approximately 8 to 10 minutes.
Drain.
Combine butter, sugar, salt and cinnamon; pour over carrots and toss to coat. Serve immediately.
Yield: 4 to 6 servings.

title: woodchuck with dumplings
directions: Cut woodchuck into serving size portions.
Simmer in salted water for about 1 hour.
Remove meat and roll in salted flour. Brown in a large skillet.
Add water to the skillet to cover the meat and simmer for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix everything except 1/2 cup cheese.
Pour into an 8 or 9-inch round or square pan.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until skewer comes out clean and crust is browned.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: peach pie with praline biscuit crust
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in saucepan.
Bring to a boil, stirring often.
As soon as it boils, pour mixture into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish.
Set aside.
Combine margarine, brown sugar and nuts until crumbly.
Set aside.
Combine flour, 2 teaspoons sugar and shortening until crumbly.
Add buttermilk.
Mix until dough is made.
Spread dough on floured board and roll out into a rectangle. Spread pecan mixture onto dough.
Roll dough up into a jelly roll. Cut into 1/2-inch slices.
Top peach mixture with roll slices. Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: butter tarts
directions: In bowl, cream margarine, sugar, corn syrup, vanilla and salt. Stir in eggs, currants or raisins.
Fill tart shells almost full. Bake in 425° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool on rack before removing from pans.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix butter, sugar and peanut butter.
Roll into small balls. Refrigerate until set.
Melt chips and paraffin in double boiler. Dip balls into chocolate with toothpick.
Set on wax paper to cool.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Stretch, pinch together and spread onto a pizza pan.
Bake 10 minutes at 375°.

title: tomato cake
directions: Mix butter and sugar until creamy, add vanilla.
Add one egg at a time.
Add flour, baking powder and salt.
Add in tomato juice.
Add flour to raisins so they won't stick to the cake.
Mix in circular movement.
Pour mixture in 9 x 4-inch pan in 350° oven.
Bake for 50 minutes.
Let it cool for 10 minutes before taking it out and serving.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix in order given in a 1-quart greased baking dish.
Top with 15 crushed Ritz crackers.
Melt 1/2 stick of oleo and drizzle over crackers.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: guacamole
directions: Peel avocado and remove pit.
Mash with fork.
In bowl, combine all ingredients thoroughly.
Cover and chill.
Serve as dip for corn chips.

title: heavenly delight
directions: Break cake into bite-size pieces.
Mix milk and lemon juice together.
Mix Cool Whip with lemon-milk mixture.
Gently fold in strawberries.
Mix with cake until cake is coated.
Store in refrigerator 6 hours or overnight.

title: crabmeat toasties
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients.
(Heat cheese in jar in microwave or in jar in very hot water until cheese is soft.) Spread on split English muffins (12).
Freeze to set.
Keep frozen or use now.
Remove from freezer; cut into 4 equal parts and broil 10 minutes on low shelf.
Watch them so they don't overcook.

title: spiced tea cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Using solid shortening or margarine, grease and flour a Bundt pan. In large bowl, blend first 8 ingredients. Beat 2 minutes at high speed. Pour into prepared pan.

Bake 50 to 60 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean when inserted into center of cake. Cool upright in pan 15 minutes. Turn out onto serving plate. Spoon the glaze over the cake and sprinkle with nuts.

title: baked caramel corn
directions: Cream together butter and brown sugar until fluffy.
Combine popcorn and pecans in a shallow baking pan.
Add the butter mixture by spoonfuls and mix into the popcorn mixture.
Bake at 350° stirring two to three times, until crisp, about 8 minutes.

title: chili
directions: Brown ground beef with onion; drain off grease.
Add all ingredients in large pot; let simmer for 1 hour.

title: potato-ground beef bake
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet, stirring until crumbly.
Drain. Add green pepper, soup, salt and pepper.
Set aside.

title: french apple pie
directions: Mix sugar and cinnamon.
Mix with apples; put into unbaked pie crust.
Mix until crumbly the butter, brown sugar and flour. Spread on top of apples.
Bake at 400° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: cinnamon pull-apart coffee cake
directions: Spray Bundt pan with vegetable spray.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup pecans and half the brown sugar in bottom of pan.
Cover with cinnamon. Separate frozen rolls and place in pan.
Add 1/2 cup pecans, remaining brown sugar, cinnamon and dry pudding mix.
Drizzle melted butter on top.
Add additional cinnamon and remaining pecans.
Cover and allow to rise overnight.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Yield:
12 to 16 servings.

title: yummy cornbread
directions: Combine dry ingredients in mixing bowl.
Mix egg and creamed corn together. Stir into dry ingredients.
Slowly add milk to obtain consistency of thick pancake batter.
Pour into greased nonstick pan, filling halfway.
Bake in preheated 450° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
Can also be cooked like pancakes in a skillet for a delicious spoon bread.

title: cheese rice
directions: In pan, add butter.
When butter is hot, add cloves, cumin and bay leaf.
When bay leaf turns brown, add peas and coriander powder.
Add washed and drained rice.
Stir well.
Add salt and water.
When water starts to boil, cover with lid to simmer and cook rice.

title: sharon's banana bread
directions: Cream butter.
Add eggs, vanilla and sugar.
Add flour and soda.
Add sour cream and add the bananas.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: easy hollandaise
directions: Mix first three ingredients in food processor with steel blade. Slowly pour in butter while processor is running.
Reheat in double boiler with a little water.

title: stove top meat loaf(no egg)
directions: Season flour with 1/2 teaspoon of black pepper.
Crumble beef in a large bowl; add parsley flakes, 1/2 tablespoon black pepper and oregano; mix well.
Add cornflakes and mix well.
Add enough V-8 juice slowly to bind mixture; mix well and form into large, round loaf.
Dredge in seasoned flour.
Brown on both sides in skillet with olive oil using medium-high heat.
Place bay leaves on top.
Pour 1 cup of V-8 juice over loaf.
Cover.
Lower heat to medium-low.
Baste frequently using extra V-8 juice as needed. Cook for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: mexican lasagna
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Place 4 or 5 noodles in bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan. Spread 1/2 beef and bean mixture on top of noodles. Top with 4 or 5 noodles. Spread rest of beef and bean mixture on top.
Top with rest of noodles. Combine water and salsa. Pour on top of everything.
Cover tightly with foil. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours. Combine sour cream, onion and olives. Spoon over casserole. Top with cheese. Bake 5 minutes longer, uncovered, or until cheese is melted.

title: christmas wreaths
directions: In a 2 quart saucepan melt butter and marshmallows over moderately low heat, stirring constantly. When melted, remove from heat and stir in 1 tsp. of the food color and the vanilla. Add more food color if desired. Stir in corn flakes. Drop mixture onto waxed paper, 1 Tbsp. at a time. Decorate with red cinnamon candies. Let stand 30 minutes until cool. Makes 40 wreaths.

title: macaroon pie
directions: Spread sliced fruit in a greased pie pan.
Cream other ingredients and spread over fruit.
Bake at 350° about 20 minutes or until brown.

title: marge t.'s croutons for caesar salad
directions: Cut French bread into 1-inch squares.
Simmer garlic and oil about 5 minutes.
Cool down oil.
Place croutons, oil and garlic in Ziploc bag.
Shake it, place on tray.
Bake at about 300° until golden brown.
Then add to Caesar Salad.

title: holiday thumbprint cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease sheets.
Mix together the sugar, butter, eggs, flour, vanilla and soda.
Divide dough into 4 equal pieces.
Form each section into an 8-inch roll. Roll each piece into almonds and slice into 16 cookies.
Place 2-inches apart on greased sheets.
Make indentation with spoon in center of cookie to hold jam.
Fill with favorite jam.
Bake at 375° for 6 to 8 minutes.

title: dream bars
directions: Mix 1/2 cup brown sugar, flour and melted butter together and pat into greased and floured 9 x 6-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Remove from oven.

title: chinese chews
directions: Beat eggs until thick.
Add sugar, flour, baking powder and salt; mix well.
Add nuts and dates.
Bake in an 8 x 8-inch or 9 x 9-inch pan at 250° for 30 minutes.
Cut into small squares while still warm.
Shape squares into balls or roll in powdered sugar or coconut.

title: shortcut frozen salad
directions: Prepare pudding according to package directions, using 2 cups of milk.
Stir in Cool Whip, mayonnaise and lemon juice.
Fold in fruit cocktail, marshmallows and pecans.
Freeze in 9 x 5 x 3-inch pan.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: sweet rice
directions: Cook rice as directed on package.
In a 2 or 3-quart saucepan, bring water, butter or margarine and salt to a boil.
Stir in rice. Cover on low heat (just below boiling).
Cook 20 minutes.
Add milk, sugar and vanilla.

title: hawaiian pudding
directions: Mix crushed vanilla wafers and melted butter.
Press into 1 1/2-quart casserole dish. Slice bananas over crumbs.
Pour sweetened condensed milk over bananas.
Spoon drained crushed pineapple over all.
Cover with container of Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with small can coconut.
Then sprinkle chopped nuts over coconut. Decorate with 6 to 8 maraschino cherries. Refrigerate for several hours.

title: turkey chowder
directions: In a large saucepan partially cook bacon; stir in onion.
Cook until onion is tender.
Stir in water, undrained tomatoes, turkey, potatoes, carrots, thyme, salt and pepper.
Bring to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 30 to 35 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Mash slightly to thicken.

title: salsa
directions: Chop in blender.
Cook until thickened.
Put into hot jars with hot lids.

title: reese's chewy chocolate pan cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch jelly roll pan.
In large mixer bowl, beat butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat well.
Combine flour, cocoa, baking soda and salt.
Gradually blend into creamed mixture.
Stir in chips.

title: white chocolate cake
directions: In a large mixing bowl, let egg whites stand at room temperature for 30 minutes.

title: green tomato catsup
directions: Chop vegetables.
Add salt and let set overnight.
Add sugar, vinegar, spices and turmeric.
Cook slowly for 1 hour and put in jars and seal.
Makes about 15 pints.

title: coca-cola cake
directions: Sift together flour and sugar.
Stir in marshmallows and set aside.
Bring margarine, cocoa and Coke to a boil.
Remove from heat and pour over dry ingredients.
Stir in buttermilk, baking soda and beaten eggs.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: carrot cake
directions: Sift
dry
ingredients together.
Mix eggs, cooking oil and carrots
together and add to dry ingredients.
Beat hard. Bake in 2
layer pans at 350° for 45 minutes.
Top with Cream Cheese icing.

title: joanne's tamale pie
directions: Brown ground meat, onions and garlic.
Add corn, tomatoes and chili powder.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Stir in tomato juice, yellow corn meal and olives (drained).
Heat to simmering point.
Place in a 13 x 9-inch pan and bake for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Melt butter.
Add brown sugar; stir until well blended; cool. Add egg and mix well.
Stir in dry ingredients; add vanilla and nuts.
Spread in well-buttered 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° about 25 minutes.
Cool; cut in squares.
Makes 16.

title: light pumpkin cheesecake
directions: Coat bottom of a 10-inch spring-form pan with cooking spray. Wrap outside bottom and sides.
Position knife blade in food processor bowl; add the Ricotta cheese and cream cheese; pat smooth.
Pour into a large bowl.
Stir in pumpkin; set aside.

title: mock sour cream
