directions: Put all ingredients in blender on high until smooth.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix 1 stick of margarine with potatoes.
Add sour cream, onion, celery soup (as is), cheese, salt and pepper.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch baking dish.

title: seafoam pecans
directions: Beat egg white until foamy.
Mix in sugar and vanilla.
Fold in pecans.
Drop on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 250° for 30 minutes.
Turn oven off and leave in oven for 10 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Let cool.
Place in sealed container.

title: dolly's fresh apple nut cake
directions: Mix all except apples and nuts. Batter will be stiff; mix well. Stir in apples and nuts. Pour into a bundt pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: rhubarb crumble
directions: Cook first three ingredients until thick and clear. Add few drops of red food coloring. Mix other ingredients, except rhubarb until crumbly.
Press half of mixture into a greased baking dish. Add 4 cups of diced rhubarb, then glazed mixture, then rest of crumbly mixture. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: peel-a-pound soup
directions: Cut up ingredients and cover with water.
Bring to a boil; boil hard for 10 minutes.
Turn heat down; simmer 2 to 3 hours, or until vegetables are tender.

title: frozen yogurt pops
directions: Puree all ingredients in blender.
Pour into 6 (4 ounce) paper cups.
Freeze until partially frozen.
Stand a wooden stick or a straw (cut in half) in the center.
Freeze solid.
To eat, peel the paper cup off.

title: bonnie's blackberry pudding
directions: Cream the sugar and butter. Add flour, baking powder, salt and milk.
Spread in greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Top with 2 cups blackberries (or any kind of fruit). Sprinkle 1 cup sugar on top. Pour 2 cups boiling water over all. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
In a large bowl, beat eggs, sugar, syrup, butter and salt until smooth.
Stir in pecans and pour into shell. Bake 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 325° and bake 35 minutes or until center is firm.
Remove from oven and cool.

title: easy ambrosia
directions: Grate peeled apples; add pineapple, coconut and sliced bananas. Add orange juice and 1 can water.
Add enough sugar to sweeten to suit your taste.
Cover the bowl and let flavors mesh overnight.

title: hawaiian haystacks
directions: Layer ingredients desired on individual plates (let people self serve).
Go easy on the Chinese noodles.
Put gravy over all.

title: mom's pumpkin bread
directions: Cream sugar and shortening until fluffy.
Stir in eggs, pumpkin and water.
Sift flour, baking soda, baking powder, salt and spices.
Gradually stir dry ingredients into pumpkin mixture. Turn batter into 2 greased and floured bread pans.
Bake 90 minutes at 350°.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Sprinkle on top and bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: layered mexican dip
directions: In a souffle dish, spread bean dip over bottom of dish.
Cover with guacamole.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Cook broccoli and onion until soft.
Season with salt and pepper.
Add chicken broth and milk.
Make thickening with milk and flour; add to soup when just beginning to boil.
Add the cheese and serve.
Do not let it boil or it may curdle.

title: lazy day sweet pickles
directions: Pour all juice off pickles and reserve.
Empty pickles into bowl and chunk the pickles.
Return pickles to jar.
Add 1 cup of juice.
Add the sugar.
Re-seal and refrigerate.
Every few days, shake jar.
Pickles will make their own syrup.
Should be sweet and crunchy in approximately 2 weeks.
If not quite sweet enough to your taste, add 1/4 to 1/2 cup more sugar and continue to refrigerate.
Enjoy.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown beef. Add beans and heat thoroughly.
Place lettuce in large bowl; top with tomatoes, onion, avocado, cheese and Doritos. Just before serving add beef, dressing and toss.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown the ground beef with the cumin. Chop the tomatoes. Slice the ripe olives. Slice the onion in rings.
Chop the avocado, if using.
Mix them together and add as much picante sauce as you like for dressing.
Break up the tortilla chips into fairly small pieces and toss in last.

title: delicious venison roast
directions: Put contents of gravy mix into large pot.
Add water.
Mix well.
Add onion soup mix.
Put roast in pot; add bay leaves. Cover and cook at 350° for 3 to 4 hours.
Potatoes, celery and carrots should be added last 1 1/2 hours.
Shred leftover roast while it is still warm; add barbecue sauce and serve on buns for another meal.

title: easy stroganoff skillet
directions: In skillet, brown beef and onion until meat is browned and onion is tender (use shortening if necessary); stir to separate meat.
Drain fat.
Blend in soup and sour cream.
Add remaining ingredients; bring to boil.
Cover; cook over low heat 10 minutes or until noodles are done.
Stir again before serving.
Makes 5 (1 cup) servings.

title: spiced cider
directions: Heat cider, cloves, allspice, cinnamon and sugar to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Strain and serve hot with orange slice in cup.

title: dill pickles
directions: Pour vinegar solution in jar.
Seal.
Hot bath until all the green of cucumber has turned color.

title: quick beef casserole
directions: Cook the noodles in boiling water for 10 minutes. Drain and rinse with cold water to prevent noodles from sticking together. Brown the ground beef. Season meat with garlic and pepper. Add 1/2 cup of the cheese. Add the tomato soup, peas, carrots, corn and water.

title: molasses chip cookies
directions: Mix together flour, ginger and soda.
Set aside.
Blend together sugar, molasses, egg and oleo.
Add dry ingredients and mix.
Stir in chips (semi-sweet, peanut butter or butterscotch) and nuts.
Shape into balls and roll in sugar.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 14 minutes.

title: lemon broccoli chicken
directions: Cook chicken breasts until tender.
In skillet, combine chicken, soup, milk, lemon juice and pepper.
Cook until done.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Mix thoroughly. Chill approximately 1 hour. Add Jell-O and/or nuts if desired.

title: baked mostaccioli
directions: In large bowl, mix 1/2 jar sauce, Ricotta cheese, 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese and 6 ounces Mozzarella cheese.
Add cooked and drained mostaccioli.

title: cheese ball
directions: Allow cheeses to soften.
Mix together Cheddar, Roka, and cream cheeses.
Add onion and garlic powders to taste (be generous). Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Make one large ball or several small balls of cheese mixture.
Roll in chopped nuts.
Serve with flavored crackers.
This recipe will freeze.

title: enchiladas in a skillet
directions: In a large skillet, cook beef and onions over medium heat until meat is no longer pink; drain. Stir in the soup, enchilada sauce, milk and chilies. Bring to a boil; reduce heat and cover. Simmer for 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: clam dip
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Add clams and juice.
Add Ritz crackers and spices.
Put in a buttered dish.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350 for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Combine flour, baking soda and salt in small bowl.
Beat butter, granulated sugar, brown sugar and vanilla in large mixer bowl.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Gradually beat in flour mixture.
Stir in morsels and nuts.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Cook vegetables until tender.
Put into greased casserole. Mix onion, celery, cheese and margarine; spread over vegetables. Melt margarine and mix with crackers.
Sprinkle over top.
Bake about 30 minutes at 350°.

title: meatball stroganoff
directions: Combine hamburger, 1/2
green bell pepper, 1 onion, 1/2 cup mushrooms and egg.
Roll into 1 1/2 to 2-inch balls.
Bake or fry until brown.

title: impossible chicken vegetable pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°; grease pie plate (9 x 1 1/4-inch).
Mix chicken, zucchini, tomato, onion and cheese.
Spoon evenly into pie plate.
Beat remaining ingredients 15 seconds in blender on high speed, 1 minute with wire whisk or hand beater or until smooth.
Pour evenly over chicken mixture.
Bake about 35 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Let stand 5 minutes before cutting.
Serves 6.

title: honey-mustard dressing
directions: Blend mayonnaise with honey and mustard; whisk in vinegar and cayenne.
Add more vinegar if a thinner consistency is desired. Makes about 2 cups.

title: bluefish cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large bowl (except oil). Form mixture into cakes.
Fry or saute fish cakes in hot oil until golden brown.

title: dough for fried pies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Refrigerate overnight.
Roll out walnut size pieces of dough.
Add your choice of filling and deep fry. Makes 24 pies.

title: hearty cheese grits
directions: Combine water and salt; bring to a boil.
Stir in grits; cook until done, following package directions.
Remove from heat.
Add butter and 3 3/4 cups cheese; stir until cheese melts.
Add a small amount of hot grits to eggs, stirring well; stir egg mixture into remaining hot grits.
Pour grits into a lightly greased 2 1/2-quart baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Sprinkle with remaining 1/4 cup cheese; bake an additional 5 minutes. Yields 8 servings.

title: creamed cabbage soup
directions: In a large kettle, combine first 5 ingredients; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer until vegetables are tender. Meanwhile, melt butter in a medium pan.
Add flour, salt and pepper; stir to form a smooth paste.
Gradually add cream and milk to flour mixture, stirring constantly.
Cook until thickened. Continue cooking 1 minute longer.
Gradually stir into vegetables. Add ham and thyme; heat through.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: turkey pie with cornbread topping
directions: Combine soup, 1 cup milk, peas, carrots, pimiento and turkey in saucepan; heat through.
Pour into 2-quart baking dish. Combine flour, cornmeal, baking powder and salt; cut in shortening.
Mix egg and remaining milk; add to flour mixture. Mix well; pour over turkey mixture.
Bake at 425° for 25 minutes or until topping is golden brown.

title: big oatmeal chocolate chip cookies
directions: Beat together butter and brown sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla. Then add and mix thoroughly the flour, oats, soda and salt.
Stir in chocolate chips and pecans.
Bake cookies (2 to 3 tablespoon size) in a 350° oven for 15 minutes or until edges brown.
Cool on racks completely.
Yields 2 1/2 to 3 dozen cookies.

title: delicious dark chocolate cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients in large bowl.
Add eggs, milk, oil and vanilla.
Beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Remove mixer.
Stir in boiling water (batter will be very thin).
Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes on rack.
Remove from pan.
Cool completely.

title: deluxe buttermilk biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water; set aside.
Combine dry ingredients; cut in shortening with pastry blender until resembles coarse meal.
Add yeast mixture and buttermilk to dry ingredients and mix well.
Turn dough out on a floured surface; knead lightly 4 to 5 times.
Roll dough to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut with 2-inch biscuit cutter.
Place on greased baking sheet.
Brush tops with melted butter.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 3 1/2 dozen biscuits.
May freeze leftovers.
Wrap in foil to reheat at 350° for 15 minutes.
Open foil last 5 minutes.

title: biscuits
directions: Stir together flour, baking powder, sugar, cream of tartar and salt.
Cut in shortening until mixture resembles coarse crumbs. Make a well in center; add milk all at once.
Stir just until dough clings together.
On a lightly floured surface, knead gently 10 to 12 strokes.
Roll or pat to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut with a 2 1/2-inch cutter, dipping cutter into flour between cuts.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden.
Serve warm.
Makes 10 (2 1/2-inch) biscuits.

title: cheesecake by the bite
directions: Put 1 Macadamia nut in the bottom of a mini-muffin paper. Drop a spoonful of cheesecake on top. Bake.

title: angel dessert(easy)
directions: Cut top off cake (thin).
Hollow out cake by slicing around the edge.
Fill reservoir with softened sherbet or choice.
Place top back on cake.
"Ice" with Cool Whip.
Place in freezer until ready to serve.
Great made ahead and freezes well.
Slice and serve.
Very attractive on plate.
Can use filling to coordinate with punch for parties.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Combine and mix the first 7 ingredients in a blender.
Pour over carrots, pepper and onion.
Marinate overnight or longer.

title: scalloped tomatoes
directions: Saute onion until tender in oleo.
Add next 5 ingredients. Place tomatoes in bottom of greased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish. Add layer of onion and bread mixture.
Top with bread crumbs and oleo.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Yield:
5 to 6.

title: super spinach dip
directions: Combine spinach, cream cheese, picante sauce, green onions and cumin in saucepan.
Cook over low heat until cheese is melted and mixture is hot.
Stir in tomato and bacon; heat through.
Transfer to microwave-safe serving dish.
Sprinkle with cheese and microwave until cheese is melted.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: hungry jack casserole
directions: Brown hamburger meat; drain.
Add onion, brown sugar, barbecue sauce and beans.
Pour in rectangular baking dish.
Tear biscuits into 20 pieces instead of 10 and arrange on top of meat-bean mixtures.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° until browned on top.

title: molded cranberry salad
directions: Drain pineapple; add water to pineapple syrup to make 1/3 cup liquid.
Soften jello in syrup.
Cook cranberries in 1 cup water until skins pop; drain and add 1 cup hot juice to gelatin mixture. If needed, add boiling water to make 1 cup puree cranberries and stir in sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Chop celery and nuts and add along with 1/2 cup pineapple, ground orange and juice of 1/2 lemon to gelatin mixture.

title: fresh strawberry cheesecake pie
directions: Bake pie crust and cool.
Combine cream cheese and 1 tablespoon sugar; beat until smooth.
Spread in bottom of crust. Puree half of strawberries.
In saucepan combine pureed strawberries, remaining sugar and cornstarch.
Cook and stir over medium-low heat until mixture thickens and becomes clear (7 to 10 minutes).
Remove from heat.
Stir in remaining strawberries.
Let cool 10 minutes.
Pour into pie crust and refrigerate at least 3 hours.
Serve with whipped topping.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Simmer celery and onion.
Combine all ingredients and place in casserole dish.
Sprinkle crushed potato chips on top.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: cornbread casserole
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch glass dish. Mix all other ingredients and pour into dish. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: tamale pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In a 10-inch skillet over medium heat, cook beef and chili powder until well done, stirring to separate meat.
Remove from heat and drain off fat.
Stir in remaining ingredients except corn muffin mix.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat to low, cover and cook 5 minutes.
Pour into 2-quart casserole.

title: german potato salad
directions: Into bacon drippings in pan make sauce from the water, vinegar, mustard, cornstarch and sugar.
Cook sauce together with celery and onion and pour over potatoes.
Serve warm.

title: pork balls and kraut
directions: Mix pork, rice, salt and pepper; form into small balls. Spread half of sauerkraut in bottom of a casserole. Place meatballs on this. Top with the rest of the kraut. Bake at 350°, covered, for 1 hour. Serves 4.

title: favorite light bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Scald (don't boil) milk and water; pour over shortening and salt.
Cool to lukewarm.
In a separate bowl, dissolve yeast and sugar in lukewarm water.
Add to mixture.
Add 4 cups flour and beat well.
Add remaining flour.
The mixture should not be too sticky.
If so, add a little more flour.
Cover and let rise to doubled size.
Turn onto board and knead.
Make 3 large loaves or 5 small loaves.
Put into loaf pans and let rise to double size.
Then bake at 350° until top is brown.
When cool, slice and butter slices.
May wrap with foil and freeze.
Reheat when desired.
For a whole wheat bread, use 1/2 of flour whole wheat.

title: seattle 3 leaf salad
directions: Add first seven ingredients.
Whisk sugar, mustard, salt, vinegar and oil together.
Pour on dressing just before serving. Add seed last.
Toss gently.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar and salt in large bowl; set aside.
In a saucepan, add 2 cubes butter, 1 cup water and 4 tablespoons cocoa. Bring to a boil and add to flour mixture.
Mix well.
Combine 2 eggs, beaten, 1/2 cup sour cream and 1 teaspoon baking soda.
Add to the rest of the ingredients.
Place in a jelly roll pan that has been sprayed with Pam and bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
When cake is removed from oven and just warm, add topping.

title: crawfish cornbread
directions: In a pan saute crawfish, bell pepper and onions in margarine. In a mixing bowl, combine cornmeal, soda, baking powder, salt, eggs and milk.
Add grated cheese and sauteed mixture.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Yields 12 servings.
Contains 186 calories per serving.

title: pink fruit freeze
directions: Combine cream cheese, ice cream and salad dressing until well blended.
Fold in fruit cocktail and nuts.
Pour into 9-inch pan and freeze until firm. Place in refrigerator 15 minutes before serving.
Cut in squares and garnish with cherries.

title: ham loaf
directions: Mix the last 5 ingredients well, then blend in the meats. Just before baking, drizzle 1/3 cup orange juice over the top. Bake in 325° oven for 3/4 hour.
(Sometimes I cover it with foil half the time, then remove the foil for it to brown).

title: kheema(ground meat)
directions: Place chopped onions, garlic and ginger in blender with 3 tablespoons water and blend to smooth paste.
Set aside.
Heat oil in a 10 to 12-inch skillet over medium heat.
When hot, add cinnamon stick, cloves, black peppercorns, bay leaf and the red peppers.
In about 10 seconds, when peppers turn dark, add paste from blender, keeping your face averted.
Fry for 10 minutes.

Add small amount of water if food sticks to the bottom of the skillet. Add the coriander, cumin and turmeric and fry another 5 minutes. Now put the chopped tomatoes in, fry for another 2 to 3 minutes and add the chopped meat and salt.
Fry on high heat for about 5 minutes.
Break up all the lumps in the meat and brown it as much as you can.
Add 1/2 cup water and lemon juice.
Bring to boil and cover.
Simmer for one hour.
Serve with chapatis or parathas.

title: sweet and sour aspic
directions: In a saucepan, blend together sugar, water, vinegar and salt. Bring to a boil. Soften gelatin in cold water and add to sugar-vinegar mixture. Place celery, pecans, pimientos, asparagus, lemon juice and onion in shallow greased pan. Add heated mixture and chill in refrigerator until set. Serve on bed of lettuce and garnish with mayonnaise and paprika. Very good. Yield: 4 to 6 servings.

title: haystacks
directions: Melt the butterscotch chips in a saucepan over medium heat. When the chips have melted, add the peanut butter and remove from heat.
Stir well.
Pour in chow mein noodles.
Mix thoroughly. Drop the mixture by teaspoon onto waxed paper.
These will form "haystacks".
Let the haystacks cool and harden for 1/2 hour in refrigerator.
Makes 3 to 4 dozen.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix sugar, eggs, Crisco, baking soda, baking powder, cream of tartar, nutmeg and vanilla together.
Add 1 cup flour and 1/2 cup sour milk.
Alternate between two until all used.
Bake 1 cookie to test for flour content.
If spreading occurs, add a small amount more flour until firm when baked.
Sprinkle top with sugar before baking.
Bake at 375° until done.

title: cauliflower and broccoli casserole(7 servings)
directions: Combine all ingredients, except onion rings.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Top with onion rings and bake 20 minutes.

title: miracle whip chocolate cake
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Pour into greased 9 x 13 in cake pan.
Bake at 350 degrees for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: cherry pie filling cake
directions: In small saucepan, combine sugar, butter and milk.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly and cool.
Stir in chocolate bits and marshmallow cream.
Beat until thickened and smooth.
Spread on cake.

title: pan-fried liver and onions
directions: In a wide frying pan over medium heat, cook bacon until crisp. Remove bacon from pan; drain and keep warm.
Pour off and reserve all but 2 tablespoons drippings.
Add onions to drippings in pan and cook over medium-low heat, stirring often and adding more drippings as needed, until onions are golden (about 25 minutes). Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Remove onions from pan and keep warm.

title: impossible pie
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl.
Pour mixture into lightly greased 9-inch pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: best banana bread
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients well.
Mix rest into first mixture. Pour in greased bread pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: apple cake
directions: Bake in a greased and floured tube pan for 1 hour at 325°.

title: orange salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in the refrigerator.

title: chicken with herbs en casserole
directions: Saute bacon in skillet until crisp; remove.
Drain on towel. Crumble.
Saute chicken in bacon fat over medium heat until brown. Place in casserole and sprinkle crumbled bacon over top.
(Can have 2 layers if necessary.)
Melt butter in same skillet (after chicken is all sauteed), then remove from heat.
Stir in flour, salt, pepper, celery salt, sage and thyme.
Dissolve cubes in water; stir this into the ingredients in the skillet and add milk.
Stir over low heat until thickened and smooth.
(Don't turn your back on it or it will get lumps!)
Pour this over the chicken.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours uncovering for the last 15 minutes.
Serves 6 people.

title: wild rice soup
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a saucepan.
Simmer on low heat for 10 to 15 minutes.
Serve with crackers.

title: spicy sausage and lentil stew
directions: In a Dutch oven, combine lentils, 5 cups of water and seasonings.
Bring to boiling; reduce heat and simmer, covered, for 35 minutes.
Meanwhile, in a skillet, cook sausage and onion until meat is lightly browned.
Add to stew with remaining ingredients.
Simmer, covered, for 15 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: easy beef pot roast
directions: Put roast into crock-pot sprinkle with salt and pepper and onion soup mix (or sliced onion).
Do not add water.
Cover pot, set on low for 3 to 4 hours or until roast is well done and tender.
Meat juices can be used for gravy.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: the best grilled salmon steaks
directions: Place salmon in a large pan.
Mix all other ingredients (except wood chips) and pour over top.
Allow to marinate 3 to 4 hours, turning once.
Soak wood chips in water for 1 to 2 hours. Grill over charcoal, adding wood chips onto fire at same time as steaks.
Cook about 5 minutes per side, brushing frequently with reserved marinade.
Enjoy!

title: cabbage au gratin
directions: Cook cabbage 5 to 7 minutes or until tender.
Drain well. Place cabbage in lightly greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Combine soup, milk, cheese, salt and pepper.
Mix well and pour over cabbage.
Combine bread crumbs and butter.
Sprinkle over cabbage. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: berlin scalloped potatoes
directions: In a large skillet, cook bacon until crisp.
Drain, reserving 2 tablespoons of drippings.
Crumble bacon and set aside.
In the same skillet, cook onion in the reserved drippings until tender. Add spinach and heat through.

title: amaretto-pecan cake
directions: Blend all ingredients and beat at medium speed for 2 minutes. Add nuts toward the end.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan. Bake 1 hour at 325°.
When cake is done, remove from oven and immediately pour following glaze over hot cake (still in pan).

title: rosie's un-fried french fries
directions: Preheat the oven to 400°.
Slice each potato lengthwise into 1/4 ovals, then slice each oval lengthwise into matchsticks.
Coat a baking sheet with 3 sprays of vegetable oil.
Combine the egg whites and cajun spice in a bowl.
Add the matchstick potatoes and mix to coat.
Pour the coated potatoes onto the prepared baking sheet and spread them out into a single layer, leaving a little space between.
Place the baking sheet on the bottom shelf of the oven.
Bake for 40 to 45 minutes until the fries are crispy, turning them every 6 to 8 minutes with a spatula.
Servings:
4. Fat gram per serving:
Calories per serving:

title: fresh asparagus salad with lump crabmeat
directions: Trim about 2-inches off the end of each asparagus stalk. Bring a large pot of salted water to a boil. Add the asparagus and cook until just tender, 2 to 3 minutes, depending on the size. Transfer the asparagus to a bowl of ice water to cool for 2 minutes. Drain and pat dry.

title: cheese potatoes
directions: Mix together ingredients and pour into casserole dish.
Grate Cheddar cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes.

title: lemon bread
directions: Add 1/4 cup extra lemon juice to batter if you desire really lemon taste.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients well and refrigerate overnight. Toss together the remaining ingredients.
Pour dressing over salad to toss.

title: bean burrito appetizers
directions: Cook onion in a nonstick skillet coated with cooking spray over medium heat, stirring constantly, until tender.
Stir in mashed beans, salsa and next 4 ingredients.
Set aside bean mixture.

title: idiot-proof chicken casserole
directions: Combine soups, rice, onions and water.
Dump into rectangular casserole.
Arrange chicken pieces on top of rice.
Sprinkle dry soup on top.
Season with salt and pepper or Tony Chachere seasoning or Morton Nature's Seasons.
Cover with foil; bake at 350° for 2 1/2 hours.
Uncover and brown chicken pieces.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook rice before putting in mix.
Cook squash, drain.
Add all ingredients except half of cheese.
Mix.
Bake at 350 degrees until bubbly.
Sprinkle rest of cheese on top and return to oven until cheese melts.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together.
Add eggs; beat well. Stir in bananas; mix well.
Add the dry ingredients alternating with the buttermilk.
Stir in nuts.
Turn into well-greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch pan and bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: big mama's party mints
directions: Cream butter, sugar and cream cheese.
Add peppermint, then continue to add 1 drop at a time to taste if necessary.
Divide into sections to color.
Add paste coloring to desired shade; do not use liquid coloring.
Mold into desired shapes using mint molds, press, mini cookie cutters, fingers, etc.
Place on paper towels and cover with paper towels.
Let sit out on towels overnight to dry.
Seal in airtight container, then mints or dough can be frozen.
Beat if made up several days in advance and refrigerated until ready to mold.
Serves 70 to 75.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Cream butter with both sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Beat until fluffy.
Add dry ingredients.
Stir in Bits 'o Brickle.
Spread in well-greased 9 x 12 glass baking dish.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
When cool, cut into bars.

title: ham or steak-vegetables
directions: Fry ham or steak until brown on both sides in a large skillet. Lower heat.
Add 1 quart can of tomatoes.
Wash, peel and cut potatoes into medium-large cubes.
Slice carrots and cut onions into 4 pieces.
Break broccoli into small pieces.
Add vegetables. Cover and cook on low heat until tender.
Add salt and pepper to season.

title: chicken noodle casserole
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
Remove and reserve stock.
Bone chicken.
Cook celery and onion in stock.
When celery is cooked, add noodles and cook until tender.
At this point you may need to add a little more water or part of a can of cream of celery soup or your favorite kind.

title: ribbon fantasy fudge
directions: Combine 1 1/2 cups sugar, 6 tablespoons margarine and 1/3 cup milk in heavy saucepan; bring to a full boil, stirring constantly. Continue boiling 4 more minutes over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; stir in chocolate chips until melted.
Add 1/2 of the Marshmallow Creme and 1/2 teaspoon vanilla. Beat until well blended.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Repeat with remaining ingredients, substituting peanut butter for chocolate chips.
Spread over chocolate layer.
Cool at room temperature.
Cut into squares.
Makes 3 pounds.

title: rice casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except margarine; dot margarine around mixture; put in covered casserole dish.
Bake at 425° for 45 minutes.

title: congealed salad
directions: Mix everything together in a large bowl.
Cover and chill for a few hours or overnight. Serve.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a storage container. Then, put 1/3 cup into hot water. Stir and enjoy.

title: rice krispies treats
directions: Melt margarine in a 4-quart saucepan; use low heat.
Add the marshmallows and stir until melted.
Remove from heat and stir in the cereal until well coated with the marshmallows.
Put in a well greased 13 x 9-inch pan and press down evenly with a greased spoon. Cool and cut into squares.
Serve in a piece of waxed paper as they are a little sticky.

title: chocolate crunch cookies
directions: Cover bottom of well buttered 9 x 13-inch pan with crackers. Crush well some amount of crackers and sprinkle over top. Sprinkle nuts over crackers.
Combine sugar, margarine and 2/3 of chips.
Bring to a boil for 2 or 3 minutes and pour carefully over crackers.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes or until bubbly all over. Sprinkle remaining chips while hot. When they are soft, spread to frost.
Cut in small pieces while warm.

title: ham and cheese kabobs
directions: Clean and cut pineapple into cubes.
Cut cheese into balls (with melon baller) and cut ham into triangles.
Arrange on toothpicks.
Serves 24 to 30 people.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Thaw broccoli in colander under running cold water.
Saute onion in butter.
Combine soup and milk; stir well.
Add to sauteed onion.
Add Cheez Whiz and broccoli; stir well.
Heat for 30 minutes on low heat, stirring often to prevent scorching.

title: stream apple pudding
directions: Mix together. Grease bowl.
Put
dish into a crock-pot; fill halfway with water.
Cook on
high	for
3 hours or until done.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Cream the Crisco and sugar. Add flavoring.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk. Spoon batter into greased 10-inch tube pan and bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until cake tests done.

title: garden pasta salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.

title: air bread
directions: Mix yeast, sugar, 6 cups flour and salt together.
In pan, heat the milk, oil and honey to 120°.
Pour this liquid into dry ingredients and add beaten egg whites.
Add another cup of flour and beat with wooden spoon.

title: vegetable lasagna
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In 9 x 13-inch pan, layer sauce, noodles, vegetables and cheese.
Repeat layers.
Pour water over the top. Cover; bake 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Let stand for a few minutes before serving.
Serves 8.

title: weight watchers hopping john (rice and beans)
directions: In 2-quart nonstick saucepan, heat oil.
Add bell pepper and onion; cook over medium-high heat, stirring occasionally until softened, 3 to 4 minutes.
Add 1 cup water, peas, bacon, salt, pepper and hot sauce.
Stir to combine and bring to boil.
Add rice and stir to combine.
Cover and remove from heat.
Let stand until liquid is absorbed, about 5 minutes.
Fluff with fork before serving.

title: tomato relish
directions: Cook until tomatoes are done or longer if you want it thicker. Put in size jars you prefer.

title: c.m.p. cake
directions: Pat in 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: creamy garlic dressing
directions: Mix all in blender.
Substitute 2 tablespoons paprika for garlic for French dressing.
Makes 3 cups.

title: royal cheesecake
directions: Blend ingredients and press firmly against bottom and sides of a 9-inch spring-form pan.

title: clam dip
directions: In bowl, mix clams with lemon juice; set aside.
(Drain clams of juice.)
In skillet, melt butter; cook onion and garlic until soft.
Mix in clam sauce, bread crumbs and Mozzarella.
Add clams to mixture.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° in a casserole dish for 20 minutes or until bubbling.
Slice Italian bread thin and serve dip on top.

title: mock indian pudding
directions: Crumble Shredded Wheat into a greased baking dish.
Beat eggs, add milk.
Stir in molasses, salt and cinnamon.
Pour over biscuits.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes. Serve plain or with whipped cream.
Ice cream is also good.

title: apple crisp
directions: Mix sugar, flour, baking powder and salt.
Beat 1 egg hard and pour over dry ingredients.
Mix to make crumbly.
Sprinkle over sliced apples in 9 x 11-inch pan.
Melt butter and pour over apple and crumb mixture.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour.

title: apple cake
directions: Cream shortening; add sugar and beat until fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add sifted dry ingredients, alternating with milk. Add flavoring.
Pour into well-greased and floured pans, size 9 x 15-inch.
Top with enough sliced apples to cover batter.
Sprinkle apples with 1/2 cup brown sugar and 1/4 cup melted butter.
Bake in a moderate oven (350°) for 45 minutes.
Serve warm.
Makes 12 servings.
If you only want 1/2 of recipe, use an 8 x 8-inch pan.

title: apple kuchen
directions: Cream shortening and brown sugar; add flour and oatmeal.
Line a pan, 9 x 12
x 2-inch, with this mixture, reserving one cup of the mixture for the top of Kuken.
Boil the apples in 1/4 cup of water.
When partly done, add one cup sugar and 2 tablespoons cornstarch.
Pour into pan, sprinkling reserved crumbs over top. Bake 35 minutes in 350° oven.

title: chicken magnifique
directions: In a large skillet, brown chicken and mushrooms in margarine. Stir in soup, garlic and seasonings.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes, stirring now and then. Blend in sour cream and heat slowly.
Serve plain or over rice.

title: enchilada dip
directions: Mix all ingredients in crock-pot.
Heat until cheese melts. Serve as a dip with tortilla chips, Fritos or Doritos.

title: lettuce loaf bread
directions: Beat sugar, oil, eggs and lemon rind.
Add sifted flour, baking powder, salt, ginger and lettuce to sugar mixture.
Beat well. Stir in nuts. Bake in greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan at 375° for 55 minutes. Cool 15 minutes in pan. Remove and sprinkle with powdered sugar, if desired.

title: white cake good for wedding or birthday
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add flavorings and hot water.
Beat 1 minute.
Add salt, flour and water alternately.
Beat egg whites stiff.
Sift baking powder over batter and fold in beaten whites with mixer on slow speed.
Bake at 325° in 3 (9-inch) pans or a 9 x 13-inch pan until it springs back when touched lightly.
Cool 10 minutes in pans.
Remove from pans and ice with favorite icing.

title: fried cornbread
directions: Mix. Get grease hot and pour batter into skillet. Brown and turn. (When bubbles pop, it's ready to turn.)

title: strawberry pie
directions: Place sliced strawberries in baked shell. Combine water, sugar and cornstarch in saucepan. Cook, stirring constantly, until boils.
Cook 2 minutes longer. Add the jello after removing from heat and stir.
Pour over berries.
Let sauce cool before pouring.

title: ribbon jello mold
directions: Cream filling:
Bring milk and sugar to a boil.
Blend until smooth.
Dissolve Knox gelatine in cold water.
Add to milk and sugar.
Add sour cream and vanilla.
Blend until smooth.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream first 5 ingredients well.
In a separate bowl, mix next 2 ingredients to create a paste; then add to creamed mixture.
Mix well.
Alternately add flour, salt and buttermilk.
Mix well. Combine vinegar and soda in a separate bowl, then pour into batter.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes in three 9-inch greased and floured cake pans.
When cooled, frost.

title: new england clam chowder
directions: In a large saucepan, melt butter.
Saute onion, celery and potatoes until tender.
Add milk.
Simmer for about 30 minutes. Put in bowls or cups.
Garnish with parsley flakes.
Serve. Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: shrimp fried rice
directions: Brown bacon in large pot (you want the bacon to crumble). Set aside. In bacon grease, fry onions and bell pepper until they are soft. Add rice, shrimp and bacon (crumbled) back to the pot with onions and bell pepper. Mix well. Put in enough soy sauce to turn rice brown. Mix and serve.

title: prune cake
directions: Break eggs in mixer; beat well.
Add the sugar and oil and beat on medium speed.
Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with buttermilk with which the soda has been dissolved.
I cook the prunes and then I fold them in with the nuts and mix until they are all through the cake.
Pour in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 325° approximately 45 minutes.

title: chow mein chicken casserole
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°. Melt butter in a large skillet. Add red bell pepper, garlic and mushrooms. Saut until tender. Stir in green onions and next 5 ingredients. Pour into a lightly greased 7 x 11-inch baking dish. Sprinkle with chow mein noodles. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly. Makes 6 servings.

title: cream cheese spread
directions: Let cream cheese stand at room temperature until softened. Chop up dried beef in blender.
Mix all ingredients together and shape into 2 logs.
Chill.

title: steamed shrimp
directions: Wash
shrimp
in cold, running water.
Place in a large pot. Add
the
2 stalks celery, onions and lemons for every 3 to
4 pounds
of shrimp; do not add any water.
Use only what hangs onto the shrimp when you wash them.
Sprinkle liberally with
Old Bay seafood seasoning.
Cover pot and cook on top of stove
over medium
heat.
Stir frequently; the shrimp on the bottom cook first so keep turning them over until they are all pink
and tender.
Remove
from heat.
Drain (there will be a lot of fluid). Peel and eat.

title: perfect play dough
directions: Combine all ingredients until smooth.
Cook over medium heat (a heavy-bottomed saucepan works best) until it "almost burns," stirring constantly.
It will be quite stiff.
Knead on counter when cool enough to handle.
Lasts several months if kept in a tightly closed plastic container.

title: zucchini rounds
directions: Mix Bisquick and cheese together.
Add to beaten eggs and stir until moistened.
Fold shredded zucchini into mixture.
Melt butter or margarine in skillet.
Drop 2 tablespoons of mixture for each round into skillet and cook 2 or 3 minutes on each side.

title: honey bun cake
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and pour half into a greased and floured 9 x 13 pan.
Combine cinnamon and brown sugar.
Sprinkle half over cake batter.
Pour remaining batter over cinnamon mixture.
Top with remaining cinnamon mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.
Combine powdered sugar, vanilla and milk.
Pour over hot cake.

title: mama voyles' pound cake
directions: Cream the ingredients together, but add flour last.
Add eggs one at a time.
Pour into tube pan.
Cook for 1 hour and 45 minutes at 300°.

title: sugar imprint cookies
directions: Mix all.
Refrigerate overnight.
Roll dough into small balls (smaller than a walnut).
Roll balls into sugar.
Press flat with a glass dipped in sugar.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.

title: milky way chocolate cake
directions: Cream
stick butter and sugar and set aside.
Melt 1 stick butter
with candy bars in double boiler and set aside. Add
eggs to	sugar and butter.
Put soda in buttermilk, then add to candy bar mixture.
Combine with butter and sugar.
Add flour,
a little at a time.
Beat and add nuts.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: shrimp and crab dish
directions: Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: breaded chicken
directions: Mix wine with cream of chicken soup; set aside.
Mix margarine with bread crumbs; set aside.
Dip chicken pieces into soup mixture, then roll in the crumbs.
Place chicken on cookie sheet and bake for 25 minutes in 350° oven.

title: cake mix cookies
directions: Mix well and drop by teaspoon 2-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool on rack. You can add raisins, chopped nuts or coconut, if you like, before cooking.

title: cream potato puff
directions: Combine cream cheese and potatoes, mixing until well blended. Add remaining ingredients. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix together all ingredients in a saucepan. Simmer until mixture comes to a boil, stirring constantly. It has a tendency to stick and scorch. Boil 1 minute. Makes one pint.

title: potato soup
directions: Boil potatoes, carrots, celery and onion in water until tender.
Add salt, pepper, bacon, milk and butter.
Bring to boil.

title: mom's christmas fudge
directions: Put sugar, milk, butter and salt into large saucepan.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Cook at moderate rate, stirring occasionally, until it forms a soft ball.
Remove from heat immediately and set pan in cold water.
Don't stir or beat until candy is thick, creamy and loses its shine.
When at setting point, add cherries and nuts and fold in quickly.
Pour into buttered 8-inch pan and let stand at room temperature until firm. Cut into squares.
Makes 2 1/2 pounds.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Mix first 2 ingredients together; add other ingredients.
Mix everything together except sour cream.
Pour 1/2 of mixture in large Pyrex and let chill.
Then spread sour cream and pour remainder on top.
Chill.

title: baking powder biscuits
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Mix all ingredients in a bowl to form a ball.
Roll out on floured board.
Cut with glass 2 1/2-inches in diameter.
Place on greased and floured cookie sheet.
Bake 12 minutes.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix well.
Pour into a 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for about 50 minutes.

title: italian pork chops
directions: Select or ask your butcher to cut 1 pork chop per person, 1 1/2-inches thick.
Brush each pork chop with Caesar or Italian salad dressing.
Roll each pork chop in a generous amount of Progresso bread crumbs.
Place on a broiler pan and bake at 375° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: refrigerator cookies
directions: Blend shortening, sugar, salt and egg.
Add dry ingredients and nuts to this mixture.
Blend well.
Shape into a roll about 2 1/2-inches in diameter.
Roll in waxed paper and chill in refrigerator for several hours or overnight.
Cut thin slices of chilled dough.
Put on lightly greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Yield:
8 dozen.

title: sweet pickles
directions: Put the cucumbers in lime and water overnight.
Wash out 3 or 4 times.
Mix sugar, vinegar, salt, turmeric and pickling spice. Put cucumbers in mixture.
Let stand for 3 hours.
Boil cucumbers for 30 minutes.
Pack in jars.

title: homemade soup
directions: Mix the hamburger, potatoes and onions; cook until done.
Mix all other ingredients.
Let simmer for about 1 hour.
Good to eat with cornbread.

title: cream cheese chicken
directions: Flatten chicken breasts with hands.
Make a mixture of half and half of grated Parmesan cheese and bread crumbs.
Cut cream cheese in approximately 1-inch slices.
Melt butter in pan.
Set aside and cool slightly.
Dip chicken first in butter and then in Parmesan cheese and bread crumb mixture to coat.
Place cream cheese at edge of chicken piece and roll.
Place, uncovered, in a baking dish. Sprinkle with small amount extra butter on top.
Bake at 375° for about 30 to 45 minutes.
